    "10922117551101175512007/07/08 16:13:09legickThis chain is soloable.  I soloed all 3 quests as a 63 rogue.  For this first part just follow the dwarves i had to kill 3-4 mobs.  For the next part as said by somebody else you need to do it right outside the outpost and keep your back to the worms it will teleport behind you and be killed by the guards.  For the last part go to were they say and kill a clefthoof then use the Thumper.  Immediatly use some sort of a stopwatch and sprint and or vanish away.  At around 1 min 45 seconds burn evasion and go un-stealth right above his body hit him a couple times and at 2 mins he will die and you will get credit for the kill. Hope this helps!",
    "109223351710335172007/02/10 08:57:05kronixKilled 2 mobs + the worm - easily soloed by lvl 66 Shaman.",
    "109229391520939152007/05/30 21:19:37pechConfirmed, this is the easiest quest ever. Quite possibly, the miners you are protecting could possibly kill on their own every mob you encounter while \"escorting\" them.",
    "109222106410210642007/01/17 14:38:04DaAznSaNVery simple, albeit boring quest. I only faced three mobs along the way until we faced a worm-like monster (you may have seen them around the Bone Wastes already). Kill the mob and the escort should be completed.\
\
Note that the worm hits very hard. It was firing bolts of nature damage for nearly 1,000 damage. Make sure you kill it fast.\
\
This quest is the prerequiste to the quest Fumping. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10929",
    "1092257144260571442007/03/25 19:41:13KathadiaI'll echo that this quest is easily soloable.  The five dwarf NPCs can easily handle any roaming mobs, and the boss, with your help alone.  All you have to do is stay in the middle of the circle (so that they get aggro before you) and help with anything they go after.\
\
The dialogue from the quest is priceless, though, and worth transcribing.\
\
Chief Archaeologist Letoll says: Aright, listen up! Form a circle around me and move out!\
Chief Archaeologist Letoll says: Aright, <race>, just keep us safe from harm while we work. We'll pay you when we return.\
Chief Archaeologist Letoll says: The dig site is just north of here.\
(The team moves out to the dig site.)\
Chief Archaeologist Letoll says: We're here! Start diggin'!\
(The team spreads out and starts digging.)\
Chief Archaeologist Letoll says: I think there's somethin' buried here, beneath the sand!\
Chief Archaeologist Letoll says: Almost got it!\
