  ["Bark for the Barleybrews!70"] = {
    "11293705npcBecan Barleybrew23627npcBecan Barleybrew23627",
    "11293164830111644752007/10/08 17:12:11kaessaI just finished this on my own mount.  The trick is to complete ALL FOUR checkpoints, and then use your own mount to ride in for the quest turn in.  Don't try to use your own mount until you've completed all of the checkpoints.",
    "11293163979201639792007/10/06 21:56:52MegargonAfter you;ve gone to every checkpoint you can dismount the ram and mount your own mount if it helps. If you have an epic land mount it helps alot and also, I would use entropicdragon's route.",
    "11293163546301635462007/10/06 01:54:50UnknownHeroThe reward has been upped to 40 tickets instead of 15.",
    "11293164891111636462007/10/08 20:15:50mckaysalisburyYou can dismiss the ram, and use your own mount to finish the quest, but only if you have completed all 4 objectives.",
    "11293164165101641652007/10/07 09:20:09haloman800Here is the best and safest way to do it.... enter IF thru the left door.. when your inside turn to the right just enough to bark outside bank. after you have done that turn to the left and go  into mystic ward. after you have Barked there head thru The forlorn cavern, into the Hall of explorers, thru tinker town. and right when you have barked in the Military ward.. dismount the ram by clicking on the buff. get on your own mount (that is if your over lvl 40) and head thru the right IF Exit.. jump down the mountain but do it slowly so you dont die. then just run up to barleybrew or thunderbrew and turn it in!",
    "11293164010101640102007/10/06 23:37:38Fyrfoxentropicdragon's route worked for me. \
\
I'm a druid and after I'd  tagged all the banners, I galloped the ram until exhausted, then shifted to travel form.  Since the shapeshift is instant, you lose no time that way. Also, I  jumped off the road  down the mountain & made it back to the guy with no problem.",
    "11293164094101640942007/10/07 04:32:00DarniusYou can get around the entire of IF if you canter. Just make sure you don't tire your mount out before you leave IF. The last 100 meters to the quest hand-in and be laggy and you'll want as much extra time as possible. Had a emo moment this morning when I had heaps of time but due to heaps of people being at brewfest, I lagged and failed the quest. I've had a look at entropicdragon's map and I've added mine. Not sure who's would be faster but I think a full cicular route would be faster. I'll give it a try later on and let you know.\
\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=1537:160852199798222770176681207646238621272609301667330720392784468805522803576782629751668675689605708518711427696335670285628217598145545112470106402122345155317205268252237306215376211479222563]My Route Around Ironforge[/url]",
    "11293163646101636462007/10/06 08:17:55reykjavikThe easiest way to complete this quest in the allotted time, is to travel around the outer ring of Ironforge at a canter, dismiss the 'racing ram' buff when all objectives are complete, and use your usual mount to run back to the questgiver.",
    "11293163606211635462007/10/06 06:22:45LieandraThis is only a temporary ticket upgrade (40 tickets) because the Dark Iron Dwarves attacking is disabled do to bugs. \
\
When the Dark Iron Dwarves return, the tickets will return to the original 15 amount.",
    "11293164475101644752007/10/07 21:19:49nicksengThis quest is incredibly hard to complete if you're lagging, or if your machine has a low spec like mine. Try to set all your video settings to the lowest possible for this quest, and you should be able to complete it.\
\
Oh, and for those who complete the quest by using their own mount, i can confirm that that no longer works. You have to complete the quest on the ram, or you'll fail the quest.",
    "11293163594501635942007/10/06 05:55:25entropicdragonI have done this quest several times now on different characters, and I can now usually complete it with 15 to 30 seconds remaining on the timer (assuming it's not bugged.) [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=1537:]Here[/url] is a map of the route I use (I go the counterclockwise direction, but either way works.)\
\
I start with cantering (yellow) until I am at 80 or so fatigue, then trot (green) back down to 25 or so; after this I can usually canter the rest of the way back to the tent (I jump off the road out of ironforge at the nearest opportunity, it only hits for about half my life) without getting exhausted.\
\
This is probably not the only way, and I havn't done the math to see if galloping is actually more efficient (though I suspect it is not!) If you have a better route, share it! :-)",
