  ["An Apexis Relic70"] = {
    "11058170npcChu'a'lor23233npcChu'a'lor23233Ogri'la250Sha'tari Skyguard250111022211009311025411058511080",
    "11058114204201142042007/07/02 03:28:36NobbynobLittlunThe trick to Simon Says games such as these is to remember the sequence as a musical tune. The mind is much more adept at remembering the appropriate repetitions in this way. Then you simply have to learn to match each note up with a color/position, so that your fingers fly to the correct button, much like playing an instrument by ear.\
\
Or, you can get Ogri'Lazy. Slackers.",
    "1105814901841884152007/09/04 13:22:37Huckelberryor you can use your /say chat screan to type the order....",
    "110589049771882812007/05/25 18:21:04sandrockActually, you need to do 6 sequences correctly in order to obtain an Apexis Vibration.",
    "110589040881884152007/05/25 15:57:00TernusThis is a bit more complicated but this method will allow you to use your chat-log inside WoW to keep track of the patterns as they go.\
\
Join a private channel (something like /join (yourCharactersName)colors) and make four macros that send messaged to that channel, one for each color.\
\
Then you can just put the macros on your action bar and click them (or keys on your keyboard) as you watch the patterns.",
    "110588818220881822007/05/23 08:11:54NahazYou are supposed to use an Apexis Shard (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32569) on a Apexis Relic, then you click the order the relic shows you, if you manage long enough you will recieve a buff, Apexis Vibrations, that gives 15% increased runspeed. If you manage even longer you will recieve an increased time in the same buff (2h) and it's called Apexis Emanations.\
\
The next quest in the questline is to get an Emanation buff.\
\
Note: Apexis Shards are dropped off the local creatures aswell as Apexis Shard formation that I guess miners will probably be able to detect.",
    "110589363410936342007/05/30 12:12:53GadgetxBasically Simon Says, where the platform you activate has 4 different colors on each of its corners. Watch the lights shine on each color and then click on each color in the same order.\
\
Each time you correctly match one, the next code is 1 color longer, with the 10th (last) being 10 digits long.\
\
After 6 matches you get Apexis Vibrations, 15% run speed for 1 hour. 8 Matches will give you Apexis Emanations, same buff for 1.5hrs. 10 matches gives Apexis Enlightenment, 2hr buff. This buff lasts through death, works in all druid forms including stacking with Cat's 30% speed talent and Flight form. Very handy for the time it takes to get it, less than 5mins.\
\
You can simply open a chat message window inside WoW and type the order in there, then read it when you match the code. If you stand in the middle of the 4 colors you shouldn't need to move at all, just use the mouse to click.",
    "1105890893301884152007/05/26 08:48:07CamarisAn old-fashioned piece of paper works as well.",
    "1105888415800884152007/05/23 12:06:09MeeuwAllright, there is a lot of confusion related to this so I will try to explain this quest for you all.\
\
First off, you must gather one Apexis Shard (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32569). Then you need to locate an Apexis Monument. Around this monument, you will find 4 Apexis Relics. Go to one of them and stand on the white globe in the middle of the relic (Under the crystal). This way you will make sure you are in reach of all 4 buttons.\
\
Click the Apexis Relic and you will be asked to use your Apexis Shard. After a few seconds a beam from the relic will hit one of the buttons around it. When the beam has hit a button, you simply push the button it hit.\
\
Next level, the relic will hit two buttons. When that is done, you must push the buttons in the order the relic showed you. Continue this untill the quest is complete. I think it completed for me at level 5.\
\
To make this easier, have a second computer with a text editor. Asign a number for each of the buttons from 1 to 4. I.e.: You get this order: 1, 1, 4, 3, 1, 2. Type this in your text editor while the beam hits. Relax, and push those buttons in WoW while you look at your text editor for the order. If you dont have a secondary computer, try a cell phone. Good luck!",
    "11058109218101092182007/06/22 10:18:48superdifIt seems that this quest is very sensible to latency. For  example this afternoon I was having more than 1500 ms and often the ray showed up simultaneously. So don't even try it while you have lag problems, it is just a waste of shards and time.",
    "1105814866631884152007/09/03 14:50:42StompaMy method for remembering the longer sequences is perhaps even easier ... just open a speech line and type the letter for the colour that comes up.  ('R' for Red, 'B' for Blue ... you get the idea.)  You could whisper to yourself if you prefer :)\
\
/w Stompa RGRBYGR\
\
Then hit your \"enter\" key, and follow the sequence.",
    "1105899480161884152007/06/06 13:06:47DarmetheonOgri'Lazy is a great add-on for this quest.\
you can read about it and download it from the following URL:\
http://www.wowinterface.com/downloads/info7167-OgriLazy.html",
    "1105819597011884152007/12/04 15:10:46Ilovemuffinsor you can use your brain. Its not that difficult lol",
    "110588935530893552007/05/24 09:08:04CaligraHere is how i did it.\
\
I made sure i had the 4 color nodes in a square.\
\
Then i pressed \"enter\" to get my chat screen up.\
\
Then i put my pinky finger on 1, my ring finger on 2, FU finger on 3 and \"point\" finger on 4.\
\
Then i just made \
\
top left=1\
top right=2\
bottom left=3\
bottom right=4\
\
Then when it started to get hard, i just typed the numbers as it went along, worked great!",
    "11058102097201020972007/06/10 21:34:15moptopIf you have the 2h buff before doing this for some reason, make sure you click it off. When you get to the part where it gives you the small buff, it actually acts like you did the sequence wrong and zaps you and you have to start over.",
    "110589460410946042007/05/31 09:20:09sixnineI just used a bit of paper...was fine till I wrote over a previous one xD",
    "11058105700401057002007/06/16 22:53:58yurchDon't stop trying if you get one item in the sequence wrong. You'll be punushed 2700 hps for your mistake, but you can still select the correct one and keep going.",
    "11058115374201153742007/07/04 07:28:06chriswtI found the Apexis Relics at [b]33,52[/b].",
    "110581020461701020462007/06/10 18:33:40stormbreakerLocated at 31,61",
