    "1027423043170230432007/01/23 01:45:11blakeSummon the dragon at 72,43. He's a 70 elite, pretty easy to solo as a 70 warlock I just dotted him up and sacced my voidwalker and feared him. Hits for about 800 on cloth.",
    "10274130021101300212007/07/31 19:23:59colzwell soloed this quite easily with 69 frost mage.. but i had many problems with this chain.. RESIST, those creatures resisted nearly all my spellds FFS!",
    "10274163547101635472007/10/06 01:55:13gworrollSolo'd him as a prot pally in spell damage gear.  Plenty of these posts but few give more than vague hints of a strategy so I'm throwing this out.\
\
Used the horn, he came at me.  Judged Crusader, then put up Seal of Righteousness.  Judged Righteousness whenever it was up, and dropped consecrates about 3-4 seconds after they ran out.  Kept Holy Shield active throughout.  Used Retribution Aura, Righteous Fury(improved), and Blessing of Sanctuary.\
\
He got me to about 50%, he was just under 60.  Hammer of Justice and bandage to nearly full.\
\
Bit later we were tied for health around 30%.  Popped Divine Shield and FoL'd myself back to full and finished him off.  I could probably have gone all out at this point- Avenging Wrath, Avenger's Shield, outright spamming of Consecrate, but I had gotten this far with a somewhat aggressive(for prot) strat and figured it was time to play it safe and coast to the win.\
\
Really easy.  Was very low on mana at the end.  I could have eased this by using Seal of Wisdom or Seal of Light, and judging one of them as well. Could have also done without the consecrates and saved some mana.  But I went for a more aggressive tactic to bring him down faster, and he's wimpy enough that you have some leeway for that.\
\
He's tougher to bring down than the typical level 70 mob, but nowhere near the difficulty of the average 70 elite.",
