    "10842140638201406382007/08/19 14:35:03ShihliFor anyone still having bug problems, here's how I fixed it - your mileage may vary but it worked for me.\
\
At the base of the ramp into the room, there's a semi-circular pattern on the ground.  My lv. 70 mage friend and I (lv. 65 Shaman) stood in the center of the semi-circular pattern after starting the quest.  I dropped a Magma totem and she was spamming rank 1 AoE.\
\
The \"bug\" is that mobs associated with the quest (including the \"vengeful harbinger\" mob himself) instantly spawn, then despawn.  However, we would aggro the mobs *before* they despawned.\
\
Tricky thing was, when the Harbinger spawned, he became bugged - we brought him to 59 health and he wouldn't die.  So my mage friend dragged him back into the center of the circle and tried to kill him - didn't work.  So she proceeded to just run away and let him evade bug out (she ran to the back of the room).  The harbinger then proceeded to float into the center of the ring, get \"zapped\" and allow the quest to complete.\
\
So in short, here is how you can un-bug it:\
\
1)  Get a friend with a good amount of AoE.\
2)  Start quest.\
3)  Stand at the base of the ramp entrance into the room and begin spamming AoE once the Ancient Draenei Guardian spawns.\
4)  When the \"Vengeful Harbinger\" spawns, drag him into the back of the room and kill him in the center of the ring - if he goes to low health and cannot die, just run away from him and let him get \"zapped\" by the ring.\
5)  Profit!",
