    "10842102205501022052007/06/11 01:57:11Excellent1I just completed this quest a short time ago. Basically, I have been trying it every other level or so since around 64, so I've tried all the comments and suggestions posted here and nothing seemed to work.\
\
What I found out tonight, and subsequently tested by helping another group, is this:\
\
1. Kill the 3 waves anywhere, doesn't matter, as long as they don't kill the robot. You do NOT need to kill them inside circle for the Harbringer to spawn.\
2. Once the 3rd wave of mobs is down, back up to the very back wall of the tomb area. Let the Vengeful Harbringer path THROUGH the robot, who stands at the entrance to the circle.\
3. The Vengeful Harbringer will stand in the exact center of the circle, which is where you need to kill him. If you can get him to die in the middle of the circle, the robot will then walk to the middle of the circle, strike the corpse of the VH with a lightning bolt, then die.\
4. If done correctly, the corpse / spirit of the Vengeful Harbringer will float up and around the room and eventually spawn the spirit in the middle of the room that you can turn in to.\
\
The first time I did this correctly, I was completely stoked to have this completed. It wasn't until I helped the next group that I realized the position the Harbringer paths to (center of circle) and dies in (center of the circle) are critical to success.\
\
Good luck to everyone out there, and I hope this works for you.",
