    "9638103608101036082007/06/13 10:06:14seckidGradav can be solo'd too if you've downed curator and talked to wravien.  He's just a bit more tricky as you have to time the arcane protectors just right to slip past them.\
\
Ok..  a little preface. Gradav is in the back of the next cubby hole past wravien.  The problem is that you have to cut a wide path around the mana feeders next to wravien so they wont agro.  there are four protectors that you will have to time and watch.  a safe place to watch is after you jump down off the ledge and pass the mana feeders, wravien is right in front of you.  the first cubby hole is to the right.  jump up on the little ledge (cubby hole, right side) and watch em from around the middle bookshelf you can walk behind on the ledge.\
\
i noticed 2 protectors guarding this area.  after they walk away, after a slight pause, the protectors guarding the 2nd cubby hole will walk out of the way..  (briefly)!  this is your chance to slip past wravien and his mana feeders, turn right into the 2nd cubby hole and get to the back behind gradav and his altar.  the arcane protector that pats to gradav wont agro if you're stealthed behind the altar.  take a little breather, you've just completed the toughest part!\
\
once again as with wravien, you will only have 1 or 2 seconds to complete this quest and get the next quest before you die.  (i.e. good time to remove armor if you've got it on)\
\
Congradulate yourself on a job well done and release to the graveyard",
