    "1116570npcPrigmon23761npcZungam23897111164211165311195",
    "11165187118611868512007/11/18 15:34:46KindinosZungam is in a hut NORTH of Malacrass' room, not west.",
    "11165199916211967742007/12/11 22:27:24draguzaThis is a pretty good explanation of how to solo.\
\
I would like to add tho. If your a hunter, leave your pet on the ground near the water where you come out, when you release him, he walks down to the bottom, misdirect the guy in the middle of the room, and (seperately) the guy at the door, and run straight to the quest giver. You will need to feign death right there because there are 2 guards right outside the door who will aggro you (they are not connected from the inside it appears... at least they did not take to my misdirect well)",
    "11165196774201967742007/12/06 04:58:42GlowTo solo:\
\
* After you've killed Halazzi, jump into the water with the neutral crocs and swim behind the hut\
* Mount up and get onto the wall of the building that contains the Hex Lord (climb the grassy hill)\
* Take off your gear because you will inevitably die a few times before you succeed\
* Jump down onto the hut and click Zungam's ball and chain (his platform is safe from pats)\
* Run in the room and complete the quest as you die, it may take a few tries\
* Be prepared to accept the next quest in the series",
    "11165201437211967742007/12/15 00:25:41aaredYou don't necessarily need to kill Halazzi, but clearing the mobs to get to the lake is on the way to Halazzi. The hut is on the right just before the neutral alligators.\
\
Glow is right. But after releasing Zungam, he will slowly walk into the hut and stand in the middle of the ground floor (surrounded by two guards who will not kill him--it's not an escort quest). \
\
When he's standing there, you'll have two guards outside the hut entrance, one just inside the entrance, and one patrolling to Zungam's left and right.\
\
Priests: mind soothe works and might give you the window to accept the new quest before getting one shot. Fear also works.",
    "11165187683701876832007/11/19 13:45:07caseySo I tried to solo this quest, it kind of worked. You can avoid all the pats and run passed everything on your mount.\
\
Getting into the hut was not too tuff, Invis Pot + Nifty Stop Watch worked. I was able to get to him and free him from his ball in chain, but after he is free'd he walks down into the middle of the hut surrounded by mobs.\
\
I was able to kite them up the stairs and then jump down and turn in the quest, but I got 1 shot before able to accept the next.\
\
The Handlers have true-sight, so if anyone does try this, make sure to go well around them.\
\
=D\
\
p.s. I'ma a priest, would probably be pretty easy for a rogue.",
