    "10397205791102057912007/12/22 22:34:00hhallahhThis is easily one of the hardest non-group quests in the game, imo, for several reasons:\
\
1) Extraordinarily high mob density leading towards the named mob. Trying to run past anything is pretty much suicide since there are few places that are clear enough to lose aggro in.\
\
2) Very fast repop rate. 5 minutes at most for the normal mobs, no more than 2 on the named mob. Don't get caught off guard here, if you die or stall in your clear you'll probably have to start over. I remember one time I did this on my Warlock and I approached from the south (cliff) side and got stuck in a continuous battle where mobs repopped as fast as I could kill them until I died.\
\
3) Lots of patrols, and annoying ones at that. Rather than simply respawning, a lot of the mobs will spawn in the portal in the base and move back to their normal spot or route. This means that there's a fair chance that mobs will get in your way as you try to shut off the portal even if you've cleared the entire area.\
\
4) A couple trash mobs path over to the named mob... and then stay on top of him for quite a while. Either you have to wait it out (a minute or more) or fight two or more mobs at once... assuming they don't evade bug, which they can. Seriously, whose idea was it to make patrols that stand on top of the named mob for a long time, and then move? Either make them tied or don't, don't make people wait forever when there's a short respawn timer as is.\
\
5) There are several mobs around the portal that will path by it and aggro onto you while you try to shut it off. Also, shutting it off can be difficult because even if you know that you have to click and where you have to click, you need to be at the right camera angle in order to click and not have the game think you're trying to click on something on the other side of the portal. Very annoying.",
    "10397173067101730672007/10/22 09:17:17ZappymongFor me the hardest part was closing the portal. It's worth mentioning that once the key is obtained from Arix, there is a circular shaped thing floating on the southern side of the portal. This is where you must click to complete the quest.",
    "1039712491781273652007/07/22 09:45:37urbanmythThe Dark Missive (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10395)",
    "103976677150667712007/04/13 17:28:13WARBOSZThe Burning Legion Gate is north of Thrallmar - exit to the east and go north past the various demons. It's much easier to get to Warbringer Arix'AmalStick if you stick to the right side (with the mountains - east side) because you can avoid the MKI cannons. \
\
Mobs spawn fast and there's lots so don't linger too long.\
\
