    "10939152663101526632007/09/13 21:24:32sireynnSo can someone with a bigger clue help me out here.  How does this work with an affliction lock? specifically dots that cannot crit will that bump up my chance for when I shadow bolt greatly improving my chance to proc improved shadowbolt?  If so and i'm thinking this right this would be a pretty good DPS booster for affliction locks wouldn't it?",
    "10939104653301046532007/06/15 04:00:30johansenThe effect will stack and renew the 10 secs untill you get a critical hit. a very nice trinket for dual wielding classes.",
    "109391127991701127992007/06/29 10:10:03phinarEvaluating this trinket as if it were equivalent to a straight +crit trinket overlooks a lot of its real value. What this trinket excels at is making worst-case performance substantially better, not making average-case performance substantially better. For average-case performance, it still offers impressive gains to characters with low crit.\
\
For characters who have buffs that proc on crit -- Flurry, Unleashed Rage, Vengeance -- a long string of no crits can seriously harm your damage output, because you're waiting for that crit to amplify everything else. If you have a 25% crit rate, a streak of 8 attacks without a crit is about 10% likely, whereas with this card, it's only about 7% likely. That's about 1 in 30 fights where Flurry/Unleashed Rage/Vengeance is up consistently where it wouldn't be without. The average crit chance gain is only .6%, but the likelihood of very bad scenarios is significantly reduced.\
\
For characters who don't get AP from agility -- warriors and shamans, basically -- this trinket also offers a way to get a dramatic boost in crit rating without having to load on agility at the expense of attack power, strength, and stamina. You can re-select your itemization to account for the fact that this trinket will boost your crit and minimize your worst-case scenarios.\
\
Equating this trinket with its average case conversion to critical strike rating does not really account for the power of its stacking-buff model.",
    "10939160488611526632007/09/29 18:40:52EihristerHamalina's comment is valueable, because that would mean that it's pretty useless for a Shadowpriest, as they heavily rely on Mind Flay (Channeled) and Shadow Word: Pain (Damage over Time), with an occasional Mind Blast (direct damage) or Shadow Word: Death (direct damage).\
\
I was planning on getting this in combination with the Blessings Deck, but perhaps I should just sell it instead.",
    "10939152737611526632007/09/14 01:58:20hamalinaRead the tooltip of the trinket: \"Each time one of your DIRECT DAMAGE attacks does not critically strike, (...)\". In other words, dots won't trigger this buff to stack.",
    "10939189971111526632007/11/23 13:48:33MiwnaVery nice for an affliction warlock in raids. Since you'll use shdaow bolt between reapplying the DoTs. And since affliction warlocks usually don't use gear with +crit this trinket would boost your damage done.\
\
The drawback is that you already do heavy threat without the crits.",
    "10939155920211127992007/09/20 23:32:59SidonisI personally think this is a must have for Survival Hunters. The benefits of heading towards non-stop crit is just too much.\
\
1) More procs of Expose Weakness, thereby more often increasing the physical damage of the raid\
\
2) More 40% mana refunds on shots that crit.\
\
Coupling this trinket with 5/5 Master Tactician (6% chance for all ranged attacks to increase crit by 10% for 8 sec), and you can easily skyrocket your sustained dps (mana refund) and utility to the raid (expose weakness)",
