    "11294163600111635722007/10/06 06:11:43LieandraFor a little while the quest was bugged. Blizzard GM stated that the reason behind the bug was the amount of people playing the quest at the same time. However, Blizzard also recently posted a forum post about all the bugs with the brewfest.\
\
In any case. To complete the quest you must be on the ram (not your own mount) and have past all the flags. \
\
Like any other quest, when you complete an objective, the yellow colored text stating that completed objective will show on your screen. If that is not showing for you, then you are not completing the objectives, the quest is still bugged, or (as stated by the GM) to many players are attempting the quest at the same time.\
\
You have to note also, that you must return to the proper brewers ([b]Thunderbrews[/b] or [b]Barleybrews[/b]) to complete the quest you have chosen. \
\
As with other quests, the quest giver will appear as a yellow dot on your mini map. If you are having trouble completing the quest in time because the ram keeps walking; pressing and holding the down arrow button will stop the ram from moving, and provide you the time to open the dialog to complete the quest.",
    "11294163645301636452007/10/06 08:17:20reykjavikThe easiest way to complete this quest in the allotted time, is to travel around the outer ring of Ironforge at a canter, dismiss the 'racing ram' buff when all objectives are complete, and use your usual mount to run back to the questgiver.",
    "11294166966101669662007/10/12 21:28:52fullyjoey123i have been doing this quest for around a week now and for yesterday and today it hasn't been letting me do it.  anyone have any idea's how to make it work again?",
