    "10051171955201719552007/10/19 22:29:35SekaiPeople are vastly underselling the relative difficulty of this quest. The NPC walks as slow as it's possible to walk and for that reason alone clearing the path for her isn't terribly effective. What you should make sure to do is clear the patrols at a bare minimum and clean up the pair of warlocks parked at the south end of the circular path at Firewing Point. Usually aggroing those forces her to soak a lot of needless damage.\
\
Further, if she ever, ever gets tangled up by any of the warlock pairs in the very center of the camp and you don't have a partner to clean up the mess, just abandon the quest and run away. Unless you're level 66-67 as a melee or 65-66 as a caster you're going to set off a nasty chain reaction trying to save her that can bring up to 6 mobs down on your heads.",
    "100513454510345452007/02/12 07:49:17EskamoI found this quest to be Very buggy.  She'd pull mobs that wouldn't seem to move and you had no idea where to attack them (as a melee fighter).  At the end she almost died from two guards because I just couldnt attack them.\
