    "10051101393101013932007/06/09 14:14:48NightdragoonI did this quest thinking it would be a nice bonus to Cenarion Expedition rep, being that the NPC for this quest is of CE faction. Unfortunately, this quest provides no rep, which was a real bummer. But this quest is easily soloable and takes about 7 minutes to complete",
    "100519227610922762007/05/28 07:05:48DlateSoloed with lvl 65 mage, Really easy tbh u just sheep 1 of the mobs...",
    "100512568610256862007/01/27 11:39:17rpotorThe NPC that starts the quest is in a cage on the ground floor of the tallest tower (the one where you go for the Final Code quest). If she is not in the cage, just wait a little until she respawns, someone else is probably escorting her. To open the cage, you need no key, just speak with her and she will just walk out of that cage.",
    "10051208551102085512007/12/28 03:55:24AltoidAs a 65 Warlock, this quest was a joke.  I hadn't cleared out any mobs ahead of time, and while the NPC walks in her path with no regard as to how many mobs she'll pull (especially the casters), Warlocks have a VERY easy time here.  You can easily deal with her pulling 3 or 4 (which happens often).  Make the Voidwalker pick up the melee, and you pick up the casters.  They primarily cast shadowbolt so just slap on Curse of Tounges and pop Shadow Ward and they're cake.  Then finish off any remaining melee mobs.\
\
As with any escort quest, don't engage a mob unless she does - you don't want her ignoring something you thought she'd pull, then have her go on ahead!\
\
As some have mentioned, there are no \"scripted\" pulls or events that take place, no additional mobs will spawn, you fight what you pull in the process of walking her out.  Once you get past the far gate (down the road slightly from the main gate at Firewing Point) the quest will complete and she will shift into travel form and run off.\
\
I did not find this quest difficult in the slightest, but I believe that is in large part because of the combination between Warlock class abilities and the abilities (such as casters favoring shadow bolt) of these particular mobs.",
