    "109116279421592492007/04/05 23:23:14KinetiKSW:D is a good idea, I never thought of that and just chain mind flayed them down.  I missed a couple of imps which popped against the cannon but it never got below 80% health on north or south camp.  Also, I got no other spawns other than imps at the south camp.",
    "109114283010428302007/02/26 14:44:20triumphSoloed this as a rogue. Instead of backing up or sidestepping, I faced the cannon and just stayed put, backstabbing the imps as they walked past (as energy allowed). For whatever reason, even tho I was stationary, I didn't take any bomb dmg. About half got thru, but it was enough to get the port down before the cannon died.",
    "10911164597201645972007/10/08 03:59:54DeeBeeTo summarize:\
\
After converting the cannon, nothing happens until after your first cannonball attack on the portal.\
The cannonball & AoE flamethrower share a 15 second cooldown.\
The first cannonball attack causes imps to spawn non-stop from the portal -- about one every 2-3 secs.\
The imps explode in a short-range AoE to attack and head straight at the cannon.\
The imps have 450hp, according to http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22474\
If you one-shot kill them, they don't explode, they just die.\
If you hit and don't kill them, or generate threat in any way, they turn and explode on you instead of the cannon.\
\
You need to have a pet bar available and visible to do this quest. If you have addons that hide it, disable them. If you already have a pet, you'll have to dismiss it.\
\
If you convert the cannon without clearing the area first, the mobs will attack the cannon if they wander within standard aggro range. I had a wandering dog eat my north cannon from behind, since I was paying more attention to stemming the tide of a'splodin imps.\
\
Dogs (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22500) can / do spawn in at random intervals instead of imps. For me, southern portal spawned none, while the north one spawned two in succession halfway through the cannon blasts.\
\
Some claim that side-stepping, or stepping away from the imp as you hit it may help dodge their exploding damage. YMMV.\
\
If the cannon dies, just wait. It will respawn. Be aware that by this time, previously cleared mobs may be respawning as well.\
\
For shamans - totems are immune to AoE. Use that knowledge as creatively as you want.\
\
Everyone else - you need to figure out a class-specific way of mitigating the damage (heal, bubble, mana shield, plain old soak) or perform many one-shot kills (backstab, earthshock, fire blast, etc). Ideally, you'll have to find a middle-ground of damage soaking, and popping imps, leaving yourself some buffer health / mana / rage / energy to deal with the occasional dog.\
\
Good luck, and have fun.",
    "10911159753101597532007/09/28 07:43:25TigraineHad absolutely no Problem as a Affliction Lock to one-shot them with Searing Pain.\
They have less than 400 hp each.\
\
On the Northern Cannon there seems to be a Bug, sometimes Imp's don't get damage. But that's no big deal.\
\
For the Summoned Wrath Hound some people here mentioned for the Southern Gate, that's just a normal patrolling mob, kill it and you only have to deal with imps, nothing else.\
\
The Imps only explode for 500 damage if they come in melee range. If you either one-shot them or keep them at range you have no need for bandages/hp gear",
    "1091114678421378972007/08/30 17:58:22grawssScorch one-shots them, even as a frost mage.\
\
The problem is, during the north cannon, sometimes your spells just don't do anything. I'm not exactly sure why, but make sure you continue to keep the one you're on targetted even after your spells land, just in case you need to cast another.",
    "10911143228101432282007/08/24 06:16:27chimeraSoloed with 68 dw fury warrior. One item is very good here: essence infused mushroom... Use victory rush and BT to kill the imps.",
    "10911189471101894712007/11/22 12:38:12NefarionI'm doing this as a 60 warlock (in 2.3) and it's horrible.\
\
It's an easy start. Clear the mobs around the cannon and activate it using the item. Not hard. (Note though it takes away your pet!) Once you fire your first shot (on the pet bar), Imps will come in constant waves. They don't hit very hard and have VERY low health (Searing Pain can one-shot them), but they'll kill the cannon if they gather on it.. At the northern cannon after a couple shots I had dog-like creatures begin to spawn along with the Imps, at an increasing rate. They're quite a bit harder and will require a little more firing focus. Note that if you get swamped the cannon also has an AoE ability to fight these things.\
\
If you're an affliction warlock like me, be careful. Dependent upon my Imp for mana, I was surprised to see that Blizzard de-spawns your pet when you take control of the cannon. Though I had no issues with the southern cannon, this proved a problem for the northern cannon. Out of the 5 times I attempted it I got an add (the huge orange dog) 4 times, and having resorted to Life Tapping for mana (even with bandages and a healthstone) I found that (having spammed Searing Pain) by the time he came I had too little health and mana to take care of just him, let alone the waves of Imps and doggies still crashing into my cannon.\
\
I eventually just gave up. I'll re-visit the quest at a later time when I'm stronger.",
