  ["Stasis Chambers of the Mana-Tombs70"] = {
    "1097770npcImage of Commander Ameer20482npcImage of Commander Ameer20482110976210977",
    "109771382881811372242007/08/15 10:36:15PalehoofIt appears that if you complete this quest before being Exalted you can simply repeat the quest to get another key to the chamber in Heroic Mana Tombs, until you are Exalted.",
    "10977104224501042242007/06/14 10:15:24bessemerIt is possible to solo this as a mage. At the begining of the instance, wait for the pats to get close enough to the stationary 2 and then frost nova them all. Blink past and start your invis fade. The nova is important because using invis to get past all of them will result in reappearing right under the 1st boss. After you're invis, start moving toward where the 1st boss is. Stop moving when you get to the threshold of that hallway. Doing all of this takes a few tries but it will work.\
\
Now you afk for the invis cooldown. Take a look at the screenshot above. The druids minimap shows you where the cell is. Once you invis to that spot, inch your way up, being mindful of the mana leeches. You should be able to get just close enough to open the cell.\
\
Worked for me.",
    "10977134371201343712007/08/08 12:09:54BloodshotEasier done without the frost nova, especially if you don't have a water elemental to frost nova from range. Inch up to the first 2-pull, click invis and start moving forward. If timed appropriately you should be right next to them when you become invisible. Boots with minor run speed can help a great deal. Go slightly past the entrance to the tunnel behind Pandemonius and stop. \
\
After your invisibility cooldown is up, use it again, turn left and go as far north as possible into the blocked hallway. You should make it with time to spare. After invisibility fades, slowly move forward until you can activate the cell.",
    "1097796517141928782007/06/03 05:11:21ryodzeusAfter complete this quest, you'll get either one of two quests below depend on your rep.\
\
Revered:  http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10981\
Exalted: http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10982\
\
As state above, Revered rep will get only 1 time used key (which have to farm another mark of nexus-king,  but as your rep is exalted, you'll get permanent key without farming any further.",
    "10977139502101395022007/08/17 10:17:20CashewsJust soloed it with my lock.  I needed 2 invis potions, my stopwatch, and one soulstone.  This will come very close so if you stop for even a second you will probably fail.  It took me 3 attempts.\
\
First get naked as you will have to die once.  Place a SS on yourself and wait for the pat to move past the 2 guards. Start running.  Just as you get to the arch in the hallway use your first invis potion.  Run into the room with Pandemonius and just behind and to the right there is a raised area. The goal is to get on top of that and as far to the back end as possible of it.  Unfortunately your invis will run out just before you reach the bottom of the raised area.  I have instant cast howl of terror so just as i reached the foot of it i used that to give me the second or 2 to reach the top before they killed me.  I rezed via the SS and waited 10 minutes for another invis potion.  \
\
Once invis was back i used my stopwatch to increase my speed, started running and used my second invis pot.  The invis pot ran out just as i was entering the caved in doorway just behind the chamber.  \
\
The worms in front of the chamber move around a bit and can agro when opening the chamber so watch their movements for the key second to open the chamber, and only get as close to the chamber as absolutely necessary.",
    "10977198406111862172007/12/09 07:37:44HephHad to put the camera view under my feet looking up, right click the key then click the chamber. Tricksy.",
    "1097710687931928782007/06/19 05:04:39GrinnBeen revered at the moment, should i wait until Exalted or can i complete both quests to get  badges now and a permanent key later?",
    "1097718027931927012007/11/06 22:09:11KaurothConfirmed today.\
\
If you wait for a few seconds, you don't even have to Sooth the Wyrm, he moves far enough away.\
\
Just go to the back of the chamber near the empty room.",
    "10977137224301372242007/08/13 14:59:03WildhornI was wondering the same.\
\
If you complete it when you are revered, can you still get the perma key once you are exalted?",
    "1097720674221928782007/12/24 19:20:50ContayYou can go ahead and complete the quest safely -- the followup will change accordingly when your rep increases later.",
    "10977185511201855112007/11/16 02:32:54psionicIt is currently bugged.  It doesn't seem like you can click it at all.  The way to do it is adjust your camera so you can see INSIDE the purple orb, then you can click it like normal.",
    "1097792701140927012007/05/28 19:50:21m0nrEasy to solo as a druid or rogue. If you're a druid just cast Sooth Animal on the nearest Mana Leech and you should be able to open the Chamber without agroing them. If you are a rogue you might have to use one of those items that reduce your agro radius before you attempt to open it.",
    "1097792878100928782007/05/29 04:59:47ArriesIf you are exalted with them he'll give you shafar's chamber key without asking for another nexsus mark.",
    "10977199981211862172007/12/12 03:05:27anathorThis method didn't work for me (maybe I understood it wrong), what worked for me though was just facing the sphere and moving the camera up - so that I would be looking down at myself, except I would basically see above the bottom of the pink bubble. Then when I saw the base I could find the cog easily.\
\
Also for druids it's possible to solo it easily but you need Soothe Animal for one of the mana-feeders. I had to go back to TB to learn it :-)",
    "10977186727311862172007/11/18 01:17:44AnXiYzconfirmed.  this method worked for me.",
    "10977197323111862172007/12/07 07:12:14GreinConfirming, method worked fine for me as well.",
    "10977186322511862172007/11/17 12:20:19ozgulI noticed that when I turned my back to the sphere and then turned the camera angle against the sphere and looked upwards, I could click the spheres outer layer from inside. It took a bit of trying but managed it after a while.",
    "10977167695211650132007/10/13 16:26:46ReklessCorrect.  However, this part of the chain doesn't summon Yor.  You're opening the chamber after the Void Spawn boss, not the chamber near Shaffar.\
