    "105186986610698662007/04/19 23:25:29DoilynNext to the tower is a big rock with a flat top. If things go badly, you can jump on it to make the enemies evade, saving you from certain death.",
    "1051820245711137732007/12/16 17:19:38asQarneI soloed this quest today without any trouble (as a level 68 feral druid) and I can confirm that the waves are indeed 2, 3, [b]3[/b], boss. (Not 2, 3, [b]4[/b], boss as stated below.) The first wave consists of two [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=21294]Bloodmaul Goons[/url] (melee fighters), the follow two are two Goons and one [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=19956]Bloodmaul Lookout[/url] (caster). The mobs will not attack you, nor can you attack them, while they run up the tower ramp.\
\
Also; the boss, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=20116]Gurn Grubnosh[/url], will enrage at one point during the fight for about 5-7 seconds - it's possible to stun him during this effect to minimize the damage taken. Good luck. :)",
    "10518164602101646022007/10/08 04:20:32DhcstabThere is alot of good info about the locations of the champion and the tower.  This is just a tip for rogues\
\
I was able to solo this as a level 67 combat swords rogue.  Easier than I expected, didn't have to use a health pot.\
\
Tips:\
For the first wave just dps both down, no cooldowns needed.\
\
For 2nd wave, make sure you are stealthed at the top of the tower (after either bandaging or eating until full health).  The three mobs will make their way up from the bottom.  Make sure you target the geomancer and mash your opener as it arrives at the top.  There will be a period where the mobs are unable to be attacked, but if you keep hitting your opener (I recommend cheap shot) you will get it off before they hit you.  For this wave use Blade fury and cloak of shadows to stop some damage from the caster.  Should be a fairly simple affair\
\
3rd wave: Same as 2nd in that you need to make sure you get your opener off before they hit you.  Target any mob as they all are melee classes and do roughly the same damage.  Once you get your opener off and have slice and dice active use evasion + adrenaline rush to burn them down.\
\
Final wave: Simple make sure you have full health and burn him :) One thing to remember is that he enrages so make sure you have some combo points for a kidney shot.  His enrage should wear about the same time as your stun.  When he is not enraged he dosent hit that hard so you will kill him before he kills you.\
\
Hope that helps.",
    "10518195795101957952007/12/04 07:34:03Dr00dSoloed this very easy as lvl 67 feral druid.",
    "1051813773320137732006/12/12 03:06:57keller999Tough to solo, but do-able.  The tower you're looking for is at 46, 74.  Plant the banner on top of the tower to start the event.\
\
You'll face several waves of ogre baddies, starting with just two.  The waves spawn at the foot of the tower, run all the way to the top, and then turn aggressive towards you.  You can get to about midtower and drink without them aggroing if you run through them as they go up.\
\
The mobs themselves are pretty standard orcs, no elites.  As a mage, I polymorphed one mob, and then used the circular ramp to frostnova and kite the remaining ones until they're dead.  Then, I can kill the last poly no problem.\
\
There are four waves.  I'm not sure if the waves are the same each time.  These are the waves I got.\
\
- 2 orcs\
- 3 orcs\
- 3 orcs\
- Gurn Grubnosh\
\
Gurn himself is no big deal - he hits kinda hard, but some good crowd control/roots will take care of that.\
\
The quest text talks like the quest is an elite, my guess is that it will be come BC release.",
    "10518177220201772202007/10/31 09:40:02smooRogue:\
\
1. Clear Tower.\
2. Start Event.\
3. First Wave: Stealth. Wait for them to turn Aggro, distract, sap one. Kill one.\
4. Second Wave: Stealth. Wait again, Sap one. Bladefury remaining both.\
5. Third Wave: Stealth. Wait, Sap. Attack one, Blind the other, kill while blind, or get him as low as possible.\
6. Repeat Step 4.\
7. Kill the \"boss\". Make sure to start evasion when he turns crazy (~40%)",
