    "10921159731201597312007/09/28 06:29:22Soundfx4Too many people are throwing the word easy around, and occasionally I see the words, \"really easy\" or \"very easy\".  Well, I just tried this, and the verdict is that it is not an easy solo.  It definitely isn't the hardest fight, and it is the easiest elite I've ever faced, but it certainly can't be defined as easy.  Going with the suggested 3 people would, however, be very easy =P\
\
This is how I did it as a 66 feral druid solo.\
\
Pounce, Mangle, rake, rake or pounce again until max combo points.\
\
Then Rip, shift out throw rejuv, and lifeblooom on, then go bear and use frenzied regeneration when needed.  Took me down to about 3.3 k health.  Overall it wasn't that difficult, but still, not easy.",
    "10921212158111335122008/01/03 11:20:08JamieEiSame thing here, 66 druid. Not a hard solo.",
    "10921208955102089552007/12/28 19:09:58tgr316Soloed as a 70 shadow priest. Easy to do, just make sure you're not being careless. PWShield, go though the normal spell rotation, repeat.",
    "10921143252401432522007/08/24 07:54:39AthelaDead easy as a (badly geared) 70 Moonkin Druid. Open with Force of Nature for that little bit of extra DPS and 2x Starfire (i got a lucky crit). The DoT her up with Moonfire and Insect swarm, pop Barkskin and spam Wrath (or Starfire while the barkskin's up, if you want) until dead. She hits pretty hard so   keep the Wrath spam up at full speed and drop her quick.\
\
Ended the fight with 60-70% health and mana, so I doubt it'll be too much of a problem for lower level Moonkins (unless you've crossed over to the dark side and are wearing lots of cloth ;))\
\
You might want to save the Barkskin to let you get a trouble-free heal off later in the fight if you're not confident, though.\
\
Good luck!",
    "10921134440301344402007/08/08 14:32:31CrakkerzFor those w/o coordinates, easiest way to find is to enter Netherweb Ridge at it's northern point and follow the hillside south.  You'll shortly come to where the ridge / drop-offs start.  \
\
You CANNOT miss the gigantic brown spider legs sticking up over the ridge.  This guy gave me a heart-attack the first time I stumbled across him.",
    "10921195243101952432007/12/03 05:31:15Weltall189Solo'd as a lv 65 BM hunter, it was a very easy fight, sent it in pet, pop all your CDs and just keep your pet healed.  Took him down in like  20sec.",
    "10921210560102105602007/12/31 15:44:52fragoSolo'd with a 65 Protect Pally in quest gear. \
Judged Wisdom kept Wisdom on weapon and just healed. Used a sword and board. Ret Aura . Blessing of Sanct. Holy shield when Redoubt went off. \
Took awhile was pretty epic but no chance really of failure, just outlasted it a pecked away.\
Definately an easy 65 elite.",
    "109216174520617452007/04/03 19:55:50soulstone65 Demo Warlock\
Buffs: Regular warlock talent buffs, Blessing of Auchindoun, Adept's Elixir, Spirit Scroll, and Elixir of the Sages, +Spell Damage Trinket.\
\
Spider is immune to Fear and has pretty nasty poison dot. No adds to worry about, but be careful where you run since it's located on rough terrain by a cliff.\
\
Let Felguard tank a good bit, applied dots, and health funneled to keep Felguard healthy. Repeat dots, but try not overheal Felguard or you will take aggro and spider will tear you apart. Finished it off with Incinerate. Had healthstone ready but was not necessary.",
    "10921192358201923582007/11/27 17:15:42LuciferiSolo'd as a 64 Demo Warlock\
\
Importat part here for me was casting curse of weakness first. FG w/ health funnel cant maintain the damage without that. so basically technique goes:\
\
Send in FG:\
CoWeakness\
Corruption\
Health funnel, Health funnel, Health funnel\
Corruption\
Drain Life\
Health funnel, Health funnel, Health funnel\
\
Pretty straight forward. Took about 2mins and ended up with 50% health for myself and FG. \
\
Coords 54.81 confirmed",
    "10921118065201180652007/07/09 12:52:01pik4chuSoloed as a 66 SV hunter a while back by kiting around using imo traps and stings and aspect of cheetah, she is immune to snares for the most part so it took a while. \
\
Came back at 70 BM spec and easily straight tanked her for someone.\
\
Killed her as a 67 sub rogue, basically lots of stunlock, evasion and backstabing, wasnt too dangerous, brought along an evasion trinket (quest reward out of terrokar i think tho there are others) and used that too, really wasnt necesarry but meh, ended with nearly full hp\
\
going to be doing her again in the future once my druid gets closer in levels",
    "10921198450101984502007/12/09 10:07:05SqueezieSoloed as lvl 66 enhc shaman without too much problems. My first tactic was to just use earth elemental to tank, but after I engaged it, I found out my earth elemental still was on a 5 minute CD, so I just tanked it meself and healed when needed to. Not too much problems, would definitly be easy as hell with earth elemental though.",
    "10921159263101592632007/09/27 07:39:33ShivacodeDuo'd with a 64 frostmage and 66 shadow priest (me). Kept dots + VE up, used shadowfiend for mana restore + extra DPS, frost mage used elemental. Didn't use any pots, I \"tanked\" it easily. VE kept us both alive.",
    "10921140337201403372007/08/18 23:10:12thosanThis quest is NOT easy done solo, went in as a lvl 65 demon spec lock and got pounded 5 times.",
    "109218517220851722007/05/18 12:43:08deadaloneSolo'd as a 65 Affliction warlock. Used Imp for the stamina bonus and higher damage since my VW can't hold aggro.. Just used blood fury / spell damage trinket , amp CoA and spammed drain life and shadowbolts when night fall proc'd. Pretty easy.",
