  ["A Job Unfinished...70"] = {
    "1104170itemPartially Digested Hand32621npcOverlord Mor'ghor23139Netherwing250",
    "110419811310981132007/06/04 14:37:57WildhornWhen they run away and change color, if you damage them, they will enrage.\
\
Soloed as a balance druid (keep the 3 HoTs on you and keep the 2 DoTs on it, try to avoid to damage it when it run away, because when they enrage, they hurt really bad, use Barkskin in that case). It is stunnable (warstomp), but not rootable.",
    "11041108360101083602007/06/21 03:02:53zipp0Both elites fear, but it's not the fear that will get you adds (it's a very short fear), its when they change color and run. They are FAST and can run pretty far. I cleared a big area and still ended up with 2 adds (and died) because the elite ran all over the place.\
\
Very annoying to solo as a warlock since they are immune to fear and dot ticks will set off their enrage. I had to basically just heal pet and shadowbolt in between.",
    "110419274741917662007/05/28 21:41:21andersleetThe color change and \"running\" is a sort of stone shield (watch the smaller versions, they just stand still when they go into this mode).  If you damage it enough while it is in that mode, it will enrage.",
    "110418785950878592007/05/23 00:37:32RedcrosseThe quest starter drops from Arvoar the Rapacious http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=23267 who pats around in a small circle around 74,86.\
\
You get 250 Netherwing rep on completion.",
    "11041128977101289772007/07/30 01:56:03DirtypriestBoth arvoar and the den mother are soloable for a shadow priest.\
\
As others said clear the area well enough so you are not feared into adds or the mob doesnt run into any either when they run away with their enrage shield on.\
\
Its very hard to avoid damaging it when the mob runs and pops his enrage shield. So I suggest to start a heal as soon as it does this. You will need at least 1 mana pot (I used pvp mana pot). I have about 750 damage, 10k health, 8k mana, and 24% to crit. I died a few times figuring out what the trick to arvoar is, but the den mother took 1 try (since it is exactly the same). So it shouldn't be that much harder for someone with lesser gear.",
    "11041211376111999002008/01/02 04:54:31NatortotNo.  To attain neutral all you have to do is complete the questline, http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10804 started by,http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22113  ,the guy on the ground.  A 9 part chain that ends with you being neutral.",
    "110419543730954372007/06/01 15:10:31mdgames5000The money reward is now 20g 79s as of 2.1",
    "11041182460101824602007/11/11 15:08:20ikkiHow many kinds of \"This item begins a quest\" Can be found in netherwing? :O",
    "110419120920912092007/05/26 17:57:10SuhovMob who drops Quest Item wich starts this quest got 29k HP, and objective elite got 31k HP.  COmplitely easy for 2 players of any class. But need to clear around some mobs before pull.",
    "11041200887102008872007/12/13 21:45:40CynthrinThis is very easy to solo as a feral druid.\
\
Clear the entire area, and use your tanking gear for Arvoar. With decent tank gear he only hits you for around 150, and 230-ish if he's enraged. Keep Demoralizing Roar up on him and spam Maul + Mangle. It'll take a few minutes but you should kill him without having to heal. (I got a respawn add at around 5%, finish him and then kill the add.)\
\
Rinse and repeat for Den Mother. I also got a respawn add at around 50%, I killed it first before going back to Barash.\
\
Finished both fights with around 45% hp left. 20g + a green that vendors around 3g.",
