  ["Escaping the Tomb64"] = {
    "1088716462npcAkuno22377npcMekeda2237010750Lower City250",
    "108876004310600432007/03/31 08:04:32NepenthesDon't bother with this unless someone is farming and has cleared everything up top.  After exiting the tombs Akuna will walk in a path designed to pick up the skimishers that ride by every minute, as well as several of the regular mobs and the 2 that spawn just for the quest.\
\
Either be prepared to handle 5+ level 64 mobs at once, or skip it.",
    "1088715496021313212007/09/19 01:25:17WildhornI would STRONGLY recommand to bring a warrior/druid/paladin with you. \
\
Being able to taunt mobs off the npc is very useful because his chain lighting do tons of damage (take like 45% of mobs hp) and make him to instant get agro and I could only take agro off him with 2 frostshocks.\
\
I suggest to \"pre-pull\" the 2 guards right outside the tomb entrance to prevent the NPC to move slightly on left to attack them because he will then agro the caster on the other side of the \"wall\" which will bring 2 extra mobs.\
\
And i wish you that the 2 mounted patrolling mobs are not there when you exit the tomb, else too bad, but the NPC is dead in advance.",
    "108876790420679042007/04/16 01:12:09MimeisthaiSoloed this pretty easily as a 65, average-geared rogue.  I had a trinket (forget where it was from) which had basically the same effect as Evasion.\
\
Overall I had to use Blind once, Blade Flurry 2x, Evasion/Dodge 2x, and one \"super\" hp pot.\
\
1. Clear immediate area around questgiver.  Get quest.\
2. Two mobs will spawn at the ramp leading out of the tomb.\
3. Akuno will aggro one or two mobs at the top of the ramp.\
4. About ten or twenty steps outside the tomb, two more mobs will spawn.\
5. Akuno will run to one or two more mobs nearby--there is a very short time between these fights.\
\
Note that he -cannot- take much damage.  Be sure to keep aggro off him.  The most you should have to fight at a time is two, three if you happen to run into pats.",
    "10887197654111947602007/12/07 21:38:13siggboyThe problem is that, if you are unlucky, he will aggro the two patrolling horsemen as well as the two mobs that spawn for the escort quest.\
\
The horsemen are very fast so they practically appear out of nowhere for you, so there's no way to anticipate them and kill them in advance.  Their patrol path is short so the chances are not even small that they will get in your way just as you leave the tomb with the escort in tow.\
\
I had to attempt this three times with my well-geared BM hunter, and I even had Misdirection ready to grab aggro as fast as possible (to no avail because the NPC will lightning zap all four of the mobs that are on him and then there's hardly a way to get them off him before he dies).\
\
I succeeded when I didn't get the horse patrol, and in that case the quest was, in fact, easy.\
\
Game of luck.",
    "10887199295101992952007/12/10 19:33:20asQarneSoloed this quest quite easily with my 67 feral druid. Really straight forward; cat form for the single/dual pulls and bear for the one time he managed to pull 3-5 mobs. As Wildhorn mentioned, Akuno's Chain Lightning does [b]insane[/b] damage - 40-45% of the mobs HP and I've seen it jump twice (damaging three mobs in all). So while I was in bear form tanking, he basically killed the mobs for me. But as a reminder - just like most damage dealers, he got very little hp so make sure you always got aggro on as many mobs as possible.",
    "1088731321140313212007/02/05 15:30:31IlliminI was able to solo this as a 64 mutilate rogue - incredibly challenging. You can't let him tank one as he dies within ~15 seconds of doing so, so tank and kill both as best you're able. If you clear from him to outside and run back, you can just get him to skip the first spawn.\
\
Mobs you need to clear:\
2 - Interrogator next to him and the mob closest to the Interrogator (pull it carefully so you don't get its neighbour)\
2 - the mobs in the next (second) room (one patrolling, one next to the doorway)\
1 - the mob in the third room\
2 - outside, the mobs on either side of the entrance\
\
This is as far as I could clear and still have time to get back to him and get him to walk and not snag the newly-spawned. Then, walking with him, you fight:\
\
0-2 mobs in the first room, depending on whether you get back fast enough\
2-4 mobs in the third room, depending on whether he aggroes the ones on the sides (two spawn here)\
2-5 outside - two more spawn here and there are 3 patrollers in the area as well. How many you fight depends on their pathing.\
\
Good luck! This is extremely gratifying to solo, especially if you overcome unexpected adds.",
    "10887132649101326492007/08/05 13:52:13lovelyapeReally annoying. It was easy until he got outside. 2 casters were in range, 2 horseman patrols, and he spawns 2 adds... so that is a total of 6 and they all aggro to him first. He dies within 10 seconds and cannot be healed. So frustrating.",
  },
