    "10365160109101601092007/09/29 00:02:16GaloheartI'm a lvl 70 Protection Paladin and i had read what everyone said above and i solo'd it. Its not easy to Solo. But the jest of it is you have to survive for 2 Minutes after you start the shutdown and defend the console.\
\
If your a Clothy you may need help form a Melee DPS that can take the hits while defending as they come in waves just like everyone else said above.\
\
As a Paladin i did this on first try. I had on full tanking gear and as soon as you kill the oversear and start the shutdown. Start to tag the mobs around the console and use SoL or SoW and just play defense and move around while defending the console but same time try to pick up all the stray mobs. They come in waves just like everyone else said. You can drop a consecration once in a while. Key is just make sure the control is shutting down all the time. At the last 30 seconds the big engineer demons show up like 3 of them and the overseer does respawn and show up also (Should be 2 mins by then). Its one big mob fest. At that time i had my 2 mins already and i completed the quest. But by them i had like 20+ mobs on me all at once. I had to use LoH and pop a mana pot. In the end i died from just too many adds and out of mana. But that was a bit after the quest was completed. Its soloable but get ready for one long rolling fight. If tank use Tanking gear. It was a hell of a lot of fun.",
    "10365126744111216492007/07/25 17:10:08ilfusoconfirm this. as a protection warrior i survive for about 3 minutes tanking every mob spawned inside, but don't get credit for manaforge shutted down, i take the elite mob to 30% then i die.",
    "103657404711570972007/04/27 18:44:16h4rr0dsoloed as prot paladin, put tanking gear on and then just play for survival, mobs will agro you if you come close to them (even when they started channeling) when 1st big mob comes, target him JoL SoL and meelee him. 1st minute is easy, then you should start running around a bit. you will probably need to LoH (or other heal) at aprox 1min15sec, elite spawns around 1 min 45 sec, stun it and then just run away and agro aditional adds so they dont fix the manaforge. when you get credit, just bubble up and run away. realy easy:-)",
    "10365293087195672007/02/02 06:22:52fongPretty damn tricky, mobs spawn in waves of 3, and they have the HP of a regular mob rather than weak like other Mana Forges. At the 30 second mark a big elite comes who hits for ~800 on cloth. Its a very tricky 2 man, but possible (easier with an AoE class), or at least a challenging 3 man.",
    "103656800831570972007/04/16 08:01:17kyleminus2Also soloed as a 17/0/44 frost mage.   Just use your novas and ice blocks to stay alive and kite the mobs away from the control panel.  You can stay alive for 2 minutes if you don't get too many on you.  I ended up dying a few seconds before the quest was completed also.",
    "103654407961432582007/02/28 15:29:30QuadeHaleWith 4 people this quest went smoothly. Try and bring a rogue or a DPS warrior along, or a 4th person, to even things out. Even with four people (2 hunters, priest and shaman) we were all hurt 10-25% and manaless by the end.\
\
