    "982454871220548712007/03/21 14:27:12KathuckaJust to make this even more clear....\
\
In the middle of the town as you approach the tower, there is a short road off to the left (south).  Near the end of this side road, there are two buildings burnt down to their foundations.  One is on the right, and one is on the left.  If you look carefully, each foundation has a staircase leading down.  The stair on the right leads to the pond.  The stair on the left leads to the well.\
\
It is possible to solo this quest, but slow and painful.  The ghosts are all single pulls, with a few long patrols thrown in.   Each single pull is not too tough.  The problem is that they take a while too kill.  If you take too long, the respawns will catch up with you, and you'll be in trouble, and there's no chance of running away (unless you're a rogue, of course).  So, you have to keep killing and moving fast enough to stay ahead of the respawns.\
\
There's also no room to maneuver.  While you can solo-pull the mobs, the slightest screwup means that you'll get one or two more.\
\
There is one dangerous wraith mob that casts shadow bolts that hit for nearly 1000.  That hurts, so use silence and interruption effects on that one.\
\
Skip the mobs you don't have to kill.  Consider elixirs or other consumables to increase your DPS.  Be prepared to deal with adds.  Bring potions and bandages.  Bring good food and water so you can recover quickly after each fight.  Bandage yourself and your pets instead of healing or eating to save time and mana.\
\
Better yet, just bring a friend with you.  Two 70's would have an easy time of it, and your guild wants you to get keyed, so someone will probably be willing to help.",
