    "957517339011593072007/10/22 23:25:29ElcmarThis is incorrect.  I did JUST the quest chain up to and including \"The Path of Anguish\" on my alt, and I can't pick up this quest, nor can another level 60 I'm with.  This must be reputation based, my best guess is that you must be at least friendly in order to pick up this quest.\
\
Edit: Just to confirm, we had another level 59 who couldn't pick up the quest at Neutral, get just a hair more reputation and got to Friendly, and was able to pick this quest up.  So it is indeed unattainable without Friendly reputation, and is not part of a prior chain.",
    "957547040160470402007/03/06 10:20:06FortWatchmaster Gargolmar (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=17306)\
\
He patrols with 2 healer pals.  Wait for him to path away and make sure all groups on both sides of the hall are cleared out.   Once you are ready to take on Gargolmar, CC both healers and then simply DPS him down and finish them up.  If you cannot get both healers out of the way, then deal with one or both of them first as they will keep him healed up.\
\
Gargolmar will randomly charge group members, so this is a good fight to have everybody stand relatively close together so your tank can easily pick up aggro again after a charge.\
\
Omor the Unscarred (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=17308)\
\
Omor has three surprises.  First, he curses group members with an effect that does insane damage to other group members within 15 yards.  Decursing helps with this, but it's easiest to just spread out and ignore this curse on your ranged classes and concentrate the decursing on the meleers who have no choice but to stand next to each other.\
\
Secondly, he spawns felhunter adds who will start spell locking your casters.  Put an offtank/rogue on the job of keeping these cleared away.\
\
Lastly, he'll knock your tank up in the air and then shoot shadowbolts at whoever is next on the threat list.  Tanks should be prepared to switch to fury stance and hit intercept (Droods and pallies, I don't know if you have an equiv to this) - if you can do that fast enough you'll immediately re-engage him without hitting the ground.\
\
Handle all of the above and this fight is a pretty easy win.\
\
Vazruden \"The Rider\" (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=17537)\
Nazan \"The Dragon\" (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=17536)\
\
This can be a really rough fight.  The event is in play as soon as you touch one of the two final mobs at the base of the ramp where you see the dragon flying around in the air.\
\
Initially, it's a simple two-mob pull.  Once the second mob drops, then it's game time with Vazruden who will hop down off his mount to engage the group.  We've found it helpful to kill the first of the two mobs and then keep the second one CC'd for a bit to make sure all casters get topped off and everybody is healthy, because after this you'll not get much of a break.\
\
There's two good ways to handle Vazruden and Nazan, depending on how much DPS your group is putting out.  If you are chewing stuff up without a problem, then just DPS the crap out of Vaz and drop him as the dragon lands (the dragon will always land before he's dead, but if you're killing him fast enough it works out to drop him as your tank runs to the dragon).\
\
On the other hand, if your group is of the protection/holy/etc spec and you're better at staying alive than you are at dishing out mad DPS, then try the other approach.  Have your tank keep Vaz busy and everybody in the group that has range should be firing at the dragon in the air.  He IS vulnerable to attack while flying around and a strong ranged group can easily get him down to the 25% health range before he lands.\
\
Whichever approach you use, make sure you're dancing to stay out of the fire spits.\
\
When engaging Nazan, we've found it effective to have everybody move down to the ringed area.  Have your tank back up a bit and everybody else in the group stays in the 1/2 circle behind the dragon.  When the dragon breathes fire, the tank just runs \"inside\" him, rendering his spray effectless.  Everybody else's job is to avoid the fire spits and finish Nazan off.\
\
A fire potion is helpful to avoid some damage and make the fight easier, but if you stay on your toes and follow the above tips it's not necessary for a win.\
\
Enjoy the chest of booty and a successful quest run!",
    "9575210157111823902007/12/30 23:26:21grawssIf you die to the bosses, you avoid experience. Have someone resurrect you to loot them. You should also make sure you've explored all of both Zangarmarsh and Hellfire Peninsula before hitting 58 if you want to gear up pretty well. A smart player can avoid any experience other than quest experience via dying before getting it.",
    "95756361371272832007/04/08 03:15:00CobaalYou do not have to complete all quests at the Expidition Point, just a 4 step chain quest starting with the following:\
\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10141",
    "9575182390201823902007/11/11 12:19:19FixitThinking of having your guild run your 59 twink through these last two Hellfire quests to get your gear? Not sure if the experience points will make you level to 60? Here's what I found.\
\
The main thing is: you can avoid getting XP in the instances either by standing outside the entrance while the rest of your party does the killing, or by being inside but a long distance from them. You need to get up close for the three boss fights in Ramparts but those are the only times you need to get XP from killing anything.\
\
If you target your party's main tank and see a mob in the target-of-target, you're too close: you will get experience when that mob dies. The safe distance is about 200 yards I think. This is only tricky in Ramparts when the first long corridor bends back on itself: you have to follow them around and stay on the opposite side of the circle (except when killing Gargolmar of course). My party was progressing at a moderate speed and I never saw any respawn.\
\
I was in a party with four level 70's. Three orc trash mobs in Ramparts bumped me about 280 XP each when I got too close (that's including the unavoidable rested bonus). And a single orc in the Blood Furnace bumped me 560 XP!\
\
With those few trash mob XP kills, and including the 620 XP for discovering Hellfire Basin (outside the Blood Furnace entrance), my total XP gain was 33,746. That's 12,600 for the first quest, a total of around 6,200 for the unavoidable three boss kills in Ramparts, 12,950 for the second quest, and the rest in accidental trash mob XP. As others have mentioned, you don't have to stick around for the final boss fight in Furnace, just step to the edge of the large circular chamber.\
\
So if you're more than 18,800 XP from levelling to 60, you can do the first quest, and if you're more than 31,750 XP, you can do both. But you probably want to add a 5,000-10,000 XP safety margin to that, just in case.\
\
In two days, of course, patch 2.3 goes live and I don't know how much that will increase XP gains for level 59 characters. So in 2.3, your mileage will vary.",
