  ["Bombing Run70"] = {
    "1101070npcSky Sergeant Vanderlip23120npcSky Sergeant Vanderlip23120Ogri'la500Sha'tari Skyguard5001111021110102110231110270npcSky Sergeant Vanderlip23120npcSky Sergeant Vanderlip23120Ogri'la500Sha'tari Skyguard500111010111102211023",
    "1101089105100891052007/05/24 03:32:42WrexsoulDoable in Flight Form as well, so don't despair you druids without a wyvern/gryphon.",
    "11010129689101296892007/07/31 07:57:36sneakillerI have an epic flyer with riding crop so that probably made this easier but all i did was:\
1. Put your bombs on a hotkey/toolbar.\
2. Fly quite high and away from your target.\
3. Face your target so you're pointed in a straight line at it. \
4. Charge straight towards the target and arm your bomb.\
5. When near to the target, use the space bar to rise up a little and drop the bomb.\
6. Strafe away back to a height that is out of range of the cannons, but turn around to make sure there's nothing incoming - if there is just strafe about to avoid.\
7. Repeat 2-7. \
\
Very easy quest indeed once you've got the hang of it :)",
    "110108855490885542007/05/23 14:38:32doomscytheA tip for completing this quest easily:\
\
KEEP MOVING! Only stop when your bomb is off cooldown, and stop for as little time as possible to drop the bomb, then keep flying. I did this and the follow up with a 60% speed flying mount, and didnt get hit by the flak once.",
    "11010212184102121842008/01/03 12:06:14GypsyrunnerOne little tip.. before taking off look around for a big dragon named Rivendark. He hits for around 1.5k but when your in the air and he knocks you off your mount.. can be a bit annoying",
    "110109934321976842007/06/06 09:25:33DarmetheonThe Skyguard Outpost hub is available after you complete the Ogri'la quests.\
You then get:\
Bombing Run > Bomb Them Again!(daily repeatable)\
Wrangle Some Aether Rays! > Wrangle More Aether Rays! (daily repeatable)\
After Bombing Run and Wrangle some Aether Rays you get To Rule the Skies(Group)",
    "1101018234621885542007/11/11 10:26:29citizen320It has a casting timer, but you DO NOT have to stop. You only have to be in range throughout the casting time.\
\
I started at low altitude. Click the bomb (set to hotkey) and mouse over the ground and lower yourself until the targeting circle changes to green. As you swoop by, left click to drop a bomb. Then hit space bar to start rising up and avoid the incoming attacks.\
\
NOTE: I got hit being careless and not lifting up, but I landed on an adamantite deposit and mined it, lol.\
\
EDIT: After a little experience doing this, the tactic of flying down at your targets at a 45 degree angle seems to work much better and is safer. Watch for the roided out fel reavers they can knock you off your mount.",
    "11010131939511318252007/08/03 23:34:47skinnylydiaYou dont actually have to complete \"a fathers duty\" to get bombing run. I have it in my quest log but not completed.",
    "1101014367351885542007/08/25 03:50:47blupacheAnother thing to remember is that spacebar = fly up and x = fly down.\
\
I generally mount up out of range, get some height & then divebomb down at ~45 degrees towards an ammo pile, strafing from left to right & using spacebar occasionally. You get a good view of the shots coming at you because you'll generally be flying virtually directly into a cannon with two others further away to left & right.\
\
Sticking to using the keyboard to dodge means you can have the bomb active & just click the mouse as soon as the sight appears. Once the bomb starts to channel its throw, i'll immediately swerve & fly low directly away from the cannon using the mouse to steer and basically weaving it in an infinity symbol pattern (â) while still strafing left & right.\
\
I find I'll always score a hit with this and get shot down about 1 time in 5 runs - but only ever while I'm flying away and, because I'm flying low then, I take stuff all falling damage & end up taking ~3k damage at most. Worst case situation you'll end up in a fight with one of the patrolling demon while on lower health.\
\
The down side of this approach is that doing one at a time is slow & you need to be selective with which ammo dumps you attack. On the other hand, I've never yet had to run back to my body & foot the repair bill either, despite being on a 60% speed flight mount. And it's a lot more fun than just jumping on & off your mount at ground level.",
    "11010152131211318252007/09/12 14:34:19YeomanConfirmed, it opens up after first part of chain, named: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=11030]Our Boy Wants To Be A Skyguard Ranger[/url]",
    "11010147107201471072007/08/31 11:19:06caritasThe strafe method works quite well...my best suggestion is get naked prior to doing this just incase something goes wrong.  No durability loss ftw.",
    "11010125044101250442007/07/22 15:56:01ThrazeThis was actually pretty challenging compared to the egg bombing in Skettis.\
\
Lots of fun :]\
\
Only advice I have is to use spacebar and X a lot.",
    "11010135169211349582007/08/10 00:13:50ZarakosFound an error. To do a descending corskscrew You have to press W+A(or D)+X.",
    "11010181868101818682007/11/10 09:13:33BKRhobKeep in mind that you don't need to stop to throw the bomb, the casting doesn't interrupt if you are moving so you can throw it on the move. The cannons won't hit you (at least with an epic mount).",
    "11010103711301037112007/06/13 13:49:13PleegWatI have found the following tactic to work for me.\
\
First: make sure you have turn left/right, strafe left/right, ascend (jump) and descend hotkeyed, and can reach them all in any sensible combination with one hand. Also check if all these combinations work, there are combinations of 3 keys that do not work correctly for hardware reasons.\
\
Now:\
1) get on your mount well away from the demon camp\
2) make sure your flight is level\
3) do not use the right mouse button from this stage onward, till you're done\
4) change to a top down view (but maintain level flight)\
5) fly to the demon camp of your preference.\
6) Use your move keys to avoid the flak.\
7) Use your hotkey to select the bombs.\
8) Pick your target\
9) Dive down, keep avoiding the flak.\
10) Once in range, bombs away!\
11) Immediately move back up (keep avoiding that flak)\
12) Wait till the bombs are off cooldown\
13) Repeat till done",
    "1101012016231885542007/07/13 18:50:25SmorftyNote that the closer you get to a cannon the more irregular you'll have to move.\
If you're just flying by this place and have cannons shooting at you from a far, you can chill and just fly straight forward without any problems but if you're really close up (like when you're bombing) you'll need to move very irregular (going up and down helps aswell).",
    "11010118717301187172007/07/10 18:17:25dotnetaddictall the comments that say \"just dodge the flak\" or any variant thereof are really unhelpful. \"Flying erratically ie. not in a straight line\" doesn't help either if you're on a slow mount. The flak is somewhat random and won't always focus on the exact spot you were at 2 secs ago. I found the easiest way to do this quest is to have the bomb hotkeyed then:\
\
1. Stop in front of a stack of cannonballs unmounted\
2. Click mount then mouseover the cannonball stack \
3. As soon as you're mounted Click the bomb action then immediately dismount \
4. Ideally no flak whatsoever will be fired at you in that short time but just in case strafe away and you'll be fine.\
\
GL",
    "11010115823911098282007/07/05 05:00:30DonaldxrYes, It is very advisable to do this quest naked. There's no point in ruining your epics on this sometimes annoying quest.",
    "11010134958201349582007/08/09 13:56:07ZarakosEven without an epic mount or flight form, this is extremely easy. \
\
I found out a very effective move, that gets you up and down the air with a 90% chance of missing flak. All you do is either W+D(or A)+Spacebar. This sends you to do an ascending corkscrew. To descend just push S instead of W. Because you are constantly turning in a corkscrew, you can keep your vision still by holding down the left mouse button. \
\
Unless I wrote this wrong, this will constantly confuse flak, while at the same time, you can move up or down. To bomb the ammo though, you will have to use your own method of advancing toward it. This move is only useful when you try to avoid flak, especially in the area where flak fire is very abundant.\
\
And for druids, have no fear of being shot down and dying. If there isn't any spellcaster mobs nearby, you can simply click on flight form again when shot down and resume flying. Remember to heal yourself when fel fire takes too much of your health away.",
    "11010106216501062162007/06/17 22:07:45UrbanGypsyAs a holy priest with a non-epic flying mount I have to admit I gave up after the first two bombing runs.  Following the \"keep moving\" tactic on a slow mount involved more button mashing and twitching than was fun for me.  Went back there again tonight though, and developed a tactic that makes life MUCH easier:\
\
1. As many folk have said, make sure you put your bomb on a hotkey\
\
2. Stay on the ground at all times.  You don't have to be airborn to use the bombs; only mounted on your flying mount (or in flight form)\
\
3. And here's the bit that really made my life easier... don't mount unless you're ready to bomb. On the whole I found the mobs were fairly well spaced apart (with a bit of forward thinking in terms of which ones were wandering towards each other), so you could easily run around in between them without having to fight anything.  So long as you're not mounted, you're not being fired at.  I just ran along to the next stack of cannonballs, mounted up, set the bomb off and dismounted again.  Heal up if necessary, rinse and repeat.\
\
Hope that helps anyone else who was still having a hard time of it.",
    "110109078541904312007/05/26 05:39:19FalrinnI was able to do this quest simply by flying erratically and droping bombs whenever I got in range.  Sometimes I'd clear an entire area of cannonballs without the flak cannons halting fire once.\
\
As long as you fly at awkward angles  and keep changing direction the flak cannons can't hit you and your free to drop as many bombs as you need.",
    "110109502250950222007/05/31 22:54:52laughingdogFor those with epic mounts, the easiest method for this can be summed up with two words:  Strafing Run.\
\
Put the bomb on a hotkey.  Hover at the edge of the camp.  Set a bearing that will pass you off to the side slightly of your target using your right mouse button.  Then shift your camera angle down about 45 degrees from horizontal with the left mouse button. Once you have that set, just hold down W, press your bomb hotkey, and click as you buzz over your target.\
\
I find that it helps a little to press the space bar right after I've dropped the bomb to get some altitude.  You don't have to stay near the target to wait for the bomb to hit.  As long as your aim was good, you'll get credit, all while being nowhere near the cannon fire.  I typically get a bombing run done in less than 5 minutes with this method, and haven't been hit yet after 4 runs.",
