    "11010115659221904312007/07/04 18:55:18dlanodI'm not sure why this comment is at -1, but it's definitely the best explanation for those of us with high lag (as used to be a major problem in the north forge camp) or those who can't get the hang of flying around bombing.\
\
1. Walk/ride up to within bomb range on a non-flying mount.  You should be outside of aggro range still.\
2. Mount up on your flying mount.\
3. Toss bomb.\
4. Dismount.\
5. Move away quickly from where you were standing, because the cannons will aim their fire there.\
\
You may need to clear a few demons, but this works especially well with the Banish More Demons quest.",
    "11010162814101628142007/10/04 11:23:44CampyDo the Relic's Emanation quest first to get a speed increase, which makes this slightly easier.",
    "1101010829511932602007/06/21 01:17:18casey37I mounted up on my flyer by accident recently and the Flak Cannons will hit you on the ground now, nothing if you're on a ground mount though.",
    "11010124268201242682007/07/20 23:28:15RandomixxBoth methods are fine to use, it just depends on your playstyle I guess. For example, at first I tried the âfly out of Flak Cannon range then dive in avoiding cannon fireâ tactic and died about four times without even getting in range of the cannonballs once(Gear unequipped of course). After that I gave up and tried the ground-based approach, it made life much easier because the mobs were constantly being farmed, but it was also absurdly slow as I spent more time bandaging then bombing due to latency. So I tried the âfly erraticallyâ approach again, and decided to write up a bit of a guide to the way I did it. Simply because all of these people who just tell us to âQQ less and keep movingâ (Or any version of that) have little, if any, description in their posts as to HOW to âkeep movingâ.\
\
Step One: Go to Forge Camp of choice, pick a âsafe spotâ just outside the camp where the cannons canât get you, and hop on your flying mount (My âsafe spotâ is just outside the âenergy barrierâ of Shartuulâs Transporter for that quest). Now fly up so youâre about 10-20 metres off the ground in-game.\
\
Two: Start flying towards a Fell Cannonball Stack near the edge of the camp, it is okay to fly straight at this point, as you will not be in range yet.\
\
Three: Keep an eye on the Fell Cannons! If you see one turns towards you, it is about to fire at you: Hit one of your strafing keys and either the spacebar or X key (These are default controls BTW) at the same time. This will make you move diagonally up or down, and the Flak will explode either above or below and slightly behind you. If you do get hit though, you are nice and close to the ground, so the fall will NOT kill you (I even had a few incidents where I didnât take falling damage at all!). Also, donât be afraid to run on the ground, the closer you are to the ground, the better this strategy seems to work.\
\
Tip: Iâve noticed that the cannons tend to fire in volleys of three to four flaks, then will not fire again for at least three seconds, use this time to your advantage!\
\
Four: Once in range of the stack, click your bomb on the hotbar and quickly click the stack, then hit spacebar and strafe away from the Fel Cannon next to the target. At this point you can either go for another Cannonball Stack, or return to your âsafe spotâ (Because the cannons are behind you, you might want to turn the camera around for this) and wait out the cooldown on your bombs.\
\
I hope this helps everyone who has been having trouble with this quest, but the main problem I may have here is that it might not work with epic fliers-I did this on a normal flying mount (still 2000 gold short of the epic one -_-) - because they move faster and thus would technically have less reaction time for getting fired at.",
    "11010103075201030752007/06/12 12:20:40markabeyThe damage they do is related to your total health - fire resist or more stamina do nothing- its around 4-5% per tick",
    "1101010243491976842007/06/11 12:04:40ToggolYou have to complete the entire quest chain from the Bladespire Supplicant before this opens up. \"The Relic's Emanation\" is the end of the quest chain, not \"Ogre Heaven\".\
\
You can view the chain here: http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=11022.",
    "1101016184611904312007/10/02 13:29:30TaliaMokaniThis worked for me perfectly. As an added bonus for mages, I added two things to this when I did it:\
