    "1107112533291909442007/07/23 05:09:02RealUnimportantGamaOmega93: Please make your own speed tests before dismissing someone else's observations. Rabidfire and ZombiePope are correct and do not deserve to be rated down purely because you can't read.\
\
I cannot find the section you claim to be quoting on the official site, all of it supports what has been previously stated by the other posters here. Multiple 10% trinkets/auras/talents don't stack, that is the only restriction - spurs, carrots, and glove enchants still stack with eachother, giving an 8% total increase, but none of them will stack with either talents, auras, or 10% trinkets.\
\
The riding crop, Crusader Aura, the hunter talent to increase mounted speeds, and indeed the reward from this quest all increase your speed multiplicatively, NOT purely as a base increase. That does indeed mean that using a crop while on an epic flying mount will increase your speed by (100%+280%)/10 = 38% overall, giving you a new top speed of 418% of normal running speed. This observation is repeatably demonstrable through using one of the many player speed displays.\
\
As for \"common knowledge\" stating that taxis fly at 300%, I'd like to know which common people you hang out with. Taxis fly from between 200 and 400% faster depending on their route and direction, with the average straight/level speed being approximately 428% which, surprise surprise, is 10% slower than the 418% speed you can achieve on an epic flying mount when equipped with a riding crop! Again, this is repeatably demonstrable when using any of the player speed addons available.",
