    "110609461830946182007/05/31 09:39:25KeekuliHere's how far I've gotten in the event: \
First part as the fel guard is really easy, just fear, charge and whirlwind the trash, and hammer the shield every time the cd allows you. Once the shield is down, comes the green demon guy (no need to use crystal foci or whatever in the first part nor the green dude). Just spam the basic attack and whenever he does fel flames, fear and charge. \
\
After this it get's a little trickier though quite easy still. Use fel flames everytime you can, if the little guys start making cannon, use the leap attack and after that drain life from a mob which has a good amount left. Continue this until a big guy shows up, I just spammed him with the basic attack and once in a while do the leap/drain combo. Also use the throw axe ability all the time. Here I had to use one crystal foci thing to do the bombing attack which practically killed all the enemies(remember that you can use your other skills too when flying, drain here) \
\
After you've killed quite lot of the little guys and if I remember correctly 4-6 big guys, you face the shivan assasin. She does siphon life, and death blast or something which drains life to her, and sometimes frost nova and possibly flame buffet+fireball. Here you have to keep her stunned as much of the time possible. I was very close to die but managed to kill her too. \
\
In the next part you control (surprise surprise) the shivan assasin. This part, at least for me, felt very hectic. She has 3 \"aspects you can change every 30s. Shadow aspect has siphon life, and the same shadow attack that drains life if the mob is affected by siphon life + shadow nova. Fire aspect has flame buffet, fireball and some aoe which possibly had a debuffing effect(didn't really have time to read carefully) . And the Ice aspect has a frost nova which jumps her backwards, ice blast or something and a spell similar with ice block. Also the special attack she has(that uses 2 charged crystal focus's this time) does much damage and extra if the mob is affected by one of the debuffs she can do.\
\
You'll be fighting a beholder which killed me quite quickly. It casts a deathray attack (you get the \"Eye of shartuul is focusing or something in your chat) which I think should be avoided with ice block. I can't tell much about this fight since it was kind of  chaotic and he killed me quite quickly.\
\
I'm interested in knowing what's beyond, so please add more info as you get further",
    "11060141462201414622007/08/21 00:28:09TheololWatch out, do this quest as often as you can and don't stack up both kinds of Darkrunes, here's why:\
\
It surely doesn't work to keep a Darkrune, a Crystalforged Darkune and a Kronk's Grab Bag... If you hold all these and let the daily reset happen, you have basically just lost a shot at the Shartuul event.\
\
So, how to avoid this? Just be aware that you can't hold more than one of each of these 3 unique items, and do the Shartuul event ahead of getting full, or on the same day you got a new bag. Always remember to open the bag when you get it, if you can't, that means you need to do the event as soon as possible, because obviously it has a new Darkrune in it. You need to use your current Crystalforged Darkrune and do the event before the next reset. This will allow you to do the event as well as Crystalforge a new one afterwards, since it all took place the same day.\
\
However, if you have all of them and Gahk doesn't have the \"Yous Have Da Darkrune?\" quest, then you have let the reset go by. In this case you have already lost one darkrune whatever you do, when that happens you should just delete the bag so you can turn-in the \"Banish More Demons\" quest (usually it will be after having the quest done again and returning to the NPCs that you'll realize you already messed up by not having done it the day before). Being able to turn-in this quest is key to being able to Crystalforge a new Darkrune, so just getting rid of the bag is the single thing you need to do. You can also just delete the plain one and open the bag, same results = no bag, Darkrune, Crystalforged Darkrune. Then you can turn-in the quest and receive a new bag as normal.\
\
To be safe, always keep only one Darkrune or none, not both plain and Crystalforged because you might not have time (or remember) to do the event again before the next daily reset.\
\
The reset is at 4:00 EU, but in fact you should always do dailies preferably before 3:00 realm EU, turning in dailies after that time will make them done for the next day as well - this doesn't show right at the reset, but will happen when you log back in hours later, so you can still do them again right after the reset.\
\
Also, there will be a Raw Darkrune ( http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32642 ) item coming in a patch. This will apparently stack up to 20 and work in the same way as a normal Darkrune, 1 for each Shartuul event, therefore different than the Fragments ( http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33784 ), which will also be patched in. It's a quest item, so it's likely for it to come with a new repeatable quest, to allow you to turn it into a normal, unique Darkrune. This will allow you to Crystalforge a lot more than the 2 you currently can each day, so that in theory you can stack up the event 22 times and then do it in a single day... But mainly, it's obviously to prevent people from just losing their Darkrunes when they don't do the event along with the dailies for a couple days at a time.",
