    "1106093141300931412007/05/29 12:57:57DettonThe Crystalforged Darkrune is used to do an event at Shartuul's Transporter at the northern forge camp, Forge Camp: Wrath, on the westernmost plateau in Blade's Edge (the one with the Ogri'la camp) \
\
The quest to get a darkrune, which is then exchanged for a crystalforged darkrune, can only be gotten at Honored with Ogri'la, and it involves the quest Banish the Demons http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=11026\
\
The first time you do this quest at honored, you are guarenteed a darkrune.  The daily version of the quest does not guarentee a darkrune - at least, the bag you get as a reward says to \"cross your fingers for a darkrune.\"\
\
Using the Crystalforged Darkrune at the transporter will have you take control of the roaming demon that can't otherwise be targeted.  Your character is \"stunned\" for the duration and your view shifts to the demon's.\
\
As Jeoh says, you can used Charged Crystal Focus (charged with 10 apexis shards from a Depleted Crystal Focus) to activate an ability which will heal the demon.  \
\
Warning:  During a bit of lag, I had clicked repeatedly on the \"heal\" skill, and accidently consumed all of my charged crystal foci (five of them at the time) - There is a cooldown to the ability, but... Just be careful.\
\
The demon has five abilities:\
\
1.)  Mortal Strike.   Hits a demon for about 10,000 damage, very short cooldown.  This will one-shot any of the little demons that come after you.\
\
2.)  Whirlwind.  Hits all enemies around you for 4k-5k damage.  It is similar to Herod's whirlwind from Scarlet Monestary, or the Whirlwind Axe - you must stay in place or else you will break the channeling of the whirlwind.  This has a fairly long cooldown, so use it when you have a lot of fel hounds around you.\
\
3.)  AOE fear.  I can't remember the names precisely (as I do not have a darkrune to do the event right now) - Medium cooldown, it fears - as you'd expect - everything around you for a short time.  This can give you a needed breather and help you wait out other cooldowns.  (such as whirlwind)\
\
4.)  Destructive Charge.   Short cooldown (not as short as mortal strike) this will charge an enemy and do a MASSIVE amount of damage to everything around it, around 20,000.   It has a minimum range so it's hard to use on anything but the imps, which stand back and throw fire at you.  However, any dogs attacking you will likely follow and be caught in the explosion.\
\
Against the stronger demon, if you use the AOE fear,  you can then charge for a good amount of damage.\
\
5.)  Throw hammer.  (Forgot the exact name, again) - Will throw a hammer at the shield, which is your primary objective, doing a lot of damage to it (but it has no health bar) - it takes 4-5 hammers before something stronger then the hounds and imps come after you.\
\
6.)  Finally, there is the heal.  The wording of the ability states that it drains health from everything around you.  I could not get it to work properly though when fighting a group of the fel hounds.  This ability consumes one charged crystal focus and has a long cooldown.  Use it around your 3rd or 4th hammer to make sure you have full health for the big fight.\
\
Unfortunately, I failed BOTH my attempts for today, the day I finally reached Honored and got this quests, so what lies after this event for the reward, I do not know.\
\
If anyone would care to post a successful attempt and what you get from it, it would be useful.  Also, correcting me on the names of the demon's abilities, and exact cooldowns, would be appreciated too.  I will have to wait until tomorrow to do the event again and re-check.",
    "110609308350930832007/05/29 11:24:53JeohYou can use Charged Crystal Foci to use the special abilities of the various demons you control during this quest.",
    "110609332631931412007/05/30 00:08:57BorntorunI went beyond. Not much tho.\
With your felguard you have to defeat the demon that pops out the Transporter. How to defeat the winged demon: Fear-charge-mortal strike-whirlwind whole channelled. Repeat. Better you have between 40-50% of your felguard HP be4 facing it. Then the winged demon should be ready to be submitted.\
When it is at about 25%-20% you gain control of that winged demon and new wave of mobs appear.\
New mobs are of 3 kinds:\
- mini fel cannons (stand in place shotting at you)\
- Mechanar netherbomb throwers shaped mobs (only melee hits)\
- Mechanar minibosses shaped mobs (strongest ones, poison spray skill, not many around)\
\
It has a really unusual way of fighting, since it has these skills (can't remember names, I try to write 'em as accurate as I can):\
\
