    "105855467111387642007/03/21 06:46:55royaleI finally decided that it was not worth all the deaths caused while trying to do this as a 69 warrior.  The biggest problem was the patrol of the Infernal and 2 Tinkerers that would walk throughout the caves (there wasn't one time they aggroed me that I survived), and the frequent respawns.  Without any real healing it was pretty difficult and I would recommend other warriors to find a different quest chain.\
\
The only reward fitting our class anyways (at the end of the quest chain) is an 13 agility ring with 50 attack power and 10 hit rating (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=30973), something I could easily live without for all the trouble involved in getting it.",
    "105853359220335922007/02/10 13:04:03FlyvThis quest can be easy if you can stealth and fly. Once you have the Elemental Displacer, fly down to the southern cave entrance at 40.4, 39.5. Stealth in, to the right, and down. It's a bit tricky but you can sneak all the way down to the green summoning pool without aggroing any mobs.\
\
Go to the back of the pool, unstealth where you're out of aggro range, and use your displacer. The first time I did this it didn't quite work; it summoned an elemental but then nothing happened. So I killed the named summoner closest  to the pool, resummoned, and the elemental then killed the other summoners standing around. Then I killed the elemental and quest complete.",
    "105854456721387642007/03/01 12:29:52FrozerThere is no need to take out the group of 3 normal summoners just take out Summoner Skartax, then the Infernal Oversoul, done.",
    "105853583250358322007/02/14 10:44:27ToloranI'm not sure if it was just the day when I tried but....\
\
When I was there, the spawn rate in the cave was INSANE. I was clearing mobs pretty quickly but the respawns were right behind me. I often had to burn a bunch of cooldowns (on my mage) just to handle all the mobs that suddenly spawned right on top of me (usually when low on mana, of course).\
\
Has anyone else noticed a high spawn rate in those caves?",
    "10585194694301946942007/12/02 02:43:13ValvsCan't believe no one posted coord yet :). The summoning chamber is at around 37,38.",
