    "105853342010334202007/02/10 02:54:54smasher007When you go into second cave down to the right there should be 4 summoners and a named nonelite. This is a farm spot for mark of sargeras so first time down someone had killed just kill the summomers and the named then a spawn. Was quite confused for a bit.",
    "105853844510384452007/02/19 00:42:01tmenteleIf you go in the first cave - then fight your way to the other side of the bridge - you can go out on this ledge overlooking the summoners (on the right side) -- just use the displacer there, then you need to kill the summoned elemental.  I think you could just ranged attack the elemental and complete the quest, however I didn't think of that, so I jumped down.  (I made it alot harder than it had to be).  Could someone please confirm if that works?",
    "105858092310809232007/05/10 13:57:57antianaraIf anyone is having a hard time acquiring the elemental displacer here's a trick: kill the summoners around Skartax...then wait for the elemental to appear quickly pull the Deathforge Tinkerer's as you see them on the ramp fight them near a section were there's an ore deposit against the corner wall that way if a summoner spawns again you won't agro them. Of course avoid the bombs on the ground...I got the displacer that way and completed the quest after using the displacer and killing the last summoned elemental.",
    "105852907990290792007/02/01 18:11:08elonexNext is - Bring Down the Warbringer!\
\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10603",
    "10585131812101318122007/08/03 16:44:24jolthammerThe Ledge Trick works great.  As a Paly .. i used the displacer at the ledge.  This killed everyone except the main bad guy, 69 non elite.  The I bubbled and jumped down, and easily killed him and hearthed out.",
    "105852511570251152007/01/26 13:52:22bobbyjrAs you go down the ramp towards the caves, take the first one to your right.  Kill mobs in here until you get the displacer, then go outside and head to the next cave.  Kill the summoners in there and follow the rest of the quest",
    "105854787520478752007/03/07 19:05:51recrudescei can agree about the respawn rate.  i'd kill one guardian, then move onto another and by the time i'd downed the second, the first one had appeared again !\
\
rest of it was pretty easy, did the whole quest and only died once.",
    "10585154578101545782007/09/18 08:23:49bas3this is how I got the displacer\
\
since you are going to need the backpack anyway (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10583), just rush to place where the backpack is, die there and ressurect in the corner. Kill the mob guarding his corpse (use a healing pot if needed) and after he is dead drink/eat to regain health and mana. Now kill the two guards at the exit. Now you can safely pull two fast running tinkers. When you got the displacer the easiest way to get out is use your hearthstone (if it's on cooldown you can just die and spirit rez). After that, getting to the ledge is much easier. Wait just outside the first entrance till the fire elemental patrol passed, then go in and kill mobs till you reached the end of the bridge; there jump down.",
    "105855356851387642007/03/19 06:07:31MalygosMudYou don't even need to take Skartax out.\
\
On your way in, jump off the path as soon as you see green water. You can walk between some stone blocks and end up behind the ritual circle. You don't need to fight any of the summoners. Just summon the elemental, he kills the summoners instantly, you solo one level 69 mob (5 seconds) and you're done.",
    "105853876440387642007/02/19 15:32:58aimoneAll of the information posted so far is true but just to clear up one thing about the respawn rate...\
\
When you get to the bottom of the summoning chamber, there are 3 normal summoners with relatively low health which are easy to dispatch, then there is the named Summoner Skartax who will continually summon the Infernal Souls which walk up out of the green water, around the corner and are joined by two of the Deathforge Tinkerer's (they spawn just as the infernal spawns.) The group of three will start patrolling around. The spawn rate for this seems to be around 3-5 minutes, I had the same problem on my mage where I would rest after killing the initial guards/patrol, then this mob of 3 would keep reappearing after dispatching them and I had finished resting.\
\
I suggest killing the patrol as quickly as possible (don't rest even if you have to) and moving down and standing behind the summoners in the chamber (there is a small amount of space there.) After that take down the rest of them. Once you kill Summoner Skartax the Infernal Oversoul will spawn which you need to kill to complete the quest, it was no issue as a frost mage.\
\
As for the disrupting from the ledge trick I'm not sure, I think clearing down to the bottom is the best solution. The summoners seemed to be on a ~5 minute cooldown too, so it would make a good farming spot seeming as they are relatively weak.",
    "105857689910768992007/05/03 02:14:43AzelonGo across the brigde, and turn right just before the doorway.. Theres a ledge, and you can stand on the legde and use the rod. The non-elite will kill all the summoners, and you just kill him. He's easy as a lvl 69 warrior. Before i did this, i made Wildhammer Stronghold my home, and i just HS'ed out of there. Else the fight out of there is INSANE. Good luck",
  },
