    "1076458393120583932007/03/28 01:39:50leftquarkIf you stand around 59, 41 in Hellfire Penninsula, there is a Fel Reaver that pats by. If you are patient and wait for him, you can pull the fell reaver to the right into a pack of elite mobs. They'll kill it for ya. If you're alliance, they're Thrallmar guards, so you will most likely die. If you can have a friend do the pull and you stay alive, that's fine. Or you can have an SS or whatever so you can complete the quest after the guards kill the fel reaver.",
    "10764188928201889282007/11/21 14:31:46JaqlConfirmed, still works as of yesterday.  As an alliance hunter this was very easy to do.  Instead of waiting on the east side of the group of elites and running the Fel Reaver into them yourself you can go stand next to the Thrallmar wall on the west side of the elites and use your pet instead.  Once you're standing near the wall use Eyes of the Beast and run your pet out past the elites to where the Fel Reaver paths by.  As it comes close, aggro it and run your pet into the group of elites.  Once your pet gets to them they will AE it and with the Fel Reaver already chasing it will get AE'd as well.  The pet will die pretty quickly and the entire pack will start heading for you but you can just FD and then watch the show.",
    "10764194861301948612007/12/02 11:58:51beanj007Kiting him to Thrallmar still works wonderfully after patch 2.3 on December 7th, 2007.",
    "10764179098201790982007/11/04 14:57:31SklaninhaosConfirmed, still works as of today.  As a Prot. Warrior, just pulled and ran just outside of the range of the mobs.  Fel Reaver used his Thunder Clap and aggroed the orcs.  Big and stupid.  Used my Shield Wall to lower damage and took off to lose aggro.  Aggro stayed on Fel Reaver.  Waited for the death of Fel Reaver and went to fetch my key.  Every time I got close to Fel Reaver I was stunned by picking up aggro, but I did manage to make the key.  As it was said before, the big deal was to get some of the elites to aggro onto Fel Reaver or they both reset.\
\
Good luck and happy hunting! :)",
    "1076420619711982322007/12/23 20:16:32bob1052or if your class has any means of surviving having multiple 66 elites and a 70elite beat on you (most likely pally bubble or mage ice block), you can wait and hope the fel reaver uses his earthquake attack",
    "1076417340211583932007/10/23 00:11:26gorka34Did this on 10/20.  I died, rezzed and made it back in time to watch the orcs kill the Fel Reaver.  I walked up and made my key.  Thanks for the tip.",
    "10764205646102056462007/12/22 15:25:31geordiesiI am contributing to this thread not to say 'Hey I done it' but to add a couple of points as at first I thought this was no longer possible, I tried several times to get the FR and the Elites to agro each other and failed, it was only because there was a post after the last patch (2.3) saying it was still possible, that I endured. It would appear that  you need to run right into the Elites, not just by them enough for their health bar to show. Also note that when you walk into the corpse of the FR to fire the key mold you do enter combat for a short time. This is not the Elites aggroing you(hopefully) but the intense heat of the FR's fel fire core.  Ouch!!\
\
And yeah of course this is soloing a Fel Reaver.......",
    "107645029080502902007/03/12 21:26:53AgraviceDeathforge Automatons will also work to fire your key mold. Tried this just now in my guilds raid group and it worked just fine.\
