\
So there you have it. You don't need to actually kill the Fel Reaver, if you see his body just stand on it and use the item.",
    "10764123188211163042007/07/19 06:41:59gwdragonI agree.  As a Pally my 20 Yard instant didn't give me enough time to get back to the group and survive.  Since the Fel Reaver disapeared very quickly, I had to do it a second time and this time used my Boomerang (there is a use for it!) and walked through the group then shook them off as the fel reaver went to town on them.  The best path is once you run into the group head for the road and on the other side.  It is usually void of mobs and allows you some running space down the road to loose aggro of the mobs you picked up.  After that, a quick few heals and I was able to walk right behind the Fel Reaver and wait for him to fall.  Gotta get the key made quick otherwise his body does disappear quickly.",
    "10764116304201163042007/07/06 03:37:40seliceTo aggro the mobs its not enough to pull the fel reaver close to them. You have to wait for them to do the Blizzard OR wait for the Fel Reaver to use Thunder Clap so he aggros the mobs around. The Fel Reaver's remains vanish pretty quickly so I suggest you do it right after the FR is killed.",
