    "1107289411671892142007/05/24 10:13:05WrexsoulYes you do. Which means that this quest is nearly as frustrating as they come. You first have to grind 6 dusts off of the (currently horribly overfarmed) living Arakkoa with their 25%ish droprate. Then you've to gobble the potion down, grind scrolls (~75% droprate) from the ghosts (that commonly zerg in groups of 3, heal eachother with unlimited mana, etc), until you a) get ganked and lose your potion, b) get zerged and lose your potion, c) get respawns while fighting and lose your potion. Then you have to grind 6 more dusts, and repeat the steps above. All in all, if your server is ganky, innumerable hours of \"exciting new solo content fun\". Oh, yeah, and that's provided you don't get ganked at the actual summoning, in which case you lose the 10 scrolls and have to go grind more. \
\
(Do I sound bitter? Gee, I think I do :p)",
    "1107211444731880712007/07/02 13:16:19modsquadThe best way to farm the scrolls is in a group of 2 or more people. If you can get a healer or a class that can heal (feral druid) grinding out the scrolls gets MUCH easier. Just have one person that can DPS drink the potion while the other just heals & keeps the regular non-spirit mobs off the DPS. You will kill them faster, and only use up 1 pot per farm & be a lot less likely to get killed & waste a pot. I put on some druid healing gear I have stashed & healed for a rogue as a feral spec'd druid & it went great. The scrolls are lootable by people that DO NOT drink the pot that are also in the team so you can either just let the loot swap normally or put it on free for all & just take turns looting scrolls....or just have a designated scroll collector that will do all the summoning.",
