    "110721176142701176142007/07/08 19:05:28KalakaEntire quest 2manned by a dark pact/ruin warlock and holy paladin. Imp was used, warlock did the tanking. You require 10 scrolls per boss per person (the two of us required a total of 80 time lost scrolls). We got 10 scrolls per 15 minutes, so 8 elixirs were needed (48 shadow dust). Only warlock used shadow elixirs (healers donât need to see undead to loot them). Took about half an hour for the shadow dust, and another 2 and a half hours of farming scrolls/killing bosses. When farming scrolls, itâs best to do a boss in between each elixir to allow for respawns.\
\
All bosses are immune to fear/stun/etc. After summoned, you have about 5 seconds before they aggro. They each have special abilities.\
\
Karrog â Approx. 73,000 hp. Hits for about 1900-2500 on cloth. âFixatesâ on a target, drastically reducing his move speed and increasing his damage to about 5500 on cloth. When he fixates, just kite and damage him, no healing should be needed if you just run (he walks REALLY slow).\
\
Gezzarak the Huntress â Approx. 59,000 hp. Hits for about 1500 on cloth. Casts âwarped armorâ debuff, reduces armor to 0. Will âfocusâ on a target, then warp to them, dropping aggro.\
\
Darkscreecher Akkarai â Approx 47,000 hp. Does a frostbolt attack, 2.5 second cast, for around 1000 frost damage. Every few frostbolts, he will do a fire blast for around 1600 fire damage. Will also summon adds around every 20 seconds. They come 3 at a time, they are birds that donât hit for much, have about 5000 hp. The pally gathered them up while the warlock burned Akkarai down, then after he died the birds were killed with seed of corruption (only needed 4).\
\
Vakkiz the Windrager â Approx. 59,000 hp. Hits for about 1500 on cloth. Does a chain lightning with around 2000 initial damage for the first 50%. At 50% hp he switches to a bone form, and begins to cast âBone Sprayâ. Initially hits cloth for around 500. Each time he attacks, it adds a stack to a debuff he puts on you which increases damage taken by 5% per stack. He casts this around every 2 seconds. Save all your cooldowns for 50%.\
\
Each boss will drop 1 of their quest item that gets rolled on. They also each drop 1 BoP blue item with a random enchant on it. Despite WoWheadâs info, their quest item is a 100% drop (people who donât need the quest that kill the bosses get no drop, which alters WoWheadâs information).",
    "1107210111011994772007/06/09 03:15:23FuzzyThe main reason I see to do this line, beyond a possible time killer, is for the Skyguard reputation involved in the line. 350 from this quest, and apparently 1000 from killing Terokk. It's the only reason I'm going to put the time and effort into this, though this is also due in part to the fact that I only get the dusts from mobs I kill everyday escorting the Skyguard Prisoner. :P Every time I get enough for a potion, I pop it and get as many scrolls as I can, then repeat when I get enough dusts for another potion.\
