    "10290168537701685372007/10/14 17:28:25BattleguardSoloed with a level 70 Protection specced Paladin with average gear. This is how:\
[ul]\
[li]Used [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=20470]Improved Righteous Fury,[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=27179]Holy Shield[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=27168]Blessing of Sanctuary[/url].[/li]\
[li]Opened with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=31884]Avenging Wrath[/url] so that [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=25771]Forbearance[/url] would have faded in case I needed to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=1020]bubble[/url]. If you're with the Alliance, proccing the DoT from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=31801]Seal of Vengenace[/url] while [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=31884]AW[/url] is active will cause it to keep the 30% bonus damage even after it expires.[/li]\
[li][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=20271]Judged[/url] a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=27166]Seal of Wisdom[/url] to regen mana, then used [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=31801]Seal of Vengenace[/url] for the rest of the fight.[/li]\
[/ul]\
When [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=18885]the big one[/url] died, I usually had 30-50% Health and ~10% mana left. The small ones were relatively easy to kill with a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=20271]judged[/url] and an active [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=27166]Seal of Wisdom[/url] (they do around 100 damage to someone with 10k armor, which was fully blocked each time). Of course, it's not necessary to kill them, since they don't drop anything, and despawn shortly after leaving combat.\
\
I've seen Hunters solo this as well, by just nuking them, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=27046]spam healing[/url] their pets, then running out of range to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=5384]Feign Death[/url].\
\
Hope it helped :)",
