    "1099270npcArthorn's Sparrowhawk23338npcArthorn Windsong22924Cenarion Expedition150110990210991310992410993510994611001",
    "10992143996201439962007/08/25 18:40:16GrunthorusI just solo'd this in my resto gear as a Feral, 0/47/14. Died once, Very challenging. Kept root up at all times, abolish poison when it's down, decurse when you get cursed and starfire spam. Low to mid 3k range with no crits, and thorns did about 130ish damage when he got to close. Lots of fun.",
    "109929945420994542007/06/06 12:30:22EnanoI know when I did it a few weeks ago instead of my Starfires hiting for around 1.9k they were hiting for about 9k. I did trinket and get a 20k Starfire crit, really makes you happy. But the general strategy is to always keep him rooted no matter what, and just hammer him with a Starfire, less spells cast, less amount of times you will have to reapply roots.",
    "109928900930890092007/05/24 01:06:20SundancerPutted all my healing gear on (since I got no balance gear) and that gave me a lot more mana so I could cast longer and nuke him quite easily =) Remember to Abolish Poison/ Remove Curse. Did this easy by casting wrath and kept him rooted as a feral specced Druid.",
    "10992189706101897062007/11/23 00:06:53FaignTake a hunter, druid, or shaman with you. The mob is Nature and Arcane weak, Serpent Sting ticks for 1k, Arcane shots hit for 3k+ and my combat log doesn't say what the damage from my Snake Trap was, but I can guess it was decent. Also he can't be silenced.",
    "10992114094201140942007/07/01 22:02:11Woozardid it as feral with the help of an ele-shaman. he did more than 6k dps. the fight didn't even last 10 seconds.",
    "10992116421201164212007/07/06 09:30:19RennoThe rank 1 root works just as well as the rank 7. Also your innervate gets reset if you die and if you die your automatically ported alive at the graveyard.  As a feral druid only no skills in balance I was able to do this with a 7500 mana pool. Also dont wait to cast your abolish poison just cast it when it wears off. Also be sure to just kill the adds all around the alter before you try this. You will need all the room to run around.",
    "109928874250887422007/05/23 18:16:47jef3189Strategy:\
\
This is the third of three mini boss fights in this quest, each involving a different aspect of your druid abilities. (This particular fight involves your ability to root and cast spells)\
\
Click the statue and the NPC will spawn directly in front, like with the other you will have a few seconds to back up and prepare your roots and initial abolish poison. Remember that your abolish poison ticks and dispells future poisons, so keep that in mind you can completely avoid  the viper sting he throws at you. He occasionally curses you so be aware of that too.\
\
DO NOT attempt to use melee combat, and take advantage of barksin. Preempt your roots to make sure that he doesnt come within melee range, and use your wrath/moonfire to burn him down as quickly as possible. They do almost 400% damage (all your druid spells).",
    "10992200960102009602007/12/14 02:06:14vanadium322I got to this quest as an alt, newly to level 70, feral spec with -0- spell damage gear.  It was HARD.  Starfires hit for under 4k, he resists roots far too often, and my mana pool was under 6k.  After about 10 attempts, I managed to get him down, but it was as much luck as anything else.  People in my situation should either bring a friend, gear up a little first, or be prepared to lose to the random number generator a lot (i.e. 2 root resists in a row).",
    "10992119440201194402007/07/12 08:09:02contentiousDid this with help from an arcane mage. Small problem; if you take this route, keep in mind that mage arcane spells cast very fast and damage breaks the roots. I basically wound up spamming roots and still had to throw a brez to the mage. \
\
Went down REAL quick tho",
    "10992117613201176132007/07/08 19:03:45TiforixHe does seem to take about 5x damage from Arcane spells. I was getting Starfire hits in the 8-9000 range, and one crit for 18,011.\
\
If you are Balance spec, don't use Moonkin form though. You'll need to decurse and de-poison yourself a few times.\
\
And don't use Wrath. Starfire and Moonfire are the way to go.",
    "109929024840902482007/05/25 12:27:48parprapaAt 15-10%, he hits you with \"Death's Hammer,\" a short stun.  He then goes into a berserk mode and starts doing much more damage in melee range.  Make sure to catch him in roots before this happens.\
\
I recommend using Starfire over Wrath for this encounter since the less-frequent hits give you a lesser chance to break your roots.  Nature's Grasp also comes in handy.",
    "10992104932201049322007/06/15 14:04:58TaurentWow! This guy is tricky. It's true you need to keep him rooted and just pelt him with balance spells as they do way more damage than normal. I had a hard time my first attempt - he drained all my mana and my roots were not sticky long enough. His melee hits are exceptionally heavy.\
\
I ended up getting a resto druid pal (who is nearing his 5k gold) to help just in case I needed a mid-cast roots or an abolish poison. Went down quickly!",
    "10992179788201797882007/11/05 20:54:16BeastyA tip for those low on spell damage but good for anyone as its a huge dps increase (i only had a quag's eye and my end of dreams from back at 60 along 2 pieces of high warlord gear)\
\
Is to use the netherwing ally trinket and summon him while fighting, it does very respectable damage and can take some hits while you nuke if  you want it to.\
\
http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32864\
\
Really helped.",
    "10992182923101829232007/11/12 13:31:40ManxomeSince I'm feral, I did it in bear form, with the help of a healadin. At first I tried the root and nuke method. Even with some healing gear giving 7500 mana, and with heals from the healadin, it didn't take long to get killed. My roots would only hold for a couple of seconds. No question I was rusty casting spells, and I didn't get far enough away from the mob so I could cast roots while it ran to me. \
\
But I simply lacked the patience to get the technique down, so I switched to tanking gear (14K HP, 24K armor) and slowly, ever so slowly, beat the mob down. It wasn't a strain so much as it took time; each mangle would only reduce the mob's health by 1%. The healadin had to pot a couple of times, but my health never even went down to 50%. Just clear the area of mobs and fight the npc right at the statue.",
    "109929075220907522007/05/26 04:20:06magilyncNo balance comments yet? :D This was my favorite essence to do as a moonkin. 14k starfires = owned. :)",
    "10992134955201349552007/08/09 13:51:52LarasThis is the fight where moonkin shine. Root the guy, drop your treants, pop a trinket, and watch the 10k normal starfires fly. His curse makes you take DOUBLE melee damage so keep him rooted at all costs.",
    "10992144383201443832007/08/26 14:52:11Luciferhawkeas a feral i had a hard time with this one. Took me 4 tries.  Luckily you dont have to spirit rez when you die so it doesnt matter.  First time i simply didnt know what i was doing and i died pretty fast.  2nd time he kept resisting my roots.  Resisted about 4-5 times.  Not good. 3rd try i was about to beat him and one of those dang birds respawned on my and finished me off.  4th time i used wrath instead of starfire..WAY easier.",
    "109929234320923432007/05/28 09:20:54wowheadshicI'll add balance druid comments, did 2 starfires crit with 15k  dmg each then more crit with moon fire, I'd say just stick with moonfire and starfires, mob seems to have negative resistance to those, lol. Easy fight. I teamed up with a feral druid for all 3 parts, she just demo tank and maim first and second with me blasting from far, then this fight was my turn to shine. :D If don't have balance druid friends, bring a pocket mage.",
    "109928787730878772007/05/23 00:59:41thrillhaus45, 93 is where this guy is at. Uses a viper sting (2 manned it with 2 druids, since we're both doing the quest line ;) )",
    "10992189829101898292007/11/23 06:47:00HellsyKilled him solo in tanking gear. Just keep in mind, that u need to decurse asap, and try to do it between attacks.",
    "10992194111101941112007/11/30 18:36:18StewwieSimple fight as a Moonkin.\
