    "1068028565600285652007/01/31 20:31:111dsk1The Eye (25-man raid)\
\
- The Hand of Gul'dan\
Speak with Earthmender Torlok at the Altar of Damnation in Shadowmoon Valley.\
=> The Earthmender, who starts the chain, can be found in Shadowmoon Village.\
=> Earthmender Torlok can be found at (45,46)\
\
- Enraged Spirits of Fire and Earth\
Earthmender Torlok at the Altar of Damnation in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to use the Totem of Spirits to capture 8 Earthen Souls and 8 Fiery Souls.\
=> They can be found in the surrounding area.\
\
- Enraged Spirits of Water\
Earthmender Torlok at the Altar of Damnation in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to use the Totem of Spirits to capture 5 Watery Souls\
=> The Water Elementals can be found around (47,22)\
\
- Enraged Spirits of Air\
Earthmender Torlok at the Altar of Damnation in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to use the Totem of Spirits to capture 10 Airy Souls.\
=> The Air Elementals can be found around (62,57) all around the netherwing fields.\
\
- Oronok Torn-heart\
Seek out Oronok Torn-heart on the Shattered Shelf - north of Coilskar Cistern.\
=> He can be found at his farm at (53,23)\
\
- I Was A Lot Of Things...\
Oronok Torn-heart at Oronok's Farm in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to recover 10 Shadowmoon Tubers from the Shattered Plains.\
He also wants Oronok's Boar Whistle back when you're done.\
=> Use the whistle near a tuber in the field north of the farm,\
Note: A boar must be alive and near for it to work & If you got multiple boars nearby when you use the whistle you'll get multiple questitems from one tuber.\
\
- A Lesson Learned\
Oronok Torn-heart at Oronok's Farm in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to destroy 10 Ravenous Flayer Eggs on the Shattered Plains.\
=> You can find them in the eastern part of the field where you found the tubers.\
Note: Watch out for the elite roaming around there.\
\
- The Cipher of Damnation - Truth and History\
Oronok Torn-heart at Oronok's Farm in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to listen to his story. Speak to Oronok to begin hearing his story.\
=> Listen to his story to recieve the next 3 quests in the questchain.\
\
* The First Son:\
- Grom'tor, Son of Oronok\
Find Grom'tor, Son of Oronok at Coilskar Point in Shadowmoon Valley.\
=> He can be found at (44,23)\
\
- The Cipher of Damnation - Grom'tor's Charge\
Grom'tor, Son of Oronok at Coilskar Point in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to recover the First Fragment of the Cipher of Damnation.\
=> Kill Naga to get keys to open the lockboxes in the Naga stronghold just south from Grom'tor untill you get the Cipher.\
\
- The Cipher of Damnation - The First Fragment Recovered\
Take Grom'tor's Lockbox to Oronok Torn-heart at Oronok's Farm in Shadowmoon Valley.\
=> Go back to Oronok at (53,23)\
\
* The Second Son\
- Ar'tor, Son of Oronok\
Find Ar'tor, Son of Oronok at Illidari Point in Shadowmoon Valley.\
=> His spirit can be found at (29,50)\
\
- Demonic Crystal Prisons\
Seek out and slay Painmistress Gabrissa at Illidari Point and return to the corpse of Ar'tor, Son of Oronok with the Crystalline Key.\
=> Can be found up the stairs to the right.\
\
- Lohn'goron, Bow of the Torn-heart\
The Spirit of Ar'tor at Illidari Point in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to recover Lohn'goron, Bow of the Torn-heart from the demons of the area.\
=> Kill the demons nearby to retrieve Ar'tor his bow.\
\
- The Cipher of Damnation - Ar'tor's Charge\
The Spirit of Ar'tor at Illidari Point in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to recover the Second Fragment of the Cipher of Damnation from Veneratus the Many.\
Creatures attacked or damaged by the Spirit Hunter will not yield loot or experience.\
=> Escort the NPC up the hill to the west & help him slay the summoned bossmob.\
\
- The Cipher of Damnation - The Second Fragment Recovered\
Take Ar'tor's Lockbox to Oronok Torn-heart at Oronok's Farm in Shadowmoon Valley.\
=> Go back to Oronok at (53,23)\
\
* The Third Son:\
- Borak, Son of Oronok\
Find Borak, Son of Oronok near Eclipse Point in Shadowmoon Valley.\
=> He can be found at (47,57)",
    "1068028566450285662007/01/31 20:31:531dsk1- Of Thistleheads and Eggs...\
Borak, Son of Oronok at the bridge north of Eclipse Point wants you to find a Rotten Arakkoa Egg and deliver it to Tobias the Filth Gorger in Shattrath City, located in northwest Terokkar Forest.\
=> Search the Arrakoa village just north from the NPC for eggs, keep looting them untill you got a Rotten Egg. Bring it to Shattrath to Tobias at\
(64,69)\
\
- The Bundle of Bloodthistle\
Take the Bundle of Bloodthistle back to Borak, Son of Oronok at the bridge near Eclipse Point in Shadowmoon Valley.\
=> He can be found at (47,57)\
\
- To Catch A Thistlehead\
Borak, Son of Oronok at the bridge near Eclipse Point in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to recover the Stormrage Missive.\
=> Place the Thistlehead at the beginning of the bridge & hide untill Borak tells you to go kill the carrier of the Stormrage Missive.\
\
- The Shadowmoon Shuffle\
Borak, Son of Oronok at the bridge near Eclipse Point in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to recover 6 pieces of Eclipsion Armor.\
=> Kill the Blood Elves around Eclipse Point (44, 65). Drop rate is ~20%\
\
- What Illidan Wants, Illidan Gets...\
Borak, Son of Oronok at the bridge near Eclipse Point in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to Deliver Illidan's Message to Grand Commander Ruusk at Eclipse Point.\
=> Use the disguise to talk with the commander at the highest point of the encampment in Eclipse Point just north from the questgiver.\
\
- The Cipher of Damnation - Borak's Charge ( 3 man )\
Borak, Son of Oronok at the bridge near Eclipse Point in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to recover the Third Part of the Cipher of Damnation from Ruul the Darkener.\
=> He walks from the Sanctum of the Stars to Dragonmaw Fortress, although you don't see him on the first sweep through the area, so its possible he doesn't spawn untill after you've gone past.\
\
- The Cipher of Damnation - The Third Fragment Recovered\
Take Borak's Lockbox to Oronok Torn-heart at Oronok's Farm in Shadowmoon Valley.\
=> Go back to Oronok at (53,23)",
    "10680170232211165312007/10/17 05:50:59WhisperbladeWhile the attunement is no longer required, in 2.3 anyone finishing the old attunement quests (heroic mode dificulty dungeons) will get the option of having \"(Character name), Champion of the Naaru\" as a title instead of your old PvP rank.  Not much of a reward but kind of cool.",
    "1068030562600305622007/02/04 12:00:48marskid2The Cipher of Damnation is an extremely long quest line in Shadowmoon Valley.  It is a prerequisite for attunement to The Eye in Tempest Keep and Mount Hyjal in Caverns of time.  \
