    "107813299530329952007/02/09 05:53:22EledvenDone yesterday, and can say no need of 2 tanks at all but at third wave there is realy need of additional healing for tank. \
About recomended 4 players for this quest can say only this is mistake. No matter what gear they wear in 4 players this is simply undoable. \
Warlock in group is great advantage because he can not only enslave one of demons but can banish another, thus made 1 st wave way easier. Just have to release demon not to summon his own after all first wave is cleared for quest fails, because enslaved demon disappears in summoning proces.",
    "1078170281170702812007/04/20 23:04:44benjiFMManaged to 3-man the quest after 2 tries.\
Setup was Prot Warrior, Holy Priest and Rogue. Remember to Shadow Resist Buff.\
\
First Wave\
Mixed spawn of melee mobs that comes in 2 forms, Humans and Demon forms. Basically tank ran in and grab aggro while healer waits till tank has a sunder on each mob. They don't hit too hard. Meanwhile the rogue would start peeling off the Demonkins first as we noticed they have about 2k less HP then the humanoid version and they're pretty big so we wanted to get better vision as well. Once ya down to the last mob, let healer regen back mana before killing it to trigger the second wave.\
\
Second Wave\
This is the wave that gave us the most problems. Spawns 2 x Demons that does a mean mind flay and fears. Key to this fight is to interupt as many mind flays as possible, they can be stunned so thats a huge plus. Rogue would Kick / Kidney Shot / gorge, while warrior Concussion Blows / shield bash. Also to note, as we were 3 manning it, the warrior tanked them similiarly to Onyxia style, getting berzerker rage up as often as possible to avoid fear. If warrior is feared, priest would get all the aggro, just keep healing as the fears don't last too long. Concentrate DPS and take one down asap, then move on to the other. Don't use them to regen mana, as a badly time fear could be a wipe. Quickly move on to the third wave.\
\
Third Wave\
4 x humanoid caster style that has quite a good amount of HP and casts FlameStrike for about 2k damage. For this, we got priest to stand in middle while the warrior would tank 3 of them on one side of the priest while the rogue tanked the 4th one on the other side of the priest. Basically we wanted all of us to spread out to avoid FS. Simple fight, rogue quickly kill his while warrior tanks the 3, when you guys see the casting animation, simply just move away from where u're standing as that would be the FS location. Key to this is to not let priest aggro and move out of FS range when ya see the casting animation. Once rogue is done with his, just join the warrior and finish up the remainder.\
\
Last Boss\
Cake.. Has a spell reflect that looks like a counterspell animation, and cast a 1k++ shadow damage knockback. Tank him in the middle, when he casts knockback, we just run out of range.. quite alot of HP, classic tank and spank..\
\
Notes\
Basically as long as priest does not get aggro and warrior is comfortable with multi tanking, 3 manning is very possible. Priest used alot of binding heals for the fight and had pretty decend mana per second to last the waves. Ideally for all the waves except the second one, possible to tank the last mob while healer gets back mana.",
