    "1078127197540271972007/01/29 14:13:20SledeauThis is easy as long as you have the right group make up, everyone's on the ball, know what to do, and have at least five rather than four. I did this with a feral druid tank, arms warrior tank, tree druid, enhancement shaman healer, and a warlock. I really reccomend having at least two tanks and two healers for this. It might be doable with one healer if everyone plays smart. The warlock was also nice for the first wave because he could enslave one of the demons.\
\
The first wave is pretty simple. A bunch of demons and blood elves spawn and you basically take them down. As far as I know they are not CC'able, with exception to enslave.\
\
The second wave is two eyes which do a mean mind flay. Interrupt them when they do that as soon as possible to help save the healer's mana.\
\
The third wave has four fire lords which are blood elf npc's who have a ton of hp and cast flamestrike. This is the fight you have to be on the ball on. It is preferable to have each tank on two of the npc's. Whenever one of the npc's start to cast flame strike, the tank on them and any melee DPS on them need to MOVE. This is pretty universal for any flamestriking mob, but since flamestrike is a ground target spell, its possible to dodge it if you get out of its area of effect (the center of its target when it starts casting, the area of the effect will not follow the person if they move after the cast begins) before it finishes casting. If everyone can dodge the flame strikes, this wave is fairly easy.\
\
The last wave, the final boss is a simple straight up fight. He will occasionally do an ae damage/knockback, this is another one that can be dodged by moving away when he does it. The casting animation looks like he's casting a shadow spell, so its fairly easy to spot. If you managed to do the third wave though, this one should be no problem, even if you eat the ae's from the boss.\
\
Enjoy your blue ring reward and flashy new tabard.",
    "107814087940408792007/02/23 02:14:24ezekialOn a side note. After the first wave if you have a warlock in your group they can enslave one of the demons. The next wave wont come until the demon is dead, so you have some time to rez/drink/bandage if you keep the target enslaved. When your all ready, just let it go.",
