    "10781112270101122702007/06/28 09:28:17KeilunNearly 2 manned this quest. Feral Druid, Holy Priest. A Holy Pally jumped in on the 2nd wave and helped with some heals. After that though, it went smoothly.\
\
Wave 1\
\
Any decently geared tank won't take much damage and can tank all of them. While there was a lot of them they were hitting for about 50dmg on the druid. Hit me (the priest) for about 200dmg. It probably actually worked out better that it was just the druid DPSing as a tank to make it easier to hold everything. It's a given that a tank that can multitank well is pretty essential.\
\
Wave 2\
\
This is the toughest part. Being unable to mitigate the wide range of magic damage that these two Eyes put out makes it a healing intensive part of the fight. I went through a mana pot, my shadowfiend, trinkets and inner focus. On our successful attempt, we brought them down to 10% before I was out of mana. The innervate would have come but I died.\
\
Holy pally came in at that point and picked up the heals which gave the druid enough time to battle rez me.\
\
Wave 3\
\
Simple fight. Tank needs to watch out for the flame strikes, especially with that curse debuff that adds 50% fire damage. Can be deadly if more than one flamestrike is being cast and lands. Healing wise, this wasn't very intensive either except for the odd flamestrike that landed. I managed to rebuff myself and regen from 0 mana to full during this wave.\
\
Boss\
\
Straight forward tank and spank as previously mentioned. Has a good chunk of HP, and hits a bit harder. Some horde swung by waiting for their turn to do this (didn't gank us thankfully!) and helped add some DPS.\
\
