  ["The Second and Third Fragments70"] = {
    "983217068npcKhadgar18166npcKhadgar1816615800The Violet Eye35019824198252982639829498315983269836798378983899840109843119844129860",
    "983236689140366892007/02/15 23:47:08zenmastervex70 Rogue, just solo'ed the third fragment. Here's how...\
\
In the room with the sentinal, there are also two larvae-work things. They're non-elite and can be killed quite easily. You can pull them from the corner without aggroing the sentinal.\
\
In the Voidwalker (VW) room there are 3 mobs to worry about. The first is a fleshling beast. He's non-elite, just pull him into the sentinal room and kill him. The second mob that poses an issue is a VW that patrols from the center of the room to the doorway of the sentinal room. Third, there is another VW that patrols from the center of the room to the arcane container. These patrols are random, but every once in a while they do match up. The weakness in the room is when they are both in the middle of the room.\
\
First, open the arcane container. If you have good timing and a little luck, you can stealth as the container opens and the keeper spawns. If not, just vanish. After the keeper spawns, the trick is to wait until both the VWs are in the center of the room. Distract them there to ensure they stay in the middle for a few extra seconds. Next, run over to the keeper and gun/bow/throw pull him. Have him follow you back to the sentinal room, and kill him there.\
\
This way you don't have to deal with voidwalkers, and you can take your time on the keeper.",
    "983220267150202672007/01/11 22:05:08mrmcpheeFollow-up: http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=9836",
    "98327636160763612007/05/02 03:12:18IseultThe key guardian, despite looking like a VW, classes as a beast. Druids can just Hibernate and Starfire it; it's not immune. I did this for the second key fragment. It took me a while, but I never got hit once.",
    "9832211949102119492008/01/03 01:42:01cenaforeveru'll get the secoun key from SV its in the water before the first boss [Naga] then u have to do ARC after the first boss [all ppl skip him] u go up there is a place that have alot of shadow elementals in the right of the entrance of that room u'll find the third frag ! [good luck with the next quest]",
    "983235335241352572007/02/13 16:03:33BoggsAs of the patch today, the containers spawn an elite mob that must be defeated to obtain the key.",
    "983245228340452282007/03/02 16:43:04XukimondeWhile it's nice that so many classes are capable of soloing these key fragments, let's all take some time to remember that instances were intended for groups.\
\
Don't forget to ask people on your friend or guild list (at least) if they are also in need of the key fragment you're going for. It's much more efficient to go in as a group and wreck up the joint than it is to cunningly solo up to them and miss out on four other people you could run Karazhan with not having their fragments completed.",
    "983227916560279162007/01/30 20:56:13SinsweeperThere are three ways to go about doing this quest. \
\
First and most obvious, complete the instances. The fragment from Steamvault is at the bottom of the pond leading up to the Naga boss. The fragment from Arcatraz is on the right side of the room where the first boss (a voidwalker) is at. \
\
Second, you can \"borrow\" someoen's completed instances. Do a /who check on who's doing the instances and ask them if they can preserve the group after they've cleared it. Then, simply go in and acquire the fragments. \
\
Third, if you're a druid or a rogue, then you can actually solo (if u're a rogue) or duo (if u're a driud) this. Second fragment is straightforward, stealthing into the pond wouldn't be a problem at all if you had at least 1 point into Master of Deception/feral instinct. The third fragment from arcatraz is slightly more difficult. You need to go through a narrow tunnel before you reach the room with the fragment, and in that tunnel sits a mechanical bot that does an AoE lightning zap which hits all targets around him every 2 seconds. If you're a rogue, then turn on sprint and run through him, and vanish until AFTER you're well out of the range of his lightning (which is around 15 yards). If you're a druid, then you must have another rogue or druid to help you pull him away; note that, even if you are hit by his lightning, you won't get into combat, so just wait for prowl to cooldown after u get hit by the lightning, and run into the room.",
    "9832173545101735452007/10/23 08:47:54HoosecowNote that you need the ability to fly to get to the third key fragment. A Warlock cannot summon you up to the entrance platform.",
    "9832151020101510202007/09/09 20:51:09deadaloneIt is possible to do this as a Warrior solo also.. kind of tricky though.  \
\
You'll need a soulstone from a warlock.\
\
Pop on tanking gear and go in defensive stance.\
\
Second, run as close as you can to the first mobs, pop an invisiblity potion and then use your nifty stopwatch, run around to the left (to avoid the stealth detecting giant mob) and get as close to the water as you can, by the time you are around there, your invisibility will be wearing off, so you must die between the hallway and the pack of 4 mobs there, make sure you can use the soulstone in a safe spot, because you'll need to be out of combat when you res up to use another invis pot.\
\
\
Once you res, use the next pot and jump to water.. open thing and kill mob.. get fragment.\
\
Of course it might be easier finding a group to just do this, since you have to wait 10 minutes to use the potion again, but meh, if you know a warlock that won't mind soulstoning you I guess it's worth it.",
    "98322970121279162007/02/02 21:20:08GokouFor the second key fragment no need to complete the instance, or in fact kill any bosses. All you have to do is killed a few trash mobs. When you enter the instance in the first room, kill the Underbog Overlord to the right. Go to the spot where he was standing and wade through the bushes. Kill the 2nd Overlord. After that go straight and you should see a little hill. Kill whatever mobs you need to get over the hill. Once you get there, there should be a large pond nearby. Go into the water and you should see the Arcane Container.",
    "9832170969101709692007/10/18 09:02:08Darkriftdid the SV key frag as a resto shaman solo.  here's how:\
