    "983229939120299392007/02/03 09:05:19dheemersiThe second key is soloable for a lvl 68+mage. Train invisiblity, buy some invisibility potions and go into Steamvaults(second instance on the left). Get as close to the first set of mobs as you can, pop invisibility, run dead center(the bog lords to the left and right can detect invis) then a little to the right after the first stone column(about a 100 meter run from start to pool). Just as invis is running out pop a invis potion and dive into the pool. The arcane container is at the bottom of the pool(20 meters down)",
    "98325533490553342007/03/22 11:00:47NirodhaI just soloed both these fragments and wanted to give some tips on the 3rd fragment (the one in arcatraz) It was much more involved then the steamvualt's second fragment.\
\
First have at least 350 lock picking or the arcatraz key.\
\
Once inside, there is a short hallway at the end of which there is a larger circular room with a fight going on. Fleshling style mobs are running to into the room opposite the side you entered on. Blood elves are killing them quickly. I moved to the side of the doorway the fleshlings are coming through then waited for the BE frontline to finish off one of the bigger black fleshlings then when the rest hug the narrow hallway's wall and move into the next room (with 5 ranks of MOD you practically have to touch hall mobs to pull aggro).\
\
The next room was my least favorite part. The first time through was a breeze cause i got lucky with the timing. After that I realized that the right side of the room (where the next hallway is) was where the fleshings for the first room were spawning. If they repop on you your sunk or have to use a vanish. Hugging the wall to the right when you enter the room gave me the best results. Enter the next hallway paying mind to those corpses on the floor (all BE corpses in here spawn fleshlings.. don't walk on them.\
\
After this short hallway, there will be a translucent ramp straight ahead and to your right. Hug a side of this ramp and head up it. It will straighten out towards the top then narrow to a small hallway. There is a sentinel on the left side of this hallway in its center. Be sprinting when you enter the hall and immediately after entering the hall use Cloak of Shadows. You should resist his laser.. if you donât... use vanish. Hug the right wall after exiting the hallway. The fragment container is on this wall. Move to the corner by the container then wait for the voidwalker patrol to move to the center of the room. I like every reasonable advantage when Iâm fighting an elite of my level so I did this.\
\
Drink Potions. If you have an agility and mongoose, DRINK THE MONGOOSE FIRST. If you drink agility pots first mongoose will override them. Take whatever else you likeâ¦ then keep either a health pot , armor pot or invulnerability pot handy for the fight. In short, buff up.\
\
When the voidwalker has patrolled away open the container. Put 5 combo points on the guardian then vanish. Wait 5 minutes for vanish to cool down ( I waited in the same corner as the guardian).\
\
Then the fight. When the voidwalker patrols away he pauses sometimes before he clears the wall (the wall to your right when you stand in the corner and face the guardian). He is still in aggro range here. Once he moves away, DPS the crap out of the guardian. Use all your cool downs but save evasion (unless you have prep) in case the voidwalker comes back earlier â¦ if it looks like you will kill the guardian before the voidwalker comes back go ahead and pop evasion too. Keep in mind the guardian can be stunned and poisoned too!\
\
Buffed, I had about 7k Hp and about the best gear you could quest by yourself plus a couple of instance drops. My armory profile is under the same name, Iâm convinced mace spec saved me. When I did kill him I had him and the voidwalker pounding on me and 44 health left D:\
\
Good luck. Also I recommend doing this fragment first so you can laugh at how easy the steam vault one is :D",
