    "10408162651411539122007/10/04 03:29:53rayzoriumAh yes. As has been mentioned earlier, this happens when not all the disruptors are set by the same person. Have one person set ALL the disruptors, or this may happen.",
    "10408161582111539122007/10/01 21:35:22chuck101610/01/07 I tried it tonight and exactly the same thing happened. He summoned adds - we killed them - he stayed in shadowform and was untargetable. He just kept hitting us till we died or ran away.",
    "1040862307360623072007/04/05 01:24:09goodmanjWarning to warriors: Salhadaar's Stasis ability clears all buffs and auras, including your stance.  You are put into \"no stance\", and your toolbar switches to the \"no stance\" toolbar.  You probably have never seen this toolbar, so it's probably going to be blank.  So you're tanking along, when suddenly your ENTIRE TOOLBAR VANISHES.  Fun, eh?  Just hit one of your stance buttons and all will be well.",
    "1040827833100278332007/01/30 17:50:19Awbeeit seems if 1 person does all 3 pillars he wont get bugged",
    "10408177459211263032007/10/31 21:16:07LieandraBut the coordinates do help those people out that use the lightheaded addon. So having them here, being that lightheaded uses wowhead's data, is a great improvement to the site and the addon at the same time.",
    "1040814394711263702007/08/25 16:42:36Nart8/25/07  It appears the ice block no longer removes buffs.",
    "10408176990311263032007/10/30 18:58:30unitepunxOr throughout the entire quest chain, up until this final quest, you could actually pay attention the the giant ethereal floating mid air in the same area you have been working in with the random (completely non-uniquely named) mob, Nexus-King Salhadaar. [/sarcasm(not really)]",
