    "1077316581311423562007/10/11 02:46:19RarehunterYou really have to watch out - the respawns are really fast. In fact, they are less than a minute, so one corpse run will be enough to allow most of the mobs to respawn. Along with the respawn rates, aggro is immense here. One step off and you might aggro another group of three. Be on guard, as the patrolling Cavaliers and their 70 elite leader aggros too. If your luck is bad, you could have a couple Sons of Corok, six+ sunfury mobs, 5+ cavaliers, and a 70 elite on you all at once. Not good.",
    "107733223230322322007/02/07 12:26:41AprusObviously, the mobs are all on The Path of Conquest. Good place to fight mobs is 55,69, where the path starts on the back side. Holy Paladins can solo this (I did), but expect to take about 5 minutes per Son of Corok.",
    "107733788710378872007/02/18 02:41:07stylewalkerAs an affliction Warlock, lvl 68 i soloed this q. Soldiers are easy, but often they come in pack of 3, where one is a caster. \
\
Cavalier's are not hard either, but after you kill the humanoid, you will have to fight the mount aswell. Cavalier's give's you a debuff that lowers spelldamage with 75%, a bit pain for casters.\
\
Son of Corok's hit pretty hard on cloth, but clear an area and chain fear until dead will work. As above poster said, about 5 minutes for each Son is correct.",
    "107735707220570722007/03/25 15:44:42biohazrdWatch for patrolling Cavaliers, they tend to chain pull many mobs. They also have absurd patrolling paths, so watch where you sit down to eat.",
    "107734235610423562007/02/25 21:02:22ranky26Perhaps its a recent change, but the respawn rate on the mobs, ie. Soldiers and Spellbinders is very fast. 1-2 minutes at max",
    "10773140040201400402007/08/18 11:01:24Hat3d150 63 at the very top, is an area that you can see the pat coming, get out of the way, and just pull 1 son the cavvy;s and the soldiers,\
\
quest solo'd by 70 hunter there.",
    "10773128244101282442007/07/28 12:37:41frostymageIf you're looking to solo, kill mobs at the bottom of the path, rather than the top. Just go as far south as possible, and when you reach the fork, take the path that goes down. Basically, it's the section of the path that leads toward Altar of Shadows. The elite with all the adds doesn't patrol down there, and there are a couple cavaliers, one Son of Corok, and more than enough soldiers there.The respawn is quite fast, so you won't have to worry about running out of mobs.",
    "107738326010832602007/05/15 02:53:41kulgarAll above posts are correct, just watch for a boss and his mounted guard travelling up the road every 10 minutes or so, if they arrive just run to the edge of the cliff and they will pass by without aggroing, a pain if your mid fight with a son of corok though",
    "107736246721604422007/04/05 09:57:01NeonGenesisBreaching the path (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10751) which you did is Horde-side.\
