    "108983212550321252007/02/07 08:16:18IlliminHe is vulnerable to incapacitates and stuns. Interrupts are very useful as two of his nukes are potent and have 2 second cast times (chain lightning and lightning cloud.) His melee is fairly weak. He has a very powerful instant lightning nuke that he uses perhaps every 10-15 seconds. This is quite easily soloable by any class 65+ if you use consumables and abilities correctly. Use the line of sight of the tower you fight on to your advantage if you need to interrupt chain lightning. Do not let him beat on the bird for more than a few seconds. If he gets a cloud off, kite him (and thus the bird you're escorting) out from underneath it. On the way to him you will not fight more than two arrakoa at the same time.",
    "10898191060111837652007/11/25 14:09:11TyrarlI can confirm this happened as well, but I'm not sure whether it's the \"jump down from the platform\" that's causing it or the fact he gets into a fight before he even finishes jumping to the lower platform that does it.",
    "1089837291121365202007/02/16 23:37:23KaganarBy reading the posts above I thought this quest was hard -- it isn't. I managed to solo it as a level 65 shadow priest (that is, no shadowfiend) with full health and half mana at the end and no potions. I imagine other classes with at most health potions and/or bandages can do the same. Here's how:\
\
The elite at the end doesn't appear to have much of a physical attack and only chain lightning to supplement it. So, three key points:\
\
1. Clear the mobs on the final platform ASAP before Skywing summons the elite! You must be engaged in combat (that is, the mob is hitting you or Skywing) to prevent the summoning. The final platform itself after you jump down after Skywing and cross the bridge.\
\
2. The platform the elite mob spawns on has a center to it which is subject to line of sight. This is to your advantage. When the elite begins to cast chain lightning, run out of its line of sight. Stay out of light of sight until the elite's casting bar goes away. The cast time is about three seconds, so you've plenty of time. This prevents you from ever getting hit by chain lightning.\
\
3. Don't get knocked off. The knockback isn't very far, but it's enough to ensure that if you're near the edge, you've failed the quest.\
\
Good luck!",
