\
1. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10944 [70] The Secret Compromised\
For this quest you just return to Akama.\
2. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10946 [70] Ruse of the Ashtongue\
Inthis quest, you must use the costume Akama provides, and kill A'lar inTempest Keep: The Eye while wearing the Ashtongue Cowl. Attunement forThe Eye is a whole different chain.\
3. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10947 [70] An Artifact From the Past\
Inthis, you need to gain access to The Battle of Mount Hyjal in Cavernsof Time, and slay the first boss, Rage Winterchill. Attunement for thisinvolves killing Lady Vashj and Kael'Thas Sunstrider.\
4. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10948 [70] The Hostage Soul\
For this you must speak with A'dal in Shattrath city.\
5. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10949 [70] Entry into the Black Temple\
For this, just speak with the naaru Xi'ri in front of Black Temple.\
6. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10985 [70] A Distraction for Akama\
Unknownwhat this quest asks of you, most likely you need to defend Xi'ri andmake your way into Black Temple. At the end, you become attuned toenter and are granted The Medallion of Karabor (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32649)\
\
Atthis point, you are attuned and can enter Black Temple, although thechain continues and you can soon upgrade your medallion. It continueswith:\
\
1. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10958 [70] Seek Out the Ashtongue\
You just need to find Seer Kanai (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=23158) inside Black Temple.\
2. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10957 [70] Redemption of the Ashtongue\
This involves entering Black Temple, and killing the boss the Shade of Akama (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=22841).\
3. http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10959 [70] The Fall of the Betrayer\
Afterkilling the Shade of Akama and returning to Seer Kanai, he asks onelast thing of you. Kill Illidan The Betrayer. After doing so, you aregranted the Blessed Medallion of Karabor, an upgraded version of youroriginal medallion, and allows teleportation to the Black Temple.",
    "1095914010451988982007/08/18 12:55:15Bonez0rThe links in your post after step 4 don't link to the correct pages.",
    "1095919313051987252007/11/29 03:27:12TaothThe three examples you give for character resurrection are bogus, only Medivh is relativly accurate, and that can be written off to his extreme magical ability for his soul/whatever to linger after death and reform a body whatever.\
Regarding Kazzak, you're not seriously trying to say that storywise raids actively had an impact? Of course not. Ignoring raid activity, when BC was released the story became that kazzak was stranded and looking for a way to reopen the dark portal, and when he succeeded he went back through it.\
Regarding Kael, if you look at the quest from the verdant sphere itself, the quest specifically says you take it from a \"still twitching body\" of Kael. Upon turning it in, Adal also specifically says that Kael indeed was still alive when the raid party left. There was no decapitation, so while maimed the true killing blow was never delivered and thus he was able to leave after the raid left. They didnt exactly drag his body out for a trophy.\
\
Illidan however was specifically killed by Maiev, she wouldnt have left or expressed the comments of feeling nothing at having finally killed him. Having such hatred theres no way she wouldnt have given a mortal blow.\
Besides, Illidan turned insane, convincing himself that he actually beat Arthas instead of losing, so why would he return regardless.",
    "10959162439401624392007/10/03 15:56:00FarundThe Item you Gain, has a 15min CD and teleports you to just outside Black Temple, very useful just like a 15min CD hearthstone to Outlands.",
    "10959987251180987252007/06/05 14:05:48TaemojitsuYou do not kill Illidan. After getting him to a certain percentage in the fight (with the assistance of Akama), Maiev comes to finish him off. As he dies, Illidan utters this line of dialogue:\
http://www.invictuswow.com/pics/BLACK_Illidan_16.wav\
\
Illidan may be dead (at least until we get tired of killing him), but his legacy lives on. His actions during his life will forever leave an imprint in our memories, as despite his eventual fall into darkness, Illidan Stormrage DID save the world. Multiple times.",
    "1095999555301987252007/06/06 14:48:31KalJWheter he is actually dead or not in lore is still to be seen. While apparently Maiev killed him, in blizzard games there are several notable cases of npcs/bosses/characters that were killed only to come back alive and kicking in later games. Most notable examples are Medivh - killed in WC2 only to come back in WC3 - Kazzak, killed and raided to death only to become the one responsible for the dark portal opening and be promoted to TBC outdoor raidboss, and lastly Kael'thas sunstrider, which according to various comments turn out to be beaten but alive,  yelling in shattrath when you turn in the http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32405 to ada'l.\
I find it quite interesting that unlike several of the raid bosses that are confirmed to be 100% dead ( ossirian, nefarian, onyxia, maghteridon ) you don't get the \"head of Illidan\" as a quest starting item to turn in somewhere.\
Don't know what blizzard plans for him, but I wouldn't be surprised to have him leave BT to a lieutenant  demon hunter  and then run to Northrend ( or whatever will be the area for next xpac ) to settle scores with Arthas and become a level 80 raidboss,  just as it happened to Kazzak at the start of tbc.",
    "1095919515711987252007/12/02 23:59:23NysaI agree with you on that. Mainly, I just got to thinking about it, and if they're making Death Knights a hero class they're certainly not leaving out Demon Hunter's. So why not have your demon hunter learn from the best one there is? If he really did die, I'm sure its not permanent and they'll bring him back if/when they come out with a Demon Hunter class just to do the same thing they're doing with Arthas. I could totally be wrong too, though. =P",
