    "11015125234101252342007/07/23 00:03:43wowrogue24Well just incase it helps what helped me wit this quest is switch between the mobs just to do something different so its not mindless grinding.. yeah i know its hard but also theres a chance ( even though its little) an egg will drop off the mob you are grinding on i just had one drop ^_^ but yeah just switch it around a bit",
    "110151003141601003142007/06/07 17:00:39PseudoOur good friends at wowwiki have a listing of all the quests at http://www.wowwiki.com/Netherwing\
\
However, detailed information isn't exactly there, so you'll want to keep wowhead up for your specific browsing..\
\
This is a standalone daily quest, one of the first you can get. Aside from the daily limit of 10 daily quests, no other quests will prevent you from doing this (assuming you're neutral with Netherwing).\
\
Crystal's ONLY drop on/in Netherwing Ridge. You can have an Unlimited(?) number of these crystals, and can farm for them before, during, and after accepting the quest. So done with quests for the night? Farm some extras for tomorrow so you can save time the following day.\
\
-Pseudo",
    "11015198457101984572007/12/09 10:24:06NatasiaThis quest is quite the annoying one to be done solely on its own but one that you would do while doing;\
\
Picking up the Pieces\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=11076 \
\
Dragons are the Least of Our Problems\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=11077\
\
But if you choose to \"grind\" this quest I would suggest grinding the Crazed Murkblood Miner http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=23324 as they have a decent drop rate at about 1 in 3 and if they do not drop you are still getting good trade goods like Netherweave Cloth and Netherwing Eggs.\
\
Everyone has their 20 cents worth hope mine is worth more to you.",
    "1101588375190883752007/05/23 11:31:01ToaboBased on my first night of farming, this was the quest seemed the biggest time sink of the Neutral ->Friendly, but your results may vary.  (And if you're determined to be first on your block to be Exalted, you'll have to grit your teeth and power through it regardless.) \
\
These crystals drop from essentially any mob on Netherwing Ridge.  Above ground, you'll find nether rays lurking around the edges of the Ridge and flayers on the mountains further in.  The flayers are more densely packed for easy farming, but that also makes them popular with your fellow grinders.  The nether rays tend to be less over-farmed and the respawn rate is decent enough to keep a solo player from having too much downtime.  Only risk is that some of the nether ray packs are near paths of the patrolling elite drakonids.  These guys have ~100K health and hit hard, so best just to avoid them.  \
\
I found less competition in the underground mine, though that may change when more folks may find out about it.  On the other hand, it's much less convenient to get to since you can't fly, so maybe folks won't bother.\
\
You'll have to go fairly deep into the mine to find mobs.  You'll see slimes and worms mostly in the central tunnel as you enter.  Further in you'll get access to some side tunnels which feature flayers and ravagers.  Way in the back you'll find murkbloods (hostile, unlike the friendly ones at the mine entrance).  I was with a skinner, so we focused mostly on the flayers and ravagers and had decent results.  \
\
You can only turn in 40 Crystals per day, but you can collect as many as you can carry.  Thus, you can get a jump on the next day's turn-in by farming longer.",
