    "10583127950201279502007/07/27 19:07:46frostymageThe Deathforge is plain ridiculous. The respawn rate is insane, mobs aggro from very far away, the mobs use ridiculous abilities (Shrapnel bomb, mines), and getting adds is easy. When you die, the mobs will have respawned, leaving you no safe place to rez.\
\
Bring a friend, or expect to die a lot.",
    "10583123178101231782007/07/19 06:22:50VindriziJust dont break the balls , only kill whats \"standing\"",
    "10583178219101782192007/11/02 16:40:03regarrMore precise coordinates for Flanis are: 34.6 39.9",
    "10583100490201004902007/06/08 01:42:20romanesEasiest way I found to do this was to make sure I had enough bag space, take off all my gear and suicide run through.  died twice on the way (with no cost) - and once i got the pack, just hearthed out",
    "10583128634201286342007/07/29 10:45:32SmitaThe way I did this was I unequipped all of my armor and weapons and corpse ran to Flanis. It may not be the absolute best way, but it worked. It took me four deaths to get to him, and I was able to quickly click to gather his pack before the last death. Luckily, you do not have to corpse run back out, but rather, rez above ground on the road where the Pariah (the bird guy) patrols.",
    "105832954591263752007/02/02 15:58:51edessain order to get the Bring Down the Warbringer! quest you must complete both The Fate of Flanis & The Summoning Chamber.  You still get the quest Bring Down the Warbringer! from Stormer Ewan Wildwing.",
    "10583123644101236442007/07/20 00:13:47ZiliikatusActually this was easy with 2... 70 shaman and hunter... but i could have soloed it too... for the Dormant Infernal just need to stick to the middle... they have a really small Aggro range...also depend on class and built... but generally easy... just need to be aware of the Tinker/Elemental Pat... died once but that is cause I was careless.",
    "105834381740438172007/02/28 06:52:39AbzillaI would suggest doing this in a group to speed up the process.  I did this as a solo full prot warrior, at one point I would die, run back, and there would be respawns, by the end I just run in, die, res, run in some more.  He is at the VERY FAR BACK, and every inch of the place has 68+ mobs.  So get a group going and finish it in one go.",
    "10583156634101566342007/09/22 11:21:38ookluhGot discouraged when I saw Kagrosh, the Horde's NPC.. almost ran out, but went a little further - turns out Flanis is in the room just beyond him.\
\
Paladins, don't forget that there are demons (including the Tinkerers), so make sure to use your Demon combat abilities.  Soloed this as a 70 Prot Pally with no problems (though I was fortunate enough to not really have any adds to each group that I fought while in there).  The Dormant mobs don't attack unless you attack them, so don't Consecrate near them.",
    "10583189827301898272007/11/23 06:29:47CannonballBetter than having any exact coordinates for the corpse, simply go to [u]40,38[/u] as stated above, take the tunnel to the [u]right[/u]. Move to the very end of this tunnel, it will be quite a lot of mobs to fight on the way and the the fact that newly made elementals to craft infernals are being escorted from the summoning room into the \"factory\" and they are being spawned regulary. When you reach a door requiring Deathforge Key you've reached a milestone, skip the door and keep moving. Next into the narrow tunnel, keep in the middle and fight the newly made infermals and after those you will meet two deathforge guardians. Behind them stands a summoner with his demon, kill him and you've free passage to the corpse of Flanis.\
\
If you're a [b]ranged class the corpse of the summoner might drop down over Flanis[/b], so you don't do the mistake of not being able to find him like I did (went back out again thinking where the heck this guy could be), so I was there twice. Fortunatly I checked extra carefully and his corpse was under the summoner :-)",
  },
