    "1080516765npcBaron Sablemane22103npcBaron Sablemane2210314600110797210798310799410800510801610802710818810805910806",
    "1080590316120903162007/05/25 13:49:07novacurseI don't know if this changed after patch 2.1, but the mobs definetley aggro when feared into, especially the ravagers. At least, they all did for me several times.",
    "1080517316111903162007/10/22 13:13:05unitepunxThey will also leash most of the time if you try and kite them into a clearing outside of their pathing area. They did all night yesterday (patch 2.2.3). \
\
If you fear them just before the sky turns a bit lighter (outside of the area where they are) they tend to stay, but you have to check and see if they fear back into the crowd, which is a sure sign to book it out of there.",
    "10805127123201271232007/07/26 11:05:57EldarielDo yourself a favor; Get a group to do this with you. Also you can use the group to do the next follow-up: Showdown ( http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10806 ) He will be easy and can be two manned if played properly.",
    "1080526320190263202007/01/28 10:51:50fridgidThe mobs start at 62, 22 and are all elites. Almost all are single pulls and could probably be soloed, I would not recommend it. Its a lot of mobs and most have 24k hps+. Firegrom is really no different from any of the battle mages, just named. Pretty simple, just long if you solo.",
    "10805196314101963142007/12/05 07:46:51adashielMy favorite spot for doing this quest is the area behind Fingrom's building.  Ogres and raptors patrol the path above it, but they won't be close enough to add.  No mobs spawn in or patrol through the area itself.  There's not a huge amount of room, but it's sufficient to keep out of the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=19996]battlemages'[/url] flamestrikes and [i]maybe[/i] do some tight kiting.  I've even managed to chain fear there, with only one case where a feared mob ran into adds.",
    "10805187888101878882007/11/19 19:49:31UrbanGypsySoloed slowly but easily as a badly equipped (489 spell damage, 7070 mana) resto druid with enough in balance to get insect swarm.  Do the Ogri'la quests first so the ogres are neutral to you and you can generally pull the raptors separately by rooting the patrolling ones and attacking them after the accompanying ogre has moved off.  On the rare occasion they get linked in to another mob, just focus target the raptor and keep it slept whilst you take the ogre down first.  \
\
Fingrom was the only tricky part.  First off, make sure you've dealt with the patrol who wanders up and down to visit him.  Thereafter, good news - even though he's indoors you can still root him!  So stand in the doorway, open with a starfire, swiftly root him and move out of line of sight.  Straif back to cast moonfire, then straif out of line of sight again.  Straif back to cast insect swarm, then get back out of line of sight.  Rinse and repeat, leaving out the initial starfire.  If for any reason you're not fast enough and one of his fireballs hits you, one lifebloom is enough to get you back to full health.\
\
Hope that helps!",
    "10805194081101940812007/11/30 17:35:37siggboyIf you have the gear for Gruul's Lair (T4ish), this can be easily done solo as a hunter as well.  I used a boar because it holds aggro far better than any other pet (if it has Charge).  To kill the named, put the pet outside, downstairs, run up and misdirect to the pet, then shoot him.   Jump down immediately.  It's a bit tricky to place the pet so the \"boss\" doesn't have LoS because he is ranged, but worked for me.\
\
If your guild runs Gruul's Lair, you can complete this quest while you're waiting for the raid to gather.\
\
Just be careful about the pulls, and yes, completing Ogrila attunement first helps a lot (as mentioned above by somebody else).",
  },
