    "1009112886711374322007/07/29 20:29:40ManiaxAgain confirming that you can solo this whole thing as a rogue (I'm only 68). Right side of Blackhearts room has 2 in that tent, I sapped closest and gathered through the tent wall. Now have 2 orbs. Go to other side of the room and sap eastern most mob, then immediately blind the next mob. Gather, vanish, wait repeat. (Now have 4 orbs). Exit and reset to collect the last one on the right and your done!\
\
*TIP: If your subtlety spec it's even faster. Follow above direction then pop Prep! Rinse, repeat",
    "100913972821374322007/02/21 05:05:48senkeiConfirmed. This works for a rogue with Improved Sap.\
\
I stealthed all the way to blackheart's room easily. Sapped the closest guard to the soul device on the left side. I even used distract before moving behind the tent.\
\
I moved as far back as i could while still being able to operate the soul device.\
\
This was my final soul device so i'm not sure if it works at other locations. However if you really wanted to finish the quest, you can do what Duffs suggested (out, reset, repeat). This spot definintely works :D",
    "100913442850344282007/02/12 02:02:42FinneganThey are objects, not drops - and they have three prongs, the center of which has a small circular torch on the top.",
    "100913585530358552007/02/14 11:55:32McBainXIVThere are 4 in the room with Blackheart the Inciter, in the little huts to the left and right that there are orcs in.",
    "100916242431374322007/04/05 08:07:13GonoWith imp sap, this works on both soul devices in the tent on the right side when entering blackhearts room. Sap the closest mob, move behind the tent as far away from the mobs as possible and use device. I used distract when I got the one closer to the mobs, but I'm not sure if this is needed. \
\
Lvl 70 rogue.",
    "100913067060306702007/02/04 16:06:24FlyvThere are about seven of these devices scattered through the instance around the second and third boss. There's a whole lot more in the final room just before you fight the last boss, Murmur (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=18708).",
    "100916013271581332007/03/31 12:50:35BartMannYou cannot gather this one for the quest, its just a graphic.",
    "10091144292101442922007/08/26 11:07:44alwayslostI made multiple attempts to do this quest solo on a level 70 balance druid. It is an easy stealth to both Hellmaw's and Blackhearts rooms. Just stay as tight to the wall as you can. One npc to be extra careful of is the fel reaver that patrols the short hallway leading into Blackheart's room. The reaver has a short patrol, stopping just past the end of each side of the hallway. It's safe to run past him (between the wall and the brazier at the corner) into the hall when he is at the end of his patrol, and then run into and around the corner into Blackheart's room. I got stuck in the brazier at the far end the first time and didn't make it into the room. The reaver stopped and stared at me a long time, but did not aggro. \
\
There are two tents near the dias where Blackheart walks around. \
\
The left-hand tent (as you approach Blackheart) has two soul devices, one near the front as you approach the tent, the other at the back of the tent. I did not try the one near the front as it required getting too close to the mobs on that side. The one at the back \"should\" be collectible, but for some reason I could not see the device from behind the tent, and could not find an angle where the device was both visible and in range. Some posters seemed to have found a way to do this, but I couldn't get the angle. \
\
The tent on the other side only has one soul device. Had the same problem with camera angle on this one, too, until I figured out that there is a tiny crease at the back of the tent that allowed me to see inside. I was able to collect this device, being very careful to stay at max distance possible before unstealthing. It's tricky, and I died a couple of times when I didn't have just the right position. \
\
So it's definitely doable, if you have a lot of patience and are willing to reset and re-enter multiple times.",
    "100916488510648852007/04/10 09:25:32NavarothI soloed this quest as a level 70 rogue without Improved Sap (http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=14076), just go behind the hut to the right, so far away you can, take the sould devices, quit the instance and reset it, repeat. I am sure it could be done as a feral druid too :).",
    "10091173464101734642007/10/23 03:12:40scott541soloed as 70 feral druid with 3/3 feral instinct, and +1 stealth level on my boots, just go as much range as i could from the hut, then collected, and quickly shadowmelded (the closest guy turned around when i went unstealthed, so pretty close to failing)",
    "10091181310101813102007/11/09 04:15:18Spookeh1- unequip all your durability items, you will probably die several times.\
\
2- you can get into shadow lab without the key, by dying outside the gate and ressing inside. (fly up, and drop worked for me)\
\
3- if you harvest 1 soul device and reset each time, you'll not be able to go into another instance for 1 hour afterwards (You have entered too many instances recently!)\
\
\
How to collect the devices: the only one i found i could get was in Blackheart the Inciter's room, as you enter, its in a blue tent on the far right. There's 2 guys just outside the tent, and 2 devices, one of which is in the far right corner (looking at it as you enter the room)\
\
Go behind the corner of the tent, spin the camera around with left mouse button so you can see inside it, and loot. If you're about 2-3 yards away, you can loot without aggroing the guys. Run out, reset, repeat x5. takes about 4-5 mins per attempt.\
\
A note on the distance: if you're more than ~2-3 yards away when you right click on something, you character runs over to it, and stops next to it, and starts to open it. The problem with this is you stop VERY close to the item, say 1-2 yards from it. This will get aggro and you'll die.\
If you're about 2-3 yards away, you can still loot, but your character doesn't move forwards. \
This distance difference is crucial, turn 'always run' off, will help you move to the right place (default key is numpad slash: / )\
\
\
total time for soloing the whole chain was about an hour.",
    "100915940831374322007/03/29 20:50:30silwithinDruid - Stealth Run;\
\
I was unable to do it as a druid, I managed the first part of the quest by going around the boss as close to the wall as possible (he sees through stealth) and then received this quest.\
\
I found the tent as explained above, and knowing that I was too close to the mobs (even though I was as far as I could go and still operate the Soul Device) - I still unstealthed. I attempted from the back of the tent, and the left side while facing, and from the corner away from the mobs - and all three of the mobs there came after me every time.",
    "10091160047101600472007/09/28 20:02:16SoYeah101i solo'd this as a lvl 70 combat rogue with 13 points in the subtility tree. \
\
first enter the instance and make sure to stay out of the mobs agro ranges. use distract to keep them looking away from you. keep doing this till you reach the large room where the stands are. \
\
now go over to each side, there should be two mobs there. sap the closest one and begin to open the devices. when the other one agros use blind to get him away from you. finesh opening and use vanish when blind wears off. \
\
wait for your cooldowns to come back and repeat. there are only 4 stands in the room so you mite have to reset the instance once and go back in. \
\
yes it takes awhile but if you cant seem to get a shadow labs group going and need better armbands then its worth it",
    "10091123314101233142007/07/19 11:08:20teukkaAs a lv 70 frost mage I was able to solo Find Spy To'gun quest. Got 1 Soul Device from tent West side of the room where 2nd boss is but I got agro when I tried get another Soul Device from tent.",
    "100913743240374322007/02/17 08:37:41DuffsI would imagine this is possible as a rogue or druid to stealth run this quest. As you enter the room of Blackheart the Inciter, go to the top right hand corner of the room, and there's a purple tent with 2 soul devices in. If you very carefully go behind the tent, and edge closer to the soul devices, you are able to loot them and get away without pulling the mobs, then out -> reset -> repeat.\
