    "10011208271102082712007/12/27 15:33:48KrilvThis quest is soloable by pretty much anything other than a paladin, rogue, or warrior. \
On my 67 elemental shaman, I was able to wiggle between the mobs surrounding the named guys and LB him, and then beginning to kite. \
They are immune to snares and roots and they both run at 100% movement speed, so you have to be very good with jump-turn-cast-turn-land-run. (don't worry, neither mob has a ranged attack)\
\
Other than that, my only problem was mana, With my shaman Water shield made it fairly easy, just recasting Flame shock as the dot drops off. This can be done with moonfire and warlock dots. I made it all the way to Garadar, and the guards made short work of them, causing alot of whispers by bystanders asking what I was doing. \
\
The only problem was the respawn rate, by the time I rode back to the spot, they were already respawned, so I had to kite Demos around the green thing infront of him and use a stoneclaw totem to make just enough time to finish the use of the cannon. XIrkos was a different story, I had to use my pocket tank (Earth Elemental Totem) which made it easy. However I have no clue how one would turn it in without the elemental. \
\
All and all, it was ALOT of fun and easily one of the best experiences Ive had in WoW.\
\
Krilv - Tauren Shammy\
Twisting Nether",
