  ["Hallow's End Treats for Jesper!70"] = {
    "831117066npcJesper15310npcJesper153101250Darnassus250Exodar250Gnomeregan Exiles250Ironforge250Stormwind250",
    "8311170798401707982007/10/18 02:34:15failquailOn completion of this quest you will be able to purchase [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=20557]Hallow's End Pumpkin Treats[/url] from Katrina Shimmerstar in Ironforge located outside the bank.",
    "8311171061301710612007/10/18 11:29:55TaliaMokaniTook me awhile, but I finally found Talvash at 36,4 in IF, off in a back corner of the Mystic Ward area. The others are easy, they're all in the major inn of the city.",
    "8311161253201612532007/10/01 08:19:43FirebrandThis quest is a joke when you have a mage with you.  Free candy!!",
    "8311172265901722652007/10/20 14:06:57PokesyEasy way to do the quest in a very short time: (Any non-mage class)\
1. Accept the quest from Jesper (He's located in: Stormwind: 47,35) (People with no cords:he's located in the orphan house just abit north from the east enterance of the Cathedral Square,just check the map for a little house shaped orange square.)\
2. Head to Stormwind's main Inn (53,65) (People with no cords:it's just to the right from the water fountain located in the Trade District)\
3.Speak to the inn keeper and accept the quest,do a /flex emotion at her and grab the Stormwind Nougat.\
4. Take the Deeprun Tram to Ironforge\
5. In Ironforge head to Talvash Del Kissel. (34,6) (People with no cords: He's just east of the Mage trainer hall in The Mystic Ward)\
6. Accept the quest and do a /train emotion at him,grab the Gnomeregan Gumdrop.\
7. Now go to Ironforges main Inn located at. (21,53) (People with no cords: It's abit north from the auction house,just check the signs above the buildings north of the AH.)\
8. Accept the quest and do a /chicken emotion at the inn keeper,grab the Ironforge mint.\
9. At this point,if you're a druid then use Teleport: Moonglade and fly to Darnassus. If not you're going to have to hearthstone to shattarth (That is if you have it,if you don't fly to menethil harbor and take the boat to auberdine,then to darnassus.)\
10. At darnassus head to the inn at: (68,15) (People with no cords: Just open your map and head to the \"S\"  in the Craftmens Terrace.)\
11. Accept the quest and do a /dance emotion at the inn keeper. grab the marzipan and you're done :).\
Now head back to Stormwind and make an orphan happy.\
I hope this is any help to anybody.",
    "8311171135201711352007/10/18 13:40:42KaashammerThis quest also awards you with 250 reputation with Alliance, which is very nice for such an easy quest.",
    "831120148020142006/10/18 09:21:43pinktoqueJesper can be found in the Stormwind Orphanage of Cathedral Square in Stormwind City at coordinates 47,35.",
    "8311177308201773082007/10/31 13:32:17wowisashthe quest start by going INSIDE the orphanage in Cathedral district in SW, and taking the quest from Jesper (I didn't see the sign, but sure want to now!) \
\
(if you are lower level, you may want to set your HS to SW, just to make it easier) \
\
First, go to the Inn by the bank in Trade district. The innkeeper will have a ! above her; talk to her, and get the Stormwind Nougat by typing /flex, and then talking to her again after the ? shows up. \
\
*She will have ANOTHER !, but just ignore it, and move on! \
\
Next, on to IF. If you are really low level, it is easiest to just take the tram. otherwise, tram or griffin - your choice. \
\
In IF there are 2 - the Gnome is in the Mystic Ward, just to the right of the gnome area, if you exit the tram and go left. You will see him in the corner, on a building porch. For the Gumdrop, talk to him, /train, and collect. \
\
For the Mint, talk to the Innkeeper close to the bank/AH. He wants you to do a /cluck or /chicken. Again, collect the candy. \
\
The last one, well - was easy for me, or any druid(ess) able to get to Moonglade - just teleport to MG, and take the hipp flight to Teladrassil. Run up into Darn, ask any guard where the inn is. \
\
Go over to the inn, talk to her, do a /dance (nice Jay-Z ref there), and collect your Marzipan. If your HS is set to SW, just hearth on back. \
\
The only problem I see is if you are really low level, and need to get to Darnassus. My only suggestion is to put a VERY NICE REQUEST into General, seeing if a friendly mage will open a portal. Explain your level, and what quest it is for. If you are in IF, ask for a Darn portal, and then plan on HSing back. \
\
As for the treats, yep - you collect 30 of the things; the effects are cool, but they will all disappear in 14 days after collection (unlike the other candies you buy). \
\
ps - do NOT forget about the apples!!! They are awesome for any level - not only do the yrestore MOST of your health and mana, but also give a temp 25% boost to both spirit & stamina!!!",
