    "1080444688291235072007/03/01 16:28:40defektungeWhen you feed the drakes, make sure you don't have Lightning Shield or any other similar buff on you. After eating, the drake will cast some harmless effect on you (doesn't show up in the log so I don't know what it does), which while completely harmless will still cause such defensive shields to \"attack back\"... causing the dragon to aggro and come after you. You still get quest credit, but you'll have an angry lvl70 elite chasing you.",
    "1080475305140753052007/04/30 06:07:13AisenfaireTrivia:  The dragons will eat the carcass and then tell you, \"Belan shi karkun\", which is apparently Draconic for \"Thank you, mortal.\"",
    "108045272461295992007/03/17 15:11:46clovis6780Since the meat has a cooldown of 30 seconds, it is probably best to lay down the meat immediately when you pick it up so that you don't have downtime just laying it down after you've picked up all the meats required.",
    "108046115740611572007/04/02 15:38:06greengooVerified: You can kill Netherstorm Netherdrakes (by switching to \"at war\") In order to skin them or complete quests and NOT LOSE REP.",
    "1080461003101609952007/04/02 10:58:52DubbillOnce you hit neutral with Netherwing you can toggle At War in your reputation panel. You can then kill Netherdrakes without penalty to your reputation.",
    "108046466210646622007/04/09 22:18:03NobodyYouKnow<b>Mobs</b>\
The rocknail flayers do a physical debuff called \"flayer flesh\", which increases the physical damage you take by 87ish damage you take for the next 15 seconds. Sadly, there is about one rocknail flayer per spawn. However, there is at least 10 different Rocknail spawns so lack of mobs shouldn't be an issue.\
\
The rocknail rippers do a physical debuff called rend flesh, which is basicly a DoT. The damage DoT does is also effected by \"flayer flesh\". The rocknail flayers are bigger than the rocknail rippers. \
\
Both the rocknail flayers and the rocknail rippers are melee. They do not cast anything.\
\
Watch out for Ruul, an elite lvl 68-72 mob that wanders around the area. From a distance Ruul looks like a very large dragonkin (about two times larger than the drakes), but that is actually Ruul's mount.\
\
[b]Drops[/b]\
The Rockanil Flayers drop a Rocknail Flayer Carcass at least 99% per kill. The rocknail rippers drop one Rocknail Flayer Giblets at least 99% per kill. If you have five rocknail flayer giblets, you can find it in your bag and right click on it to turn it into a Rocknail Flayer Carcass. For this reason, you want to kill the Rocknail Flayers as much as possible. \
\
[b]Feeding the drakes[/b]\
There are two ways of doing this. \
\
The first way is:\
Once you have one Rocknail flayer carcass, try to find a drake. They tend to fly 100-200 yards above the ground. Once you can see one, target it and then use the rocknail flayer carcass. If you do not target a drake first, you will get a red system error saying no target. It takes about four seconds for you to drop the rocknail flayer carcass. When you do you have to stick around for up to 30 seconds before the drake you targeted lands on the ground and starts to eat the rocknail flayer carcass. Once the drake has eaten the carcass, it will have a debuff called fed. You do not get credit for feeding it until the drake lands, eats the carcass, and says something in draconic. Do not try to feed a drake with a feed debuff. This will only result in you waisting your carcasses. For this reason this quest can be a bit of a pain on PvP servers.\
\
The second way is this:\
First gather up eight rocknail flayer carcass. Then head to 67, 52. There are at least 10 hungry drakes there at any given time. Although ruul goes through the area, it is very easy to avoid him if you are watching out for him.  It's virtually impossible to aggro any of the rocknails unless you aren't watching what your doing.\
Target a drake and then use a rocknail flayer carcass there. It will take about three seconds for you to drop it. When you do you have to stick around for up to 30 seconds before the drake you targeted lands on the ground and starts to eat the rocknail flayer carcass. Once the drake has eaten the carcass, it will have a debuff called fed. You do not get credit for feeding it until the drake lands, eats the carcass, and says something in draconic. Do not try to feed a drake with a feed debuff. The problem with this way is the rocknail carcass has a 30 seconds cooldown, so you can only use a rocknail caracass once every 30 seconds.",
    "1080424616490246162007/01/25 19:09:12TomedKill the bigger Rocknails in order to get an entire carcass. Otherwise, the smaller ones drop an item that you need 5 of to combine into a carcass.",
    "1080432677650326772007/02/08 13:55:17greengooHow to get Neutral with Netherdrake (Netherdrake Epic Mount Quest Starter)\
A list by Greengoo\
\
1. Kindness\
- Kill 8 Rocknail Flayers, Use Carcasses to Feed 8 Dragons (don't move!). Also make sure to travel a bit when laying the meat, as the same drakes won't eat twice in a row.\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10804\
\
2. Seek Out Neltharaku\
- Fly on your mount and find Neltharaku, he patrols slowly around Dragonmaw about a few hundred feet up. You'll have to be about 5 yards UNDER him to talk to him.\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10811\
\
3. Neltharaku's Tale\
- Listen to story.\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10814\
\
4. Infiltrating Dragonmaw Fortress\
- Kill 15 of any type of orcs in the fortress.\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10836\
\
5.To Netherwing Ledge!\
- Find 12 Crystals from the floating island SE of the mainland.\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10837\
\
6. The Force of Neltharaku\
- Free 5 Dragons by using the item on them, then killing the orcs they agro.\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10854\
\
7. Karynaku\
- Find Karynaku, she's the second story of the fortress.\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10858\
\
8. Zuluhed the Whacked\
- Kill Zuluhed and recover the key. I recommend pulling him inside so as to avoid the archers, and kill him BEFORE he summons his add. Use the key he drops to free Karynaku.\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10872\
\
9. Ally of the Netherwing\
- Return to Mordenai, you will immediately gain 42,000 rep and become neutral.\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10870\
\
10. ????\
- Blizzard has announced that next patch they will be introducing a continuence of this quest line, including the ability to get exalted and purchase or receive through extensive questing an EPIC netherdrake mount. You will need epic training to use it however, so save your gold!",
    "108047113151646622007/04/22 16:12:04Elementx...you don't have to target the Drakes.  Just click on the carcass and drop it anywhere.  One will land and eat it.",
    "1080423507120235072007/01/24 05:27:26EminenceAccording to worldofraids.com this quest chain gives 42000 rep with \"netherwing\", so you end up at neutral reputation, and I guess you can then start some other quests :)",
    "108047841631235072007/05/06 00:09:48sylverfyreAlso make sure you dont have a searing totem or aggressive pet out, or it will attack the drake.  (defensive pet may react as well to the 'harmless spell' they cast on you and aggro the drake, I don't know.)",
