    "11220190522301905222007/11/24 17:10:26QueggyThe Headless Horseman is to be found inside the Graveyard of Scarlet Monastery during the Hallow's End period, which lasts two weeks. He's a three-phased boss, which is able to be killed with four average players.\
\
[b]Summoning[/b]\
Inside the Graveyard, an altar will appear, with an pumpkin upon it. Behind it, is a pile of dirt. By speaking to the pumpkin, you can get a candle, which delivered to the dirtpile behind, will summon the boss. He'll soar out, fly about a bit, and then land, charging the summoner. This will consume a Daily Quest, and can only be done once every two hours, I believe.  Summoning him requires level 70.\
\
 [b]Stage one[/b]\
Tank time. Nothing exciting happens. The tank tanks, DPS does DPS, and the healer heals.\
As soon as he hits 1%, his head will pop off, and land at a random location. If this head doesn't get damaged down to about 65% before his body hits 100% again, you have to fight through phase one again.\
\
[b]Stage two[/b]\
Ok, head reaches 65%, flies back to his body, and you're fighting again. This time, he has a new ability. Conflagrate. It'll do 10% damage for 5 ticks on a random target. It also does 10% damage to anyone close to that target, so try to move away quickly.\
Once he hits 1%, his head pops off again, so try to hit it down to 30%.\
\
[b]Stage three[/b]\
When the head hits 30%, he becomes whole again, and you're fighting agin. This time, he gets the ability to summon four helpful pumpkin guys. If you're quick, they should only have time to spawn before the Headless Horseman is dead. If not, try to kill the horseman anyway.\
The pumpkins don't do very much damage, but can disrupt  the healer. The Headless Horseman will summon four adds every now-and-then, while conflagrating and hitting the tank as usual. At 1% his head flies off, and you've got a floating skull. Kill it quickly, and party. Now go and loot the various drops he has.\
\
[b]The Looting[/b]\
The Headless Horseman usually drops anything between two to four items, maybe even five.\
Two items that are guaranteed to appear, are both a Broom and any of the three kinds of rings.\
- Rings:\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33957]Witches Band[/url]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=34075]Ring of Ghoulish Delight[/url]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=34073]The Horseman's Signet Ring[/url]\
[b]- Brooms:[/b]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33183#comments]Magic Broom, 60% land speed[/url]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33184#comments]Swift Magic Broom, 100% land speed[/url]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33176#comments]Flying Broom, 60%, Air speed[/url]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33182]Swift Flying Broom, 280%, Air speed[/url]\
- Other:\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33292]Hallowed Helm[/url]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33808]The Horseman's Helm[/url]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33154]Sinister Squashling[/url]\
\
He also drops [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=34068]Weighted Jack-'O-Lantern[/url], Pumpkins you can throw on top of allied heads.",
