    "11086141663701416632007/08/21 10:24:55PaddyjackThere are several comments already on the \"how to do it\", so I would like to point out something different about this quest. I have been doing the daily quests (Skyguard, Ogrila, Netherwing) for several weeks now, and I believe this one is a waste of time compared to the others. Let me explain:\
\
Basically, people are doing these daily quests for two reasons: money and reputation. Now, this quest is given in Shadowmoon Valley, but is performed in Nagrand (on the western side no less), so completely on the other side of the Outland world map. Moreover, it is not as easy as the other available daily quests such as bombing runs (skettis/ogrila), escort, the mining/pollen quests, relic emanations, etc, because several lvl 72 elites are patrolling the area (even more annoying than the dragonmaw ascendant if you see what I mean....). So if you are doing 10 daily quests for money, spare this one IMO, it is not time efficient.\
\
The only reason why I would make that detour daily to complete this quest would be if I was really in a hurry to do the netherwing rep grind.",
    "110861015381101015382007/06/09 19:29:30Vastsomething that may help out, (especially for warriors out there..since this is what I use to do this daily) at roughly coords 8, 43, there is a arch - like structure where roughly 8 to 10 spellbinders are connected to it via their little \"energy-streams\". the arch way runs fairly north to south with the mobs on the east and west side. on the east side, there is a stairway which climbs up onto the platform of the arch (not far off the ground, just a bit). I killed the mobs on the east side, usually hitting one would aggro a second, but not always, until the east side was clear. once it was, i would climb the stairs and hit with ranged one of the mobs on the west side. these ones have to run all the way around to the east and get to the stairs before they would try casting on you. also, they would only aggro one at a time (so far that i have encountered). killing the mobs here gets you away from the patrolling elites, which means less ghost walks. (yes, trial and error meant i have done too many ghost walks here already). i hope this helps someone out there...it is one of the more frustrating daily quests for myself, mainly because of the elite pats.",
    "1108610153941988872007/06/09 19:33:12Vastconfirmed. Beliandra is correct. it may take some exploring to find out how to return to your corpse, just start by going north from the graveyard before moving west. I've made the spirit walk quite a few times now there sadly...",
