  ["Bomb Them Again!70"] = {
    "1102370npcSky Sergeant Vanderlip23120npcSky Sergeant Vanderlip23120Ogri'la500Sha'tari Skyguard500111010111102211023",
    "11023104178111041292007/06/14 09:00:43SangriliaOf course, my method requires that you have an epic flying mount already, I have not tried it with non-epic mounts.",
    "11023150948301509482007/09/09 17:03:45VeshianthApparently I'm terrible at flying so this quest frustrated me to no end. I blew up two stacks and died so often I had a 13 gold repair bill. So I had to come up with a solution. This is what I did.\
\
I put my regular Flying Mount on hotkey #3\
and my Syguard Bombs on hotkey #4\
\
I'd run to the marker, hit #3 just long enough to target, #4 to toss the bomb, and #3 again to dismount.\
\
More often than not, the cannons don't even fire at me. But with this tactic I do all 15 in less time than it takes to wrangle the Aether Rays, and only cost myself around 10 silver in repairs. Sure it's a little cheap and not how the quest was designed to be completed... but it works.",
    "11023157130201571302007/09/23 11:47:56RainfallLooks like the bombs have been hotfixed - their range became significantly larger. But cannons' rate of fire has been increased too.",
    "1102388322130883222007/05/23 10:36:40NahazThis is a \"once per day\" quest. You are only allowed 10 different of these types to be completed each day.\
\
To see when it's a new day, hover the mouse over the \"Daily: X/10\" that's located on the upper right part of your questlog. X is the amount of dialy quests you have completed the current day.",
    "1102319697021925412007/12/06 14:19:28KnoxpwnsFor those who do not have an epic flyer, I highly suggest you do this quest with any durability items places in your bags.\
\
It isn't extremely difficult to dodge them, but there normally is a time they will catch you, and often times for me it has been flying up and out of their fire after bombing ammo.\
\
For example at my luck of this quest, I am over halfway to exulted with Skyguard, and there hasn't been a time I have done this quest w/o at least dying once.\
\
In conclusion, better safe then sorry. go naked.",
    "110238966520896652007/05/24 15:39:58cptmurdok+500 Sha'tari Skyguard reputation\
+500 Ogri'la reputation",
    "11023126083201260832007/07/24 14:49:03MetroshicaJust you you guys know, cloak of shadows remove the Fel Flak Fire debuff. Couple that with light fall damage and vanish if you fall into mobs, and this makes this quest much easier to do for rogues.",
    "11023121622111041292007/07/16 12:46:53iiisamiiiTake your armor off before you do this quest. You WILL get shot down at some point. I'm using a 60% flying mount. Speedy flyers probably have it much easier.\
\
My favorite tactic is dive bombing. Fly high and choose a target. Dive down, almost right on top of the target, ready to drop the bomb as soon as you're in range. Dodge flack with q and e. Usually if you aim a little to the right or left of the target initially, the gun will fire a burst just before you're in range, then simply strafe towards the target, dodging the flack. \
\
Once you drop the bomb turn around (I use the mouse) and fly straight up. Use the left button to orient the camera down so you can see the guns firing behind you. Again use q and e to dodge flack that approaches from behind. Once your bomb is about 50-75% cooled down, turn around and bomb another. \
\
This quest is a 1000 times easier if you have help, or if other people are doing the quest at the same time. The guns will be busy shooting at everyone, not just you. Also, the targets respawn after 10-15s, so even with several people in the area, it's easy to knock it out quickly.",
    "11023103963501039632007/06/13 23:15:29GhosteThe cannons fire in pulses of three, then they rest for a few seconds. So get sort of close to a target, strafe to dodge the three shots, then drop the bombs on the target during the cannon's cooldown.  Finally, fly away while it's firing the next group of three.  Make sure you're only in range of one cannon at a time, if possible.",
    "11023105487201054872007/06/16 13:54:13PowaqqatsiFly low.   Flying high doesnt really make it any easier to dodge, and when you fall you will take way more damage.\
\
If you are near the ground, getting shot down wont hurt much.",
    "11023138690101386902007/08/16 03:10:24clarkeyboyOk guide for people [b]WITH[/b] an Epic Flying Mount (Might work without, never tried it):\
\
Fly in at about the height of the demons heads so you dont aggro the dragon above, then go right up to just so you can see the cannons arrows. Have your bombs in your hotbar ready and swoop down on top of one. Hit your bomb as soon as it comes into range then immediately fly back up (Holding jump button). Doing it this way I have not once gotten hit in the past 15 days of dailys.\
\
Good Luck all, and be proud to be a trainee Skyguard!",
    "11023119040201190402007/07/11 11:11:56Vendor12With this quest i get really high up in the sky then dive and when i was just in range of bombing distance i would drop the  bomb then space bar out of dive and fly off.",
    "11023190492201904922007/11/24 15:45:12CleodoraWhile it may seem like force of habit to WAIT for the \"throw bomb\" cast bar to fill up while hovering in the same spot, you do not need to. The moment you click your target, the bomb will throw itself on your chosen target even if you take off at full speed right after you click.",
    "11023104129301041292007/06/14 07:27:26SangriliaThis quest is easy as long as you keep the flak cannons confused. I read the comments for this quest, and was prepared for some difficult stunt flying, but it's easier than you think.\
\
First of all, make sure that you first check out the camp and pick your target from the distance. When you picked a target, you can bee-line towards it. You might think it is dangerous, but I did it even with cannon piles flanked by two cannons, and I was never hit. IMPORTANT: make sure you fly towards a spot on the ground on the line between you and the cannon pile, and occasionally press the 'space' button, to do a short climb. This will confuse the guns. If you pick targets at the edge of the camp, chances are the flaks won't fire before you dropped the bomb.\
\
With this method you can use the mouse to move the targeting mark on the ground, and left click to release the bomb. You fly towards the target pressing 'W', and press 'space' occasionally. When you are close enough, the marker is green and it is on a cannon ball pile, press the left mouse button, and IMMEDIATELY turn around, and start climbing, or simply fly erratically. Keep flying erratically while you are moving away to prepare for the next run.\
\
I used this method during my bombing runs, and never got hit. It may or may not work for you, but if you have not already picked a method that works for you, you might consider trying it.\
\
I even tried it on targets inside the camp, and managed to destroy them without getting a single hit.",
    "110239254150925412007/05/28 14:41:50DarkharmonyI'm sure most people have found their own way to do this quest and for those without a epic mount I have found that coming in from the left side of Camp Wrath to be the easiest. Coming in from the left side usually only has one or maybe two cannons shooting at you. \
\
This is usually how I have done this quest. Prior to your approach line up and then click the bomb. On your approach if you hit the space bar to move up and also your q and e it tends to confuse the cannons and you should be able to get in without getting hit. What I mean by confuse is that this way the cannons won't fire all at one spot so you should have less chance of being hit. As soon as you click to drop the bomb immediately turn swing around and fly back to the side. Don't forget to continue confusing the cannon on your way out. \
\
Then just find another one and rinse repeat. Once you get the hang of it you shouldn't have any problem with getting hit. It took me a little while to find what worked best for me. So I hope someone finds this information useful.",
    "110239897110989712007/06/05 21:03:53KurimuJust do circles (press E or Q and adjust with D and A respectively) and click the bombs on the stacks when your cooldown's up.  The cannons only hit you when you're still, so move constantly, and you'll be OK.\
\
This is coming from an epic mount perspective.",
    "11023126951201269512007/07/26 02:58:35DrelfThis might work for a non epic mount, but my tip works exceptionally well for those with an epic.\
\
PROBLEM 1: Continually knocked off mount when trying to bomb\
SOLUTION: Attack vertically instead of horizontally\
\
PROBLEM 2: Hard to aim as you get closer to target\
SOLUTION: Attack vertically and the target doesn't move\
\
METHOD:\
\
SETTING UP\
1. Get as high a possible\
2. Bind the bomb to a key you can use easily\
3. Change window settings so that you can see objects as far away as possible\
4. Zoom using mouse roller so that you're in first person mode (i.e. can't see mount)\
5. With this method, you should always be facing directly downwards.\
\
BOMBING:\
The whole run will be done in one motion - NO STOPPING. This constant motion ensures you don't get hit.\
1. Hold down right mouse button and face directly down (you should be up as high as possible to start with)\
2. Ensure during the bomb you don't press left mount button and stop\
3. Press Num Lock - you should be heading directly down towards the target\
4. Hold right mount button and move slightly to adjust yourself towards the target\
5. Press bound key for bomb and highlight target - it should be red because you're not close enough\
6. When green, drop bomb and immediately press space bar - you should be shooting straight back up into air\
\
Okay - bomb successful..... keep on going up, but as you do keep an eye on the next target and also keep an eye on cool down\
\
7. When cool down is roughly 4-5 seconds, release space bar - you should be heading down again\
8. Using Right mouse button and mouse movement you should be able to slightly adjust to next target\
9. Repeat from point 5 above\
\
In a neat little addition to this, I get my party members to hop on their land mounts (they don't get hit if on land mounts) and scout around targets. I use adjust slightly towards them as I continue to monitor mini map and their dots. This way I can bomb quickly, and everyone gets credit.\
\
This method is similar to bobbing for apples. Just an up and down motion - very easy.",
    "110239803850980382007/06/04 12:37:39windrunnerIf you want to have some real fun, just dive bomb them like you see in the movies. \
\
Pick your target and dive in anywhere at about a 45* angle, release the bomb when in range, do 90* upwards and then circle back out of range. No dodging back forth upward etc, just that simple pattern and once you get it pat down, you'll not only have a 100% success rate ... you'll feel like you're on an honest to goodness dive bombing mission.\
\
Mind you, this is using an epic with a riding crop. Not sure if it works with any less.",
    "11023127211301272112007/07/26 14:34:42FeyeI'm not really sure why people think this is hard with a non-epic mount. The cannons fire in front of you based on your current velocity. Therefore, every time you see a cannon fire, change your direction and you'll be fine. You have 3 dimensions to work with, which makes it very easy. I have a 100% success rate with a non-epic mount just using this strategy.",
    "11023212646102126462008/01/04 06:46:22AhNoxLOL. I did the mount-bomb-dismount method too on the 1st quest. Although it is somewhat funny to conduct 'land' bombings, it's not really viable in the long run, for obvious reasons. I found doing windrunner's method (i.e the 'dive-bombing action movie method) most effective for me. FYI, I'm doing this on my trust [Blue Windrider] so it should be effective for most people. Naturally a sizable amount of strafing is involved as well. Listening to the sounds of the fel cannons firing then abruptly changing direction is my method, and although I've been shot down a couple of times by cannons behind me, I haven't died just yet.",
    "11023156403111509482007/09/21 22:14:06SlimdaThis tip is by -far- the easiest solution to bombing the targets. Really! You just run up to a stack (might want to clear some mobs or not, your choice). Mount up, throw, dismount. If you're quick, no shots at you. :)\
\
Sweet!",
    "11023128125101281252007/07/28 07:00:08thevenomThis is kind of interesting for prot warriors:\
\
As a prot warrior I love these quests since farming is annoying. However, on this quest I get shot down and lose a lot of HP. When you get shot down, the dot ticks for a percentage of your hp- I have over 15k unbuffed.\
\
When I get shot down, that's a lot of eating. The dot ticks for about 850. I found myself spending a LOT of time eating on this quest.\
\
Then I got naked and the dot ticks for 250. If I get shot down, I get back on my mount and my low spirit can handle that, or eating is very fast.\
\
So my suggestion is to get naked, and watch where you are flying so you don't get knocked into mobs- and if you do, I hope intimidating shout is up!\
\
OR, another suggestion is you can bind your bomb and mount keys, and quickly mount, bomb, and dismount. After some practice they won't even shoot at you. You just have to be quick about it.",
    "11023103248201032482007/06/12 18:05:15kjpodsiaThe one thing you need to avoid doing on this mission is to use the same path to escape the target as you did to approach it.  Specifically, this means, do not use down (X) to attack the target if you're going to use up (space) to escape.  If you do, you risk getting nailed while ascending by flak aimed at your descent path.\
\
A better approach is one like windrunner suggests above.  Aim the camera at your target and use forward (W) to dive/approach.  Then you can use up (space) to escape and stand a much better chance of avoiding the flak.\
\
Note that you can fly high enough to get out of cannon range without worrying about the dragons -- they don't patrol the forge camps.  So fly high between runs and plot the next attack trajectory at your leisure.",
    "11023128841101288412007/07/29 19:01:33patrykThis quest is most easy with epic mount or epic flying form. Druids can put on Charm of Swift Flight (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32481) too, it will make this quest a piece of cake for them :)\
\
You just need to hang over the spot you want to bomb, then dive in quickly, drop the bomb and then fly high up before cannons can even fire. Then just wait for bomb cooldown to fade (no worries, you're in a safe place ;) and dive in again!\
\
Free money :D",
    "11023128517101285172007/07/29 03:59:39TamyrliandThe easy way i found how to do it was hit the Num lock key, so your character will continue moving without you holding the arrow key. Then do a hit and run strategy. By clicking on the target and suddenly break away and head to the spiked mountains so the canons will hit the spikes instead of you.",
    "11023186828101868282007/11/18 05:33:23TubeyI've managed - repeatedly - to hit all 15 without being dismounted. Here's the trick.\
\
1) Fly low and directly at your targeted cannons.\
\
2) Have the bomb clicked and hold the mouse over the cannons as you dive in.\
\
3) As soon as it becomes green, click to release bomb.\
\
4) As soon as you've clicked, veer left or right immediately - do not wait for the bomb to be thrown.\
\
5) Fly in the new direction for 2-3 seconds then veer away again.\
\
\
Doing this, you can complete this quest in less than 5 minutes. In general, you should do the Ogri'la dailies as follows.\
\
1) Crystal game (to get increased speed)\
\
2) Aether Ray round-up\
\
3) Bomb on flying mount.\
\
4) Banish demons on normal mount - if you're on your flying mount, even on the ground, the cannons may target you.",
    "11023162816101628162007/10/04 11:24:21CampyDo the Relic's Emanation quest first to get a speed increase, which makes this slightly easier.",
    "11023170351211553232007/10/17 10:42:01Mornayoh come on, Ride of the Valkyries is clearly the music of choice for this",
    "11023192733101927332007/11/28 11:12:37Soldonoi cant seem to get the hand of this quest, i keep getting shot down yet im trying to follow the tips from the comments before me",
    "11023198474101984742007/12/09 11:04:45SeiyukiMages...don't forget you have blink, slowfall, fire ward and mana shield. This quest is so much easier when using them, even with a nonepic. When you get hit, use a standard blink before you hit the ground, then hit both fire ward/mana shield (the fire ward is used up first, then the mana shield so the leftover DoT doesn't hurt your health) and keep bombing. Eventually you have to stop for a mana break, but at least you won't die. :D",
