    "976317067npcWatcher Jhang17884npcWatcher Jhang1788419000Cenarion Expedition500",
    "976325588320255882007/01/27 09:13:22PjolterDid this quest, not very hard if you bring along skilled players.\
\
Kalithresh hits your tank fast and hard, you will need a skilled healer. He is surrounded by aqauriums or small tanks with water, which he starts to draw energy from, one at the time.\
\
You need to destroy the aqaurium as fast as possible once he started to draw energy from it, nuke with everything youve got.\
\
If you fail to destroy the tank, Kalithresh will get doubled attack power and attack speed, and the fight will be uncontrollable.",
    "976353339131255882007/03/18 19:16:33decker12Quick recap of the strategy posted above:\
\
Have tank pull him towards one of the aquariums, and fight him there. The boss will soon start a channel spell on the aquarium, which will transform into a yellow \"mob\" so you can attack it.\
\
Have EVERYONE start DPS'ing down the aquarium, healer included. The boss will still be smacking away at the tank, but if everyone doesn't immediately stop what they were casting/doing and start knocking down that aquarium, it's most likely a wipe because of the buff that the boss gets. With good focus fire you should be able to \"kill\" the aquarium with 1 or 2 seconds left on Kalithresh's channel spell.\
\
After 1 Aquarium is down, the tank moves the boss to the next aquarium, guaranteeing that when it's channel time, he'll channel on the nearest aquarium so the group doesn't have to chase him around the room. Repeat until the boss is dead - it should take a decent group 3 or 4 aquariums worth.\
\
Again it's imperative that everyone stops what they're doing when the channel starts, tank and healer included, and immediately begin DPS'ing the aquariums.",
    "9763111821201118212007/06/27 11:40:49contentiousAs a note, his enrage buff stacks. We tried to heal through it and did fine till he sucked up another tank",
