    "108168677610867762007/05/21 10:29:19ChandriallaIf you have a flying mount, a good place to start is 72, 39. It's in a corner where you won't draw aggro. If you don't mind being patient, you can start to take down darkweavers, chosens, and slayers, making sure to head back to the corner where you started once the elite starts coming back.",
    "10816164788101647882007/10/08 15:15:31NaenthosDidn't find this quest as annoying as others apparently do. If you want to solo this keep in mind the following:\
\
-Use flight form or a flying mount to look for a nice starting spot. Stealth shouldn't be necessary if you find a good spot or two (I think).\
\
-All the single groups (single Darkweavers, Chosen, pairs of Slayers) are very much soloable at level 70. The elites are probably not.\
\
-Darkweavers: They run. Slow them, trap them or kill them quickly.. that and/or kill surrounding mobs first to give a bit of space.\
\
-Chosen: Beware for patrolling Chosen. They are much nastier than Slayers. They have a pushback, so make sure you don't get pushed over a ledge.\
\
-Slayers: Can be pulled solo if you pull ranged (not necessary in most situations and may not be desirable.. because..).\
\
-Respawn rate is fairly high for the time needed, given all the patrols and such. That also means you can just look for a few spots close together and go between those.\
\
-Drakonids/Eyes: Drakonids are probably best avoided. Make sure you learn where they patrol and how long they take. Eyes are much less of an issue as they have low hit points, but best kill them (for me a single starfire does the trick) if you can do so without much trouble.",
    "108166963610696362007/04/19 13:25:23sickcatLame...I did NOT have my pet out, and they still evaded at 40%...very frustrating.  I was able to kill the 4 darkweavers needed, but what a waste of time for the rest of it.",
    "1081610569631641262007/06/16 22:43:40FinsternisI strongly second this!  This has to be the #1 most annoying quest I've ever had.  It's even worse than the nearby \"Tablets of Baa'ri\", which was bad enough.   The mobs are extremely close together, there are practically no safe spots, the patrolling unkillable (solo) elite 70's are everywhere, and worst of all your super mighty uber 70 character with 9,000 in all your stats.... can't climb over the 1-foot-high wall on each level to try to escape.   Everytime you turn around there's another mob bearing down on you, or an elite patrol. \
\
This quest isn't part of a necessary chain and I can pretty much guarantee that your repair and potion bills will cost *far* more than the rewards.  If you feel you *must* do it, bring a couple friends.\
\
ABANDON THIS QUEST, IT ISN'T WORTH IT.",
    "10816102936101029362007/06/12 07:50:03getter2007If do not have a flying mount, forget about this quest, too many pats and wandering elites...unless you have a good group with you this quest is going to be a a royal pain. If you do have a flyer it's not too bad though, good for some spare coin ~15g after vendoring.\
