    "10248203249102032492007/12/18 06:37:36siggboySoloable with a hunter.  Here's what I did:\
\
1. Put a freezing (slowing) trap slightly up the road towards Area 52.\
2. Take control of the pet robot, wait for the reaver to appear, target him and spam the bot's slam attack as to grab aggro immediately when the reaver turns hostile.\
3. Run back behind your trap and shoot the reaver.  If you've placed the trap far enough up the road this will despawn your mechanical pet and the reaver will aggro you.\
4. Call your own pet now.  You can use it to temporarily distract the reaver if it gets too close to you/starts hitting you.  It will also allow you to feign death once without having the reaver reset.  He will pwn your pet quickly but it allows you to get some distance.\
5. Run towards Area 52, lay a second freezing trap along the way.  Sometimes the reaver will not even trigger the trap because he's ran past it before the 2 second trap delay is over.  Make sure you keep aggro on the reaver (shooting him once with Arcane Shot was enough in my case).\
6. Shortly before I entered Area 52 I had to pop a health potion as not to die.  Your mileage may vary.\
7. If you get the Area 52 guards to aggro the reaver you're pretty much sorted.  If you die your ghost will spawn directly in front of the town gates, just run back in and res.  The reaver will still be there, fighting the guards.  Keep assisting them.  As has been correctly mentioned above, the goblin \"guards\" (Netherstorm Agents) will not help you, but the two elite ogres in front of the Arena vendor building will.  So make sure you get the reaver into their aggro range.  Feign Death as soon as you see them aggroing the reaver.\
\
Optionally you can use speed buffing measures (nifty stopwatch, swiftness potion, even cheetah aspect), your mileage may vary here.  If the freezing traps trigger and you use your pet/FD ability smartly it is possible to get to Area 52 without any speed boosts, however.\
\
The reaver killed at least two guards, and two players who jumped in to help.  All in all, it was pretty priceless to watch him cause havoc in the town while shooting him from behind.\
\
Highly recommended ;-).",
