    "102486179160617912007/04/03 23:32:59ToridasI just found out that you cannot just let the robot solo the whole time due to some time limit.  Damage must be done to Negatron by you or another player on this quest. I'm a holy priest; I tried to solo heal the pet while it tanked. I was only healing and doing no damage myself. It was working fine until Negatron got down to about 15% then my pet despawned, leaving me as the only target. I didn't last long. After another try with the same result I was forced to find a group to finish the quest.",
    "102484520480452042007/03/02 15:23:31SoymeatzA tip for hunters wanting to solo this, if you get charged at any time during the attempt you will want to reset it because from then on Negatron will always try to be within melee range of you even if you did not aggro him. To avoid this, I used Smash first thing to get aggro on the robot, then ran away to approximately 30 yards and started firing away. I kept Hunters Mark and Scorpid Sting up the entire fight. I also used Misdirection + Distracting Shot onto the felreaver pet to make sure I never pulled aggro. Between 30-35 yards away is the \"Sweet spot\" where Negatron will not charge you and you will be unaffected by the earthquake. By the way, try not to go out of 35 yard range because everytime I did that the pet despawned and Negatron came after me. Good luck.",
