BTW, this boss is a mini Doomwalker. He has the same earthquake and charge abilities that Doomwalker has, but has a mortal strike instead of sunder armor. Have fun.",
    "10248204060112032492007/12/19 16:55:23shuddertrixFreezing trap or Frost Trap?",
    "10248205281102052812007/12/21 21:08:38xerentI just soloed this today as a lvl 70 Warlock, after 5 tries.\
\
Blue Equipment, with Frozen Shadoweave set on. Affliction Spec\
\
As the fight starts, Negatron immediately aggros your pet. I opened with a Smash, and kept repeating Smash as often as the cooldowns let me.\
\
Smash has a 10 Second cooldown.\
\
I popped Immolate, Unstable Affliction, Curse of Agony, Corruption, and Siphon Life. ~9.5 seconds worth of spells.\
\
Then I went onto to Heal my pet the way that warlocks do, which is a 10 second channel. I popped Smash as soon as the Heal started, and again after it ended.\
\
Rinse and Repeat. Usually I wait until my DoT's have run thier course before I re-cast. With the Exception of Siphon Life, I didn't bother this fight. You're going to be almost constantly channeling health into your pet, so you don't want to interrupt your cast to reapply dots. Negatron WILL eventually win via attrition this way, so you have to do as much fast damage as you can.\
\
An additional note. You should always keep your pet in between you and Negatron. The reason for this is your pet healing spell has a low range in comparison to everything else. If you are too close to Negatron trying to heal your pet, you will get interrupted with the Earthquake spell that occurs, and be stunned for several seconds. \
\
It was a very close fight, with my pet on its last sliver of health before Negatron finally bit it.",
