jef3189's write-up is an excellent guide, so rather than rehash that, I will note some things that helped our group finally down the Raven God.\
\
-According to our warrior, the cyclone spell is *NOT* pummelable, so don't count on that to stop it.\
\
-For the druid doing statue duty, it is highly recommended to create three macros that will automatically target and cast either Rejuvenation(Rank 1) or Regrowth(Rank 1) on them. This will eliminate the need to find the statues amongst the chaos, and your spells if not hot-keyed. The statues are named Hawk Spirit, Falcon Spirit, and Eagle Spirit. For example:\
\
/target Hawk Spirit\
/cast Rejuvenation(Rank 1)\
\
-Spell Bomb will ruin your day if you're not paying attention. For the druid spamming statues, it's extremely easy to get hit multiple times before you realize what's happening. The effect only applies when the spell lands, however, so spells with longer cast times can be timed to land just after the debuff fades.\
\
-This one may be obvious, but a cycloned target is immune to everything. Don't bother to heal or innervate someone in a cyclone, for example. This could be very easy to miss if you have debuff filtering enabled.\
\
We fought Anzu in the room where you summon him, and so had to deal with the adds as well. It was a hectic fight, but once we had our strategy down, no one died. The guild members were all on Ventrilo, the warlock was not. However, with a little practice, Anzu should be a fairly straight-forward encounter. He dropped http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32779 for us.\
\
The fight was frustrating, but can be fun once you work the kinks out. The spells and bird adds, while inconvenient, are not make-or-break unless you have a string of bad luck, so even groups with a less than \"optimal\" makeup should give it a go.",
