    "11001144592101445922007/08/27 01:09:22FroRevYou really need a druid on statue duty in addition to a main healer. The fight was too difficult for our resto druid to solo-heal, so I (a feral druid) put on my healing gear and played as a secondary healer. Keeping HoTs on the statues was my priority, and throwing occasional HoTs and decurses on party members was secondary. We had a warrior tank and two frost mages. The fight can be rather long, and I chugged at least three Major Combat Mana Potions (I gave my Innervate to the main healer).",
    "1100188753480887532007/05/23 18:32:34jef3189This is a fairly difficult boss in my opinion and here is a good setup for the boss:\
\
Raid Composition:\
----------------------------\
-AOE class, preferably a mage (for counterspell on the cyclone)\
-A resto druid to OFF heal (so that he can keep up the mini statues, explained in a sec)\
-A priest to main heal (for shackles throughout the instance)\
-A tank (either a feral druid/warrior)\
-A Marks hunter (for silencing shot to interrupt his cycone)/ Rogue to kick\
-----------------------------\
\
Boss Abilities:\
----------------------------\
Charge - He randomly charges a party member for about 1k\
Spell Bomb - He will put spell bomb on a caster in the raid. If the caster does a damage or healing spell, it will cost them 1k life and 2k mana, knocking them back.\
Cyclone - (INTERRUPTABLE) He will cyclone a party member for 8-10 seconds. (Curse of tongues may help, this is sort of like shadow power/charged fist in heroic mech and should be interrupted as often as possible)\
Paralyzing Screech - AOE Stun that will stun everyone for 5 seconds, this is what wiped us half of the time. Be SURE the tank has full hitpoints before the screech, which you will see him casting. This ability is similar to \"time lapse\" for chromaggus, and the tank needs to be topped off before this so he can survive until the healer comes out of stun.\
\
Finally, @ around 66% and 33% he will \"banish\" himself becoming immune to everything and about 10 birds will swoop in and circle the party. This is where a mage comes in very handy for frost nova. They will move around constantly, and each bird has near 12k hitpoints, so freezing them in place will help with AOEing them down. BE SURE you kill them as soon as possible because after about 1 minute the boss will come out of his \"banished\" form and continue his attacking the party.\
\
**There are three statues of birds around the room that will come alive when activated by a druid's \"Heal Over Time\" (HoT). Usually you will need a druid backup healing anyway, so have him keep these birds up by using RANK 1 Rejuvenation and  RANK 1 Regrowth.\
\
General Strategy:\
------------------------\
You MUST have a two healers for this fight, it's nearly impossible to do this without a backup healer mainly because if the main healer is cycloned or spell bombed, the off healer (usually the druid keeping up the statues of the birds) needs to pick up heals on the tank. \
\
Have your rogue/mage/hunter/shaman (if he is on DPS) interrupt the cyclones as often as possible. A cyclones healer and spell bombed off healer in combination with paralyzing screech is a most definite wipe situation.\
\
It take a lot of coordination, and would not recommend \"Pugging\" , unless you have everyone on comms or unless they know exactly what to do. \
\
**Note you need to clear the ENTIRE room before attempting the boss.\
\
If I missed anything make sure you post it below. Good luck druids.\
--FYI you can as of 5/21/07 pick HERBS in epic flight form.",
