    "10255180210111785162007/11/06 18:18:39InfernoManSlight correction to above post, it is a bit misleading:\
\
Yes, as a feral druid your weapon skill does not increase while in bear or kitty form, but there is a reason for that.  It doesn't have to.  As a feral druid there is no reason to level up your 2h mace skill (or staff skill if that is your weapon of choice), except boredom,  because it has no reflection on your hit rating or anything else while shape-shifted (see http://www.wowwiki.com/Druid  [b]\"Weapon skill with the equipped weapon has no effect. Instead, the natural weapons always have the maximum weapon skill for their level. Natural weapon skill can be increased through the feral combat skill, as seen on the Earthwarden\"[/b]) .  When you shift into bear or kitty form as a druid, you gain what is known as feral combat skill, which is always maxed out for your level, and the only benefit that you get from a weapon is the stats that are on it.  +weapon damage enchants (i.e Striking) or chance to proc enchants (i.e. Firey, Icy, mongoose etc) do nothing for you.  Hope this helps out the above poster and anyone else considering a feral druid.  \
\
If you would like my opinion, go with Agamaggan's Quill  http://www.wowhead.com/?item=29911 which is from a very easy quest when you first get to Outlands, or go through Hellfire Ramparts repeatedly to get Ursol's Claw (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=24155)  Either one will take you several levels till you can get \"Staff of Beasts\" (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=25761) from a quest chain in Nagrand called \"The Ring Of Blood\" at 65.  Again, hope this helps out and have fun",
