  ["Destroy Naberius!69"] = {
    "1032016967npcCustodian Dieworth19488npcCustodian Dieworth1948815400110184210312310316410314510319610320",
    "10320205810102058102007/12/22 23:20:10AlerielEasily soloed as an affliction lock by clearing the ghosts, applying dots, and running around the chapel to LOS out of the frostbolt.",
    "103203787331345602007/02/18 02:05:14LucidThis strategy does work, even for melee classes, albeit quite tricky and potentially troublesome.\
\
For melee classes : \
Kill his adds (they weren't linked to boss when I tried) with a ranged pull.\
\
Then ranged aggro Naberius. Stand in his light of sight until he casts his frost bolt, then immediately step out of line of sight. He will cancel and come to the door. Move back in his line of sight, but put a few yards between him and you.\
\
He will again try to cast his frostbolt, get a few hits in, run through him, into the church, and duck behind the wall before it finishes casting.\
\
This method surely is a pain in the arse, but with a little timing, you can solo this guy for an extremely awesome quest reward.",
    "1032037473120374732007/02/17 10:57:08ozgulNaberius seems to have 21-22k health (and 10k mana), his frostbolts hit around 500-600 and the Shadow Fissure (red rune under your feet) seems to hit static 1k shadow damage (900 in def stance with warrior). He also seems to have some sort of Frost Nova (Chill Nova hits you for 581) and melees for about 550.",
    "1032026518120265182007/01/28 16:49:58FugaziOnly dangerous things he does are red portals. Its small aoe 1000 damage per tick. Avoid that and nuke him down before he nuke you with his frostbolts :p",
    "1032020991111345602007/12/30 13:38:15eyanaI used a similar method after reading your strategy and not finding anyone to help in the area.\
\
Soloed as a level 69 Discipline and Holy Priestess. Make sure you are ready to dispel if you get hit by a frost bolt. I mostly just ran around and kept Shadow Word: Pain on him and managed to get a couple of smites in there every so often.\
\
I did have a ghost join in, but I kept it shackled. Definitely clear the area around the building beforehand.",
    "103205285071345602007/03/17 20:07:08aarughafyi, he is immune to silence",
    "1032022491370224912007/01/21 17:36:57TomedYou can find him in a church at (63,79). This quest is actually very soloable. Inside his room are two Tortued Spirits which can be pulled independently from Naberius. Naberius casts Frostbolt so it's very easy to LoS him. Don't get too close to the edge because he does a knockback. Lastly, stay out of the red portals he summons.",
    "10320212450102124502008/01/03 20:49:34jojodamunkyA 70 Resto Shaman can easily solo Naberius. Here's how I did it:\
\
Step 1: Like several others have mentioned, I cleared out the adds that are in the chapel with him. They didn't link with Naberius.\
\
Step 2: Ate and drank to full hp and mana. Then I entered into the chapel and dropped a mana spring totem and a grounding totem. Then I cast a Lightning bolt on him. While he started casting his frostbolt, I dropped an earth elemental totem.\
\
Step 3: After the grounding totem absorbed the frostbolt, I cast Earth Shield on the Elemental and then dropped a Wrath of Air totem (the one that gives you extra spell damage). \
\
Step 4: From here on it was incredibly simple; the Earth Elemental was an excellent tank. Dropped a searing totem and just took him down. I took him down by throwing flame shock on him and then shooting lightning bolt after lightning bolt at him. Don't think I ever even needed to heal my elemental but make sure it doesn't die. \
\
I believe at the end of the fight my elemental had more than 90% hp and I didn't lose any. For all those shaman who didn't know (not many of you, but their may be a few), the Earth Elemental you get at level 66 is excellent for \"soloing\" those 2-3 man group quests. Although I probably could have tanked him myself by throwing up Earth Shield on myself and then using melee, shocks, and fire totems to take him down, why do extra work when you don't have to?",
    "103202590810259082007/01/27 18:19:14GlassjawDefinately soloable, just did this as a 68 hunter with ~7k HP.  Sent pet in, and just dps as hard as I could.  FD to bandage or just pop a super HP pot.",
    "10320101884101018842007/06/10 12:32:37ixonAffliction locks can just throw all dots and run around the building. Stop to occasionally reapply, just make sure you cleared around the church for easier kiting.",
    "10320205995102059952007/12/23 10:53:22NeonisisEasy for 70 Shaman.\
\
Pop Grounding Totem as often as possible, just Stormstrike and Earthshock the rest.\
\
\
Btw, he didn't do that Shadow Fissure inside the building.. Coincidence?",
    "10320155844201558442007/09/20 19:17:48SlimdaAt first I tried that \"LoS\"-thing, but found out, after two almost-deaths (Flight form really helps when falling off the edge), that that wasn't possible.\
\
So... I cleared the churched and outside the entrance, I /cursed the Lich, shifted into kitten and snuck up. I dealt some swift blows, granting me five combo-points, gave him a Ferocious Bite, popped into Bear and spanked away. I had to jump in a circle every now and then 'cause he spawned those portals of his. Works like tanking the dragon in Ramparts, actually. Just move out of the \"zone\". Anyway, halfway through I was low on health, popped out of bear right after a frost-bot, chucked up a Regrowth, on with Barkskin and up with Healing Touch. After that, I had full health and a nice HoT. Back into bear and kill the thing. Easy tank'n'spank, really!\
\
Summary: Kitten, 5 combo, Bam! Bear, spank, heal, spank, /dance.",
    "1032034560900345602007/02/12 08:18:09ParynI was able to solo this with very minimal support, as a 70 shadow priest. There was a friendly tauren druid who would cast moonfire or starfire on Naberius, but that was towards the end of the fight.\
\
Here is a synopsis of the strategy I used:\
\
Naberius: \"Grr, I'm going to cast frostbolt on you\"\
Player: \"I'm going to duck around the corner.\"\
Naberius: \"Gosh I can't see you anymore. Let me run after you.\"\
Player: \"I came back out from the corner!\"\
Naberius: \"Grr, let me cast frostbolt on you again.\"\
\
Here is the strategy I used in more detail:\
\
Clear the area surrounding the church of any ghosts. Then clear the inside of the chapel of the two stationary ghosts. Like people have mentioned in previous comments, Naberius will use frostbot as a primary attack. He needs a few seconds to cast this, of course. So what you do, is mindflay or renew any dots you want to use while he is casting, then quickly move out of line of sight from the frostbolt. This will cause him to stop casting, and move after you. Once he does this, move back out into his line of sight. He will again try to frostbolt you. Mindflay, or wand, whichever you prefer. Then before he finishes casting, move out again. \
\
I used the chapel as a means to escape line of sight from Naberius by moving around corners just as he was finishing frostbolt. \
\
Oh, and if you see the red diagram under your feet, move out of the way. \
\
You could probably solo this as a lower level shadow priest. The strength is in the strategy and execution.",
    "1032040698130406982007/02/22 17:52:47zhekIf you choose not to solo, be warned he can mind control one player. The debuff isn't typed, so not dispellable.",
    "10320151778301517782007/09/11 18:05:50BKRhobLittle trick, as a warrior use Spell Reflect standing on the hole that deals 1k dmg/sec and you'll reflect huge damage to him. Soloed it that way, hope it helps :]",
    "103202965350296532007/02/02 19:36:44annickImmune to gouge, kidney shot, blind, cheap shot, rupture, garrote.\
\
Places the red circles on the ground under you that instantly hit you for 1000 damage then tick for more if you stay in them. Doable as a 69 combat sword rogue, but based on luck. If you get bad crit streak you'll die.",
