    "105146998841566992007/04/20 07:54:48AxehiltFarmbuyer's post is just outright incorrect info:\
\
* Line of sight didn't prevent a pig from digging a mound for me. Then again, hills don't normally block line of sight anyway (ie you can cast spells through terrain most of the time.)\
\
* Flayers don't have \"gigantic aggro radius\". They have normal aggro behavior. This means they have the normal radius for targets their level, and an increased radius against targets lower than them. As a level 70 mob this means they have a pretty high radius against the level 65 pigs, but a normal radius against a level 70 player. They also patrol small distances, which increases the likelihood of aggroing if you're unwary.\
\
Other observations from my 2nd time doing the quest (took ~20 mins like the first time):\
\
* If 3+ flayers are in the area and a pig tries to spawn, it will spawn dead. Dead pigs don't even give you the option of saving them. This is bad. Solve the problem by clearing the area of flayers - then pigs will spawn alive.\
\
* Try to be strategic about which pigs you keep alive. I was able to get 3 tubers in one whistle blow because all 3 pigs were within the radius when I blew it. This is fairly luck-based, but also a result of my keeping those pigs alive in an area where there were tubers. (which really sums up the whole quest: keep pigs alive in an area where there are tubers.)",
    "1051426528410265282007/01/28 17:08:15bootableIn order to loot a Shadowmoon Tuber you first have to find a Shadowmoon Tuber Mound, a tooltip will pop up when you hover over it, then you have to use Oronok's Boar Whistle when a boar is nearby and the boar will come dig up the tuber, then a lootable Shadowmoon Tuber appears and you loot the tuber from that.\
\
The only real difficulty in this is finding a spawn that is near a felboar, and also keeping the felboars alive because the Ravenous Flayers all around the are are constantly killing the boars.\
\
Note: aggroing one of the felboars to make it follow you and then using the whistle while standing on a tuber, Does NOT work, just means you have to kill the felboar, which is pointless.",
