    "1087932132550321322007/02/07 08:35:51TheUzAbout the Encounter:\
It is important to note that you have a limited area in which you are allowed to fight.  If you walk too far from the quest giver you will fail the quest.  This means limited kiting.  I would say you should try to stay within a 20 yard radius of the quest giver.   This is a multiple wave event and you will have 5-10 seconds of rest between each wave.\
\
The Opponents:\
\
There are 4 waves of enemies:\
\
Wave 1:\
2 Birds 1300-1700 health â Melee attacks for 350-700 on 0-1k armor\
Wave 2:\
 2 Birds 1300-1700 health â Melee attacks for 350-700 on 0-1k armor\
Wave 3:\
 3 Birds 1300-1700 health â Melee attacks for 350-700 on 0-1k armor\
Wave 4:\
 1 Bird 10k-12k health â Melee attacks for 1200-2500 on 0-1k armor\
This bird also has a pushback ability with about 2 seconds of cast time.\
The pushback does no damage\
Multiple pushbacks can lead you far enough from the quest giver to fail the quest\
\
My Experience:\
I soloed this quest as an elemental mage at 70.  I would rate the encounter as moderately difficult because of the limited area in which to fight.  Still, I would strongly suggest that this quest be done in a group.\
\
I was able to use all of my crowd control abilities including Polymorph, Blast Wave, Frost Nova, Frost Bolt, and Cone of Cold.  Having cold snap with three ice barriers made a huge difference as well.  I fought him with 6800 health (add 3 ice barriers for nearly 10k).  I did pop a potion mid battle but it turned out to be unnecessary, his attacks while very large were not fast enough to make his DPS as scary as his crits.\
\
I would suggest that any mage who wants to fight him solo open on him with a polymorph to prep a larger damage spell as an opener.\
\
Be prepared that all CC seems to break about 50% quicker on the big bird.  Expect 6-9 seconds on Polymorph, and 5 seconds on Frost Nova.",
    "10879106242501062422007/06/17 23:39:41ZiirSoloed this as a 68 affliction warlock so I didn't have Felguard like the one above me. Took me a few tries but it was easy when I figured it out.\
\
