\
Before the fight, have a healthstone and voidwalker. Yes, I know he sucks but you need him for the shield. Having netherweave bandages are very helpful as well.\
\
On the first wave, send voidwalker to one of the birds and just dot it with corruption and then drain tank the other bird. They die fast so don't bother with UA, just corruption and CoA was enough. The drain tanked one will die fast and just as you are finishing off the other, the next wave should spawn.\
\
Again, same tatics. On this wave, I couldn't kill off the second bird because I wasn't as fast about it as the first time, so when the third wave spawned I have three at full health and one nearly dead.\
\
They hit kinda hard for having such low hp, so I instant HoT the four and the low health one died. Stick corruption on all three and then I feared one, voidwalker on another and drained the last. Voidwalker was nearly dead so I sac'd him.\
\
Then the avatar spawned so I feared him. DC one bird, shadowburn the other and drained the last one down and healthstoned. Feared avatar again and hit it with corruption and bandaged myself to life tap cause I was low on mana. Then from there on it was just simple fear and dot.\
\
It was challenging but it's also a great example of being able to use all of your skills to beat an encounter. As you can kinda tell, I panicked when I had the avatar spawn and three birds coming towards me so I did what I could to burn them down asap.",
