    "111019920410992042007/06/06 05:14:19CarmbasThis entire script takes 6 mintues, easily soloable as any class, as Elastik states, run behind the pillars in the Temple of  Sha'tar and stay there for a min untill the mobs resets.",
    "11101151607111189542007/09/11 09:50:41Shaminoi concur, the guards do not seem to attack now.  however i was still able to solo it as a frost mage.  i died twice.  just hold out long enough and it will complete.",
    "11101103738301037382007/06/13 14:41:35mintyduckManaged to solo this as a frost mage.  As others have mentioned, if you get aggro, run behind the wall by the wyvern/gryphon and you can bandage or whatnot.  If you move back in front of the mob and it multishots, you will have the flightmaster and the gryphons beat it down with no problem.  I kept an ice barrier and a mana shield up at all times.  Don't worry about your mana since you won't be using much of it -- just your health.  As long as you can shoot down about two-three dragonmaw in the little open spot in the wall (by the flight master), you should be just fine.",
    "11101101167201011672007/06/09 04:58:22LetheSoloed as a Protection Warrior.  As was mentioned before, if you have mobs on you, run over to the 70 elite guards and when mobs multishot they'll aggro the guard.  If you can, stay close so that more multishots will keep the guard in combat.  Run back behind the fence to bandage.  If you have aggro on several mobs, they'll stand still behind the wall, unable to shoot because of LoS.  This helps reduce the number of mobs the quest npcs have to deal with until you drop out of combat.  Needed to bandage twice and eat once, as well as use Last Stand and A Potion, but made it through w/o being killed.  Demo and Thunderclap helps as well, though it's hard for melee to effectively kill things when so many mobs refuse to land",
    "11101188881101888812007/11/21 12:29:23RinorJust don't let the commander die by healing him, heal yourself, run out, drink, and keep on doing it until they kill a certain amount of the mobs, and you win. Did it as enhancement shaman with healing gear, 1k healing, 9.5k mana poll so... if you are specced for healing you will also manage to do this alone.",
    "11101107030101070302007/06/19 09:40:44bladeyamaI aggree with Dianora if it wasnt for her/hes instructions i wouldnt have been able to solo this quest.  On ravencrest it is so hard to find groups.  So alot of quest i cant do or try to solo.  Thanks to wowhead.com and the users that post here ive been able to complete many quests.",
