    "11101100643301006432007/06/08 09:03:35DianoraSince I don't see an edit function, here goes my 2nd post on how to solo this as a healer.  When you get aggro, run back towards one of the guards.  Use small heals on yourself and wait until the dragonriders fires multi-shot.  This will aggro guards, who are level 70 elites, and will make short work of the riders.  That or once you're low on mana, go to the inn until you're out of combat to drink.",
    "11101154663101546632007/09/18 11:59:41swotamI soloed this a few times recently on my Hunter so it's certainly possible. It's hit and miss if you'll succeed or fail depending on how many NPC's die before the timer runs out, but if you position yourself near the wall and take down one mob at a time you've got a decent chance of completing it. If not, just wait for the NPC to respawn and start it again. You can run behind the tall wall by the flightmaster to go out of combat and drink/eat, but you will occasionally get mobs who follow you there depending on their position at the time. Also, as mentioned, if you get multi-shotted the guards will usually get hit and run out to take down the mob. I never had to try it more than 3 times to get it done, but I also didn't have a huge amount of control over the lifespan of the NPC's. Inevitably they will die too soon and the quest will fail, other times they'll survive almost to the end, it just depends.\
\
