\
When they're dead it's a simple matter of returning to the questgiver to choose a prize.",
    "10651177890101778902007/11/01 23:01:34v1c1n1tyFor Druids, I'd reccommend taking [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=30933]Hauberk of Karabor[/url] over [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=31009]Wildcaller[/url]. It's easy to get a weapon replacement like [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=30010]Fleshling Simulation Staff[/url] or [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=28325]Dreamer's Dragonstaff[/url]. Even staying with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=25761]Staff of Beasts[/url] for some time won't hurt ya. But Hauberk of Karabor is IMHO the second best pre-raid and pre-heroic chest you can get. It's bested only by [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=33204]Shadowprowler's Chestguard[/url] for which it will take more time and money to grind and you'll either pay a hell of a lot for the Bolts of Soulcloth or be doing Karazhan for the Soul Essences before you get it.",
