    "1102770npcGahk23300npcGahk23300Ogri'la10",
    "11027124466311196172007/07/21 10:37:43kenjim0toalthough it may not seem to have a channeling cast bar, it is infact channeled and if u cast anything else within a few seconds after using aoe heal on first demon, then it will not go off and you will waste a charged crystal focus but it will not consume your cooldown. I know this because i learned it the hard way few days ago and expended 3 charged crystal focuses and saw no response. Hopefully this helps you a lil.",
    "1102794950170949502007/05/31 20:01:07JaygoodieAll the demons have several unique abilities. Due to the lack of time to alt+tab and write down the exact numbers, i will just explain each one.\
\
All demons have the ability to throw a hammer at the teleporter, dealing damage. Once it gets to a certain damage, the next demon will come out.\
\
Demon one: Felguard.\
\
1) Mortal Strike: Heavy single target damage, 1.5 second global cooldown.\
2) Whirlwind: Hits all enemies in a short range about 4 times, usually enough to kill them, if they all stay in range. 20? second cooldown\
3) Charge: Charges a target like a warrior, stunning it for a brief moment. Once the felguard reaches his target he stomps the ground in a green hellfire, dealing strong AoE damage. 20? second cooldown\
4) Howl of Terror: Instant cast, sends all little demons running away for about 6 seconds. Good to use this if your whirlwind is on cooldown. 30 second cooldown.\
5) Special \"Drain Life\": Drains the life of all nearby opponents, healing you dramaticly. CAUTION: This has no noticable graphic, but if you look at your demon's HP, it will go up. Consumes one Charged Crystal Focus.\
\
Enemies in phase 1:\
 In phase one, the teleporter will summon felhounds that do basic melee damage, and imps that shoot fireballs. Charge the imps whenever possible. Felhounds vary in size / stamina, and have more stamina than the imps. \
\
Demon Two: Dreadlord. \
(Note: this one is from memory, I only played it once, but enough.)\
\
1) Mortal Strike (same as above)\
2) Fel Fire: Emits a non-interupted channeled fire spell in a cone directly in front of you. You can rotate to get all enemies around you, but make sure you dont change your spot. Deals decent damage.\
3) Throw Axe: Throws his axe at a ranged target, dealing heavy melee damage. Good finishing move.\
4) Super Jump: Jumps at a ranged target, stunning all demons around you for 4 seconds. Also deals AoE damage. \
5) Drain Life: (name is incorrect) Hits one RANGED Gan'ark minion  for massive damage, healing you at the same time for alot. \
6) Special \"Lift Off\": (name incorrect again) Dreadlord takes off into the air, not taking any damage. Does a slow circle around the teleporter, the entire time raining fireballs down on all enemies below. INCREDIBLY effective, however it consumes a Charged Crystal Focus, and has a 5 minute cooldown. Save it for when the final boss comes out, or for emergencies only.\
\
Enemies in phase 2: \
In phase 2, you will nolonger get imps and felhounds, but you will get Gan'arks which deal weak melee damage. At about 20%, they run away and start to \"construct\" a fel cannon. This is the time to throw your axe, or super jump, or drain life from it, before it builds the cannon. The cannons are similar to a warlock imp; they dont have alot of HP, but can be very annoying.  With the Gan'arks come \"Driller\" demons (dont know the name, but the ones with welding masks/drills on them). These guys do heavier melee damage, have more HP, and do an acid geyser in front of them, much like many others of their kind do. \
\
Phase 3: I did not survive to phase 3. But the demon came out, it is a \"Shiva\" demon, like the ones to the fel area to the north. \
\
I used up 4 charged crystal focus the entire time. first 3 were used on the felguard, and the last was used on the Dreadlord wayyyy too early on in the fight.\
\
More updates to come.",
    "11027101281101995282007/06/09 10:12:25vathainIt's not just if you have the quest - you have to have COMPLETED the Banish More Demons quest on any given day that you want to upgrade a Darkrune.\
\
Here's how you can get screwed over:\
1) You have a Darkrune\
2) You did Banish More Demons on a previous day and got an empty Kronk's Grab Bag\
   * Why is it empty? It has a Darkrune in it, but you can't loot it because it's unique.\
   * Why are you hosed? You can't turn in Banish More Demons because you have a Bag, and you can't upgrade your Darkrune because you haven't done Banish More Demons today. Essentially, you lose a shot at the Shartuul event, which you only get on average once every 4 days (if you do BMD every day).\
\
So here's my advice - if you have a Crystalforged Darkrune and you get another Darkrune, do the event that day and then upgrade your rune.",
    "110279952850995282007/06/06 14:16:53alcarasNote, you can't convert your Darkrune to a Crystalforged Darkrune if you have the Banish the Demons daily quest -- you have to turn in the quest to be able to convert.",
    "11027138457111103752007/08/15 17:04:52FormosaMy second try with these strategies I completed it without any charged crystal focis and I now feel that I can farm this event any time I get a Dark Rune.  Some added hints and tips for the last few bosses (if you're having trouble with the first two you won't be able to do it):\
\
-Try to time going back into shadow after a particularly dangerous move (Dark Glare, Incinerate) and also try to time it for about 5 seconds before Siphon life will wear off so you can death blast then reapply it\
\
-For Shartuul, he has a ton of health but he barely does any damage (your siphon life ticks for 2400 but his shadow bolts hit for 3600-ish).  It's possible to not lose any net health at all on this fight if you play it right.",
    "110271103751401103752007/06/24 13:35:20KalkenI've killed Shartuul a few times now, basically farming him for Depleted items whenever I get a Darkrune.\
Here's my strat for getting to and beating Shartuul without help from other players:\
Before beginning, make sure you have at least 5 Charged Crystal Foci.\
\
Demon 1: Felguard\
Very easy fight, if you use a charged foci on this fight, you might not get past the second phase.  Use your hammer whenever it's up, Mortal Strike Single enemies, and abuse Charge.  Charging nearby enemies causes you to run a very short distance and create an AoE that basically clears the area.  Avoid using Whirlwind and if you get overwhelmed use fear.  When the Doomguard comes out begin this sequence: Mortal Strike, Fear, Charge, Mortal Strike, etc.  Hopefully he goes down easy.\
\
Demon 2: Doomguard\
Kind of an easy fight too if you keep an eye on the little guys.  Basically white damage and kill the fight few little guys, they're no issue.  The little guys are just walking healthstones for your Steal Life ability.  Whenever you see a little bugger run off or channeling any spell use your stuns ASAP or it'll make your life harder.  When the big guys spawn use your Super Jump ability to stun them and get in close.  Once he is stunned and you're in melee range use your Punshing Strike to deal a huge amount of damage and dramatically reduce his dps.  Basically just keep them stunned for your punishing strikes.  When the Shivan spawns, use Lift off using up one charged foci.  When you get better at this event you can down her without a Lift off.  Treat her as a Big guy, stun locking her and punishing striking her until she drains life.\
\
Demon 3: Shivan\
\
Stage 1: Eye of Shartuul\
Stay in shadow form and wait for beholder to spawn.  Cast siphon life and shadow nova then go into Flame form.  FLAME BUFFET IS YOUR FRIEND! Stack it constantly casting pyroblast in between CD's.  When he begins casting Dark Glare go into Ice form and ice block.  This will reflect the damage dealing huge damage.  Go shadow form when it CD's and use death blast if Siphon is still up.  Apply another Siphon and go fire.  Repeat until dead.\
\
Stage 2: Hound of Shartuul\
apply Siphon and go fire form.  Spam flame buffet and just kite the dog.  Watch for a debuff on you and cleanse it with the Clensing Flame move of fire form.  Simply kite and use to restore health and he'll die from the flame buffetx 10 pyroblasts.\
\
Stage 3: Shartuul\
Go shadow Form, apply siphon life and shadow nova, go Fire form.  Spam Flame Buffet and watch for debuffs that you MUST cleanse or Shartuul deals a lot more damage.  if he casts incinerate go ice and ice block to reflect it.  Once Flame Buffet is stacked to 10 make sure Siphon Life is still up, if not go shadow and reapply.  Once both debuffs are up, go Ice and run up to him and Frost Nova, then, cast Chaos Strike (the two charged foci move.)  IMMEDIATLEY go Shadow and cast Death Blast.  Bam, you're at full health.  Wash, Rinse, Repeat.  If you run out of foci just spam Pyroblast.\
\
Tips: If you have trouble with shartuul bring a mage or lock as their fire spell recieve the Flame Buffet effect.  My 70 Frost Mage was able to deal 77k fireballs and was actually able to aide in dps.",
