    "1070731509590315092007/02/06 01:28:35peesHeres a cheese way to do it:\
\
1) Bring a ranged lvl 70 class that can reach 36-41 yards\
2) Fly on top of the building and start plugging away at the soulstealers. They will not evade.\
3) The spawn waves will come out but won't attack you on top of the building.\
4) Shadowlord Deathwail will now land when the soulstealers are all dead, just wait a few minutes for the spawns to disappear then you can fight him all alone.\
\
Note: I tried this solo but i did not attempt to fully fight him. I attacked him from on top of the building and he did not evade since he does a ranged shadowbolt that only hits for ~1k.\
\
It may be possible to ranged tank him from the roof while taking no physical damage if your group lacks a warrior/druid/pally tank. Though his melee only hit for 900ish on cloth",
    "1070751178100511782007/03/14 16:29:02DaAznSaNAs a hunter:\
\
From the roof, kill the three casters around the pole. As stated above, they will not fight back and the melee that spawn will not be able to reach you. When the casters are all dead, wait for Shadowlord Deathwail to land and the rest of the adds to despawn.\
\
Deathwail is susceptible to Freezing Trap, Scatter Shot, and Silencing Shot, all of which are handy abilities for this fight. I also recommend wearing at least two Beast Lord armor pieces for the reduced trap cooldown. Talent points in Clever Traps and Trap Mastery are useful but not necessary (I didn't have them). The fight is pretty independent of gear besides the Beast Lord armor, and even so it'll just require you to take an extra shadow bolt every now and then if you don't have it. You may want to stack a little more HP than normal. Time does not seem to be an issue since I spent about twelve minutes doing the quest, starting from when I fired my first arrow to when Deathwail died; staying alive should be prioritized over doing damage (although doing more damage will reduce the length of the encounter, thus reducing the margin of error).\
\
The general idea is to nuke Deathwail with an Aimed Shot, Multi-Shot, Arcane Shot, and Auto-Shot rotation. When it casts shadowbolt, fire a Silencing Shot to pull it into your Freezing Trap. Run to the other side of the platform and wait for your traps to cooldown. A mod that counts down the duration of your traps is very handy; I recommend Sorren's Timers (found here http://files.wowace.com/). Just as your Freezing Trap is about to expire, charge up another Aimed Shot, etc. combo and pull it into your trap with Silencing Shot. From here, it's repetition.\
\
Some things can and will go wrong. If your trap is resisted, make use of your Scatter Shot to stun him and line of sight (LOS) to avoid his shadow bolts. A good place to exploit LOS is the nook to the right of the building's entrance, as well as the very left corner of the building. This is where the reduced trap cooldown especially comes in handy.\
\
If you trap ends prematurely, do the same thing as if it was resisted.\
\
Because Deathwail will only cast shadow bolts when not silenced, if you fail to pull him far enough to run into your trap with Silencing Shot, use your Scatter Shot and hope that it'll cause him to walk dazedly into your trap. Otherwise, use LOS again.\
\
Be careful when trapping him in melee range. He might land a hit on you before he is affected by the trap, and your character might automatically attack back and break the trap. Make sure you turn your back to him if you plan to trap him within melee range of you. You'll see me do this often.\
\
When he's trapped, that's the perfect time to use bandages.\
\
Here's a video of me doing the fight. I made a lot of mistakes but still managed to complete it easily.\
\
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HoeSAheA36M\
\
Good luck!",
