    "10707136330201363302007/08/12 07:28:23LunieSolo'd this quest as a protection warrior, took about 30 minnutes. But hell, it was the most funny thing I did in a while! Just pull the ranged adds around a corner, be sure they stay in melee. Then move to the chanellers and \"dps\" them down, watch out for the fires, be sure you have trinkets/equipment that improves your block rating and value. Also, I found the figurine of the colossus work very well here, it heals a godly amount with all those orcs on you.\
\
Once the elite chanellers are down, move to the right side of the entrance of the nearby building to avoid pulling the \"boss\". Dps the orcs you got left down, eat up/bandage and get ready for the boss. I pulled him around that same corner to avoid getting respawns on me. Now for that fight, do *not* let any kind of shadow bolt hit you, they do rather heavy damage (around 1k). Be sure you always have rage for spell reflect, and only use it to reflect the \"Shadow Bolt\". He also does a \"Shadow Bolt Volley\", which you need to shield bash, or concussive blow. Rince and repeat, and he will be down after about 5 minutes.\
\
That's about it, remember to use your cooldowns, trinkets, potions etc, and you won't need a group for this quest.\
\
(I wore mostly epics from Kara, so I do not recommend trying this with worse gear)\
\
Lacane, Moonglade EU",
