    "1109070npcIllidari Lord Balthas23427npcIllidari Lord Balthas23427Netherwing500111089211090",
    "1109021064211891852007/12/31 19:20:59KnoxpwnsJust tag him with the item as he is coming next to the portal, then go behind the portal and hover behind the RIGHT pillar, he will be unable to damage you, but will not de-aggro. this is by far the best method. (see screenshots to find out where to position yourself)\
\
This method is stated elsewhere in these comments, but it is a great method and I wanted to put it as far up as possible so people would'nt have to do much digging to find it.",
    "11090202563211945632007/12/16 22:14:43BrainsnackAnother confirmation about above tactics, BUT there is something i would like to add for the more lazy people, like myself; You can stay on the portal, but you have to be out of his line of sight to avoid being hit by anything!\
\
[Story]\
\
First try:   I read above comments, so I thought it would be a peace of cake. I flew a little between the portal and the big red dude, started the channeling and moved onto the portal. But Reth was still hitting me with every ranged trick he had and I got hit by a meteor, bounced off the portal and got vanquished by an elite pat and his buddy's.\
\
Second try:   I began to think, that the trick must have been fixed. So I tried the same thing, just began somewhere else. This time, I started hovering above the edge of the portal (you can't be landed or else the channeling will not begin), just enough to get in range, and started the channeling. I tried to avoid his attacks by strafing left and right, but his Shadow Bolts we're hitting me for 600-1000 dmg (on mail) and I would not make it to the end of the channeling, which will take a bit of time. Eventually an exploding meteor got me.\
\
Third try:   Because the above comments were really recent, I figured there had to be something I wasn't thinking of. So I decided to give it another try. I started to hover above the edge of the portal again, started channeling and just eased back on to the portal. I landed and moved just slightly back some more, so I was out of his line of sight. And heck, this time everything played out as I had hoped! Reth was just standing there, trying his Cripples and Shadow Bolts, but nothing would hit me. When you need to start a new channeling session, just move forward a bit, up if you have to, and repeat.\
\
As always, the great hints here helped me clear another quest on my path to Netherwing history.",
    "11090203094111137932007/12/17 21:57:13tamsenmcI also used the \"hang out above the portal\" method. I had to pull him back to the portal a bit and mess around with my placement until I wasn't taking damage. I was able to get myself in a safe spot pretty quick. It worked like a charm.",
    "1109010615431891852007/06/17 19:00:28CleodoraLook at the screenshots and take position above the pillars, careful not to land. Keep your fingers on Q and E to strafe out of the way if fireballs come your way, other than that no attack can touch you. Be ready to chase him when his life dwindles to near zero and he walks out of range and breaks the beam, but when he does that he won't fight you back anymore and you're seconds away from victory!",
    "110908933851891852007/05/24 08:45:40BruciatoConfirmed. Funny quest indeed. Coords 9,42 Nagrand.\
\
I did it as a mage. Suggestions: mage armor, dampen magic, mana shield before to go on your flying mount. Start draining, just fly around him avoiding everything. If you have it, bring some stamina or pvp gear. I lost 5k hp doing this quest, not that much, but better to be sure.\
\
If you get hit by fireballs (which you can avoid) you're gonna fall down in the mobs. So be really careful for this or you're gonna die fast.",
    "11090154545201545452007/09/18 07:22:53smooWait for him to come close to the portal. Start channeling, land on the portal (most possible distance to him), channel and wait. Repeat.",
    "110909478340947832007/05/31 14:15:47IgnignotI tried to kite him into the portal, but it didn't work. I did find a nice bug that made this quest even easier. just hide behind the wall of the portal like i did in the pic.",
    "11090203920202039202007/12/19 11:55:35agent8261The above methods are unnecessary. Since I couldn't figure out how to bug it i had to figure how to do it legit. \
\
Here's the trick\
The pillar (obelisk) stones with 4 mobs channeling some spell around them, kite him to one of them. In order for him to get to you, he has to go around the stones. So what i did was just kite him (in circles) around those stones. It keeps him out of melee range, and when i was crippled it bought me enough time to move out the way. \
\
Hopefully that helps.",
    "11090194563401945632007/12/01 19:10:57aurocketgirlYou don't have to fly around to avoid anything.  Stand on top of the portal at 8, 43 and nothing will hit you there!",
    "1109090575210905752007/05/25 20:40:01Phlook-Fly to him, but stay far far away while still being able to use the soul cannon. The soul cannon has a range of 60 yards, which should be plenty. The key is to be 60 yards away from him, not 60 yards directly above him. If you are directly above him he will melee you and you will die.\
\
-Activate cannon, dodge his fireballs with your flying mount.\
\
- At no point should you ever get into his melee range, or he will hit you for ~3-6k. If this happens even once you are probably dead. Possibly in mid-air, and requiring a spirit rez. Stay in range of the soul cannon, out of his melee range. Basically just fly around while he follows you. Don't go too far though, or you will lose combat and he will reset. Don't worry about the shadowbolts, they won't kill you unless you get melee'd first.\
\
- Multiple people can get credit for subduing him even if they aren't grouped. I started using my soul cannon on him when someone else already had him down to 50%, and I still got credit for it. I was not grouped with the other person. \
\
>> LONG STORY SHORT <<\
Activate cannon from 60 yards away, kite him around with your flying mount, never get into melee range, and avoid fireballs, don't be directly above him or you'll get melee'd.",
    "11090154925101549252007/09/18 23:25:17Hai2uThe hard part I found with this quest was his crippling debuff.  The slowed movement I can cope with but the -50% stamina is a real bitch as when the debuff wears off your max hp goes back to whatever it was but your current hp stays the same.\
\
After 2-3 cripple attacks I was down to like 10-15% hp and had to fly away to eat.  In the end I accomplished the mission by using the portal to get out of LoS as a number of people have suggested, it worked first time (hovering just above the portal) so I'd advise giving that a shot if you are having problems :)",
    "11090191540101891852007/11/26 09:38:41BigMongoThey fixed the druid flight form.  You can so this in flight form.",
    "11090197124111945632007/12/06 21:02:04PremierBlahShe's right. I tried it twice. The first time I twirled around him using the cannon and dodging his attacks like I was in one of those Dragonmaw races. The second I kited him to the Portal and sat down on it - I kept draining him while he stood there  as if expecting me to kill him - I did not have any meteors or Shadow Bolts sent after me and his Cripples failed to hit. Then he just started his death walk and from there it was a piece of Portal cake. Easy!",
    "110909112211908472007/05/26 15:14:40TaarvenThis can also be completed by groups together or even out of faction groups. We came into the area as horde began the event and pitched in to help. Once he was at 1% and headed to the portal we got quest credit.",
    "110901152971901152972007/07/04 03:28:27JakobudIf you look in the screenshot I posted above you will see that I am flying (although it looks like my mount is landed, but in midair) on the RIGHT side of the portal out of Line-of-Sight.  I am also very close to the top section of the portal, which allows me to avoid any of the dismounting meteors that fall from the sky.\
\
