    "10901170npcSkar'this the Heretic22421npcSkar'this the Heretic22421",
    "109019382040938202007/05/30 17:46:48JagnoUntil they nerf/fix the wall-jumping glitch, a rogue or druid can easily solo this with no potions, no soul-stone, nothing but some jumping skills.\
\
Stealth towards the first set of guards who can see through stealth and /wave to them because you're not going that way. Continue down into the water in front of you and below Rokmar the Crackler. If you swim up towards the ledge he is on, you'll notice the walls have overhangs so you can't wall walk up them. Well, along the left and right sides there is another wall connected to the overhang that is about 98% vertical. That 2% is what makes this possible.\
\
Wall jump up the nearly vertical wall and onto the ledge above. I'm not saying it's easy, in fact it's fairly difficult due to the steepness of the slant as well as getting the first jump up since you have to start from swimming. However, it only takes about 8 consecutive jumps and then you're up. From there stealth backwards through the instance and there are no guards who can see through stealth between you and him.\
\
Enjoy!",
    "109015764961464442007/03/26 17:28:19cyinAlso, you can get the quest by going into an already cleared slave pens to pick it up, if your guild runs slave pens heroic and your not needed just wait outside and your set.",
    "10901207297112013182007/12/25 23:02:00davvvActually, there are four Trials of the Naaru (Mercy, Strength, Tenacity, Magtheridon). With Magtheridon only being available after the first three heroic-only quests were completed. Have fun :)",
    "109015931251283432007/03/29 17:23:48jestyrjust stealthed to this quest. i played it safe and got a healthstone, a soulstone, and 2 Limited Invulnerability Potions. \
\
for the first group of two that can see through stealth, stay back from the ramp (make sure no patrols are near), drop stealth, evasion, sprint, and use a Limited Invuln Pot. i actually made it through them without getting hit (maybe it was a bit of lag) then vanished near the end of the hallway. \
\
avoid the first boss on the ramp, and the patrols above him on the way to the second patrol with 2 mobs that can see through stealth. wait until the regular patrols on the bridge are heading away, and repeat the above. jump off the bridge into the pool and wait for the mobs to evade. when you come out of the pool Skar'this the Heretic is all the way on the left side, in a cage. \
\
good luck!",
    "109015634851283432007/03/24 11:46:27tholexAlso note that you only need to take out 4-5 pulls to get to the questgiver, and only one (double hard-hitter) pull is of any toughness. You can skip a ton of mobs in Heroic Slave Pens just by timing runs a little bit. If you don't really need the instance, your healers / tanks / non-stealthers probably need the quest anyway, so just do the few pulls - getting to the questgiver is not hard.",
    "10901201318102013182007/12/14 18:35:29ChillingOutThis is required (along with the 3 Naaru quests from A'dal in Shattrath) to obtain the title \"Champion of the Naaru\".\
\
This means you have to hand in the 3 Trial quests (Shadow Labs, Steamvault Heroic, Shattered Halls Heroic and Magtheridon) and also this quest which requires you to get the items from Nightbane and Gruul, to obtain the title \"Champion of the Naaru\".",
    "1090128343220283432007/01/31 14:53:54shieldbWith the help of a couple limited invulnerability potions (to live to sprint past the guys who can see through stealth), and vanish it is possible to stealth to Skarthis as a rogue on heroic mode to pick this quest up and turn it in.",
    "10901196717101967172007/12/06 01:16:20mynameisob3lany rogue worth their salt can stealth to this guy without any silly \"invuln pots\" or the like.\
\
sprint + evasion past the first two stealth seers; vanishing at the end of that hallway. then make your way up the ramp behind Mennu. wait for evasion and vanish to cool down and get up to the top of the \"horseshoe ramp\" with the patrolling technicians. i was able to distract the next two stealth detectors, and the whole next group (one naga and two slave looking guys), in one move, then evasion sprint past them, not getting hit once, and vanish during the fall down to the water below.\
\
cake.\
\
\
sidenote: i still got the 24g for turning this in, but maybe because i already had the quest from forever ago, before they nerfed it.",
