    "9730157939101579392007/09/25 02:20:53lethaldosei gave it the college try as a 64 mage, she was immune to my frost nova. As well as my slow, i had no way to get any distance , and as a clothy i was getting hit for 1K + each swipe. Be prepared",
    "9730104116101041162007/06/14 06:46:07anghellicCan be a pain, but solo'd with a 62 hunter, scorpid stung him and mend pet, popped rapid fire, my trinket for attack power and beastial wrath, was slow but got him after my pet died.  As a hunter his throw back move just makes it so you can shoot him or concussive shot him and kite easier",
    "97302720160272012007/01/29 14:34:00Preacher5571He's immune to fear, I learned that the hard way.",
    "9730185956101859562007/11/16 20:02:22Hapselegaff lock soloed it by dotting it and running on the bridge CAKE WALK!",
    "973048987111369752007/03/10 03:29:52DathrenI solo'd as a deep frost mage at 63 pretty easily, just use the bridge to the east of him. Just hit him with a fire blast whenever its up to keep him tag'd and jump off the bridge when he gets close to you. Then run up the ontop of the bridge again and nuke him. repeat till dead.",
    "973021101400211012007/01/17 17:12:44aciraCoords: 65, 68",
    "973011512611369752007/07/03 17:40:50tussilagoListened to Dathren's advice and did  this quest as lvl 62 (deep fire) mage. \
\
Started with pyroblast (combustion and trinket helps), fireball and a fireblast (if he's stunned you can get more stuff in, just be careful: he hits hard).\
Then blinked and ran towards the bridge east of his location. As soon as fireblast was up (while running) I jumped and used it backwards at him midair, to keep him from resetting. Then I ran in 8:s over and off the bridge, spamming those fireblasts as soon as they were up. If not: he'll reset (did countless of times for me until I managed to kill him). \
\
Make sure you wait till he's up on the bridge before jumping down, and don't run up until he's heading down towards you.\
Might take some practice to get it to work, but at least you won't die trying (he resets if you fail)...unless he gets to you and hits too many times.\
\
Extra tip: you can get him to move back and forth on the bridge if you do the same when down in the water. Happened to me for a while and I got in 2 fireblasts before he decided to run down via one of the sides.",
    "9730200099102000992007/12/12 09:05:25zidusSolo'd as a 63 enhancement shaman, very easy. i was left with 4000/5800 hp. The totems I used were Healing Stream, Stoneskin, Grace of Air and Searing Totem. Also Shamanistic Rage helped alot. I only got crit'd for about 500 and hit'd for 250-350.",
    "9730209212112070622007/12/29 07:37:27MercrucioI have just soloed this as a lvl 64 aff lock. \
\
Dragged him away to a place where no mobs would be adds, then put Curse of Weakness and Corruption on him. Used health funnel to heal my VW while he tanked, then used first aid and health stone to heal myself when my health was low due to health funnel.\
\
Took about 4-5 mins.",
    "9730209946102099462007/12/30 14:50:09ultimar235I managed to solo him as a 62 combat rogue. I had well fed buff and some engineering equip aswell as world buff and spore bat (7k hp). The best way is to only dps him whilst he is stunned and gouge him the rest of the time until KS is back. Wait til he uses shield wall then blow your cooldowns aswell as evasion.\
\
If you get low stun/gouge sprint and bandage up. He can't be slowed or blinded but he can be stunned/incapa.",
