gl",
    "11070101554101015542007/06/09 20:03:21jon4009This guy is a big pain in the butt.\
\
What worked for me was: stay in front of him as he flies around to the mine at the start.  Use the time he wastes there to get above him and then track him from above using the arrow keys, using X and Space to go up and down as required.\
\
As mentioned above the only tricky bit was the dive over the cliff and then up the hill beside it.  Get that bit right and you are home free.",
    "110709214680921462007/05/28 02:16:10ElastikI attempted this guy at least 10 times or so before completing it. The best advice I can give you is to learn his flying path. As long as you are not chasing him he's not going to dismount you. If you stay by his side and know his turns, you can just short cut him whenever he does. If you for fall behind and have to chase him, you are most likely screwed unless he is going to turn soon.",
    "11070139010201390102007/08/16 14:36:00PaddyjackBe careful at the end, he is doing a final loop over the landing strip. My quest failed because I thought he was landing so I stopped.",
    "11070212143102121432008/01/03 10:51:44FiskodlarenI took him down on my first try! thanks for the help everyone!",
    "11070161188301611882007/10/01 05:32:31PowitoTook me one whole week (playing 2h/day) to beat this guy. I tried to find all sources of information on how to win the race, some good ones I've found:\
\
- [b]AddOn ImprovedCamera[/b]: Increases limit of the Max Camera Distance slider in Interface Options to the very maximum possible (from 30 to 50).\
\
http://wow.curse.com/downloads/details/5098/\
\
- [b]Youtube videos[/b]: Learning his path makes things much easier, watch it over and over: \
\
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UX0yysWOtMc\
\
- [b]Turn off your UI:[/b] Press alt+Z to turn off your interface, so everything on the screen disappears and you can see Mulverick easier.\
\
- [b]Raid Mark him[/b]: Invite some guildmate or random guy to a party, so you can add a mark icon to his head. Personally I used the blue square.\
\
- [b]Buy a Riding Crop:[/b] If you're farming for your netherdrake, you surely have 60-100g to spend on a riding crop. It sucks that after you win this chain of quests you get a riding crop as a reward, but to beat mulverick and captain skyshatter you MUST have this, otherwise it gets close to impossible.\
\
With the tips above, you can easily solo this guy. If you have friends, call them to be hit by his bolts instead of you, and a pally to give you crusader aura.\
\
Hope you all can do it faster than I did, good luck!",
    "11070197209101972092007/12/07 01:22:35PremierBlahI have to agree - the best course of action is stay as much above him as is physically possible and still be counted as in the running, as well as dodging all his Sidewinder Lightning missiles. My suggestion is to try it a few times even if you don't succeed at first, that way you get a good handle of the route you take, which can also help ease the confusion that comes when he sometimes changes course to distract you. Even if I took a few tries it was always frustrating in a fun way.\
\
