    "110701413201101413202007/08/20 17:58:33happysocksTip: take off your gear if you're doing this...then if you fail and die you don't have to pay repair bill.",
    "11070176137101761372007/10/28 19:02:20RunawaynowSo, don't know if anyone noticed this, but both the Wing Commanders have names similar to the main duo in the movie Top Gun. Iceman (Ichman) and Maverick (Mulverick).\
\
Obviously, Tom Cruise was the hero in that movie so the character based of the role he played must have a harder race, right? Of course maybe that's an incorrect assumption to make...",
    "11070162873201628732007/10/04 13:50:26UmokThis guy is far the hardest of the 6 racers. If you can beat this guy, you can easily beat Skyshatter. Just fly high and avoid as many missles as possible. Another good tip is that if you get lost for like 1-2 seconds, follow his missle trail. I lost him the first time, but quickly recovered and almost nailed it on the first time. After another 3 attempts, I knew the route by heart. I completed after my 5th attempt. Also, he also dive around the transporting dock on netherwing ledge. Just make sure then that you stick close, but for the rest of the run you can fly high.\
\
Don't give up on any of these races. The best way to do is to study their trails. It's much easier if you already know where you going.",
    "11070166845101668452007/10/12 17:48:13VanTokkernI have completed this quest 3 times now, except that I haven't. At the very end he does a 180 before he lands, he picks up speed right before he does the 180 and he's managed to fly out of range there 3 times now.\
