so just another way of saying AFK",
    "11070144546201445462007/08/26 22:25:21LinisThis guy is really easy if you follow a simple strat.\
\
1)Turn your UI off\
2)Get some race music playing\
3)(the actual strat) Start the race off below and too the left of him, then, when he fires his volley of lightning bolts, move to the right and then up to dodge, and then you should be above and to the right of him, then on the next bolt, move to the left and then down, so you are back around the area where you started, and keep repeating this. If you get too far from him, just try and shortcut your way closer to him, not that hard. he does do this thing where he'l flip around, and then back to the way he was going, just stop going forward and keep an eye on where he goes, then go back to chasing him when he starts back on his normal way.\
\
Hope this helps.",
    "11070210974102109742008/01/01 12:18:45MagirasTo the person who failed once because he looped around the tower you should have seen that one coming, Maverick ALWAYS buzzed the towers in Top Gun. If he didn't I would have been disappointed.",
    "110701475522401475522007/09/01 08:19:56GraunFun fact: it takes 1:40 mins for Mulverick to to trot into position, slowly fly over the airfield strip, and actually start the race.\
\
Mindnumbing.",
    "1107090820121894392007/05/26 06:55:50BeskaI've must have spent a combined total of at least 4 hours trying to find a reliable way of beating him, and this is the best tactic I had come up with, and when using it I won the encounter in only two attempts.\
\
Basically, the lightning bolts track you and that's what makes Mulverick difficult. To trivialize it, invite 3-4 friends into your group and get them to follow him too, dodging the lightning bolts. What happens is that the lightning bolts now track between 5 people (including yourself) rather than just all chasing you. It makes it incredibly easy, and requires you just to keep up with him and dodge a bolt every now and again.\
\
I've found that druids are very good at sucking up the bolts, as when he dismounts them, they can mount right back up in the air and carry on following. If worst comes to worst and they get knocked down, they're the quickest of all classes to remount and get back up to helping you.\
\
If any of your party are knocked down, tell them to remount as soon as possible and join you following him again. Marking Mulverick, yourself and everybody in the party also makes it easier to track where you are.",
