    "980764npcGshaff17925npcGshaff17925Sporeggar750",
    "980727287161234352007/01/29 17:38:31AlextaniumLow drop rate? its 32%. Thats pretty good. I've been grinding the Greater Spore Bats and Ironspike Basillisks at the top left of Zanga for a few hours now and I almost have enough spores to go to Revered. At the same time I'm getting Strange Spores to turn into Sporeling Snacks for my pet, and Chunk 'O Basillisk to turn into Blackened Basillisk spell damage food.\
\
Green drops out here are good too, plenty of vendor trash also. I should be Revered in another 2 hours.",
    "9807197173211324682007/12/06 23:40:55DemonScuzzThe real advantage to this quest, in my opinion, is that it can be done by characters other than the one that needs rep.\
\
For example, my healer is an alchemist, but not very well specced or geared for farming the naga. My warlock, on the other hand, can kill sporebats for hours without needing a break. So I use the 'lock to farm up the fertile spores, and send them to the healer, to turn in for rep.\
\
The one for the Sanguine Hybiscus can work the same way, if you're able to solo your way around Underbog.",
    "980727341191234352007/01/29 19:12:58AlextaniumJust hit Revered. Spore turn in still works. 440 Fertile Spores will take anyone from the start of Honored to Exalted.",
    "9807132468101324682007/08/05 04:38:21GumbomcnastyWhile it's a decent way to get rep, I honestly think Now That We're Still Friends... is a better rep yield. Since it dependent on a drop related quest item it's a guaranteed gain in rep. Run in, kill, run out. Fifteen minutes at the most whereas you could have a good drop rate for a few times and kill sporebats for an hour and only get a small handful of spores.",
    "980713518421234352007/08/10 01:13:52KukistajAKilling the giants awards 15 rep / kill. Farming fertile spores awards 750 rep / 10 spores * 32% = 24 rep / kill. Repeating Now when we're still friends... awards 750 rep / 24 kills = 31,25 rep / kill.\
\
There is no huge difference in rep / hour. The giants are fast and easy to kill, and there is lots of them at Fungal Vale which raises their farming value compared to mobs that drops Fertile Spores. If you own epic flier, you might want to farm the nagas, since flying back and forth is the biggest downtime there.",
