just place the kegs close to the orges, without aggroing, it worked for me, (66hunter), though if you get down to 5charges, i suggest you place it infront of patrols.",
    "10512164742301647422007/10/08 12:33:27redbackYou should be able to gather more brew from the bloodmauls if you use up all the charges before you finish",
    "10512125038301250382007/07/22 15:45:19GraunRemember, Borgrim Stouthammer wants his empty keg back. If you threw it away after it was used up, you can't turn in the quest and have to abandon/restart it.",
    "1051259154120591542007/03/29 12:05:20vatoskyEnter \"Bladespire Grounds\" @ 45.50 and start getting them drunk around that place. Enough room to avoid any Ogre.",
    "10512189386211647422007/11/22 09:58:12InfernoManConfirmed, you can go to the southern bloodmaul ogre camp and gather more brew from them if you run out of charges on your keg, just don't destroy the keg as you need it to complete the quest.  Also the brew comes in handy for later quests involving the bladespire, allows you to \"pull\" the named mobs without their \"sober\" elite guards making the fights one on one instead three vs one.  So stock up on it when need be.",
    "1051211472151591542007/07/03 01:16:56skywyzeThis ONLY works in the northern camp. It has absolutely no effect on any ogres in the south camp, no matter what you do. They walk straight through the ale on the ground.",
    "105128208021238342007/05/12 22:10:17VincenzoA rogue can just use distract on one and than place it down, the mob won't move until the 10 second distract duration is up, giving you a good amount of time to move away and restealth without having to wait for sap to end.",
    "10512185587101855872007/11/16 06:39:53Shei77they aggro to the beer within 40 yards! also when they \"drink\" the beer they attack u! VERY easy for hunters cause they place the beer and when they aggro..feign death! :)",
    "105122528660252862007/01/26 18:41:23DirePenguinApparently you don't have to wait for one to patrol into the booze.  The range at which the ogres will detect the stout is larger than their aggro range.  Figure out how far you have to be for them to just barely not aggro and drop it there.",
    "10512175298201752982007/10/26 18:36:00FaydenYou can give beer to the same ogre over and over... you just have to wait for the 30 seconds cooldown of the item",
    "105127494220749422007/04/29 13:21:14GymnosAs a rogue, I could just sneak up next to one and open combat by placing the mug down. I found it very easy.",
