    "109948880990888092007/05/23 19:45:48RasoreFirstly, make sure your hearthstone is on cooldown, go to Shattrath and portal to Orgrimmar (if your horde), then fly to valormok in Aszhara, mount up and head west.\
\
13,48 is the exact co-ordinates. As you approach this location from the east, you will see the moonstone on an alter.\
\
You interact with the stone as if to take it, at the end of the channel the goblin will spawn and sap you (As museyes said above, have your pvp trinket equipped to instantly break this).\
\
They jump instantly in the water (having ninja'd the stone off you) and start swimming south down the river. There are mines that will Frost nova you (shift in and out to continue) and other shoot you upwards (knocking you out of aquatic form). \
\
Personally I got to 7,94 before catching up with her. More and more speed boosts become available further down the path, I got 3 or 4 in total.\
\
As Duxa says, for the first part of the trek, hug the right hand side of the river, you'll avoid most of them.\
\
To 'win' simply catch up (and overtake her) at which point she will give in and stop, asking you not to hurt her.\
\
Simply speak to her to say 'hand it over' and she'll drop the moonstone in your bag!",
