    "10817120104201201042007/07/13 15:48:41jzneSolo'd as a 70 Shadow Priest in 20 minutes, flying mount required for this method.\
\
66, 42 Slayers are single pulls, killed all 8 on the way up - avoid the eilte. \
\
I flew in and landed on the corner of the structure at 68, 40 right behind a Darkreaver which did not aggro. If you watch for a minute or two you can establish the patrol patterns and drop down to kill the Darkreaver. A Chosen also patrols right up into the corner you landed at so you can take that too.\
\
The groups of duelling slayers each side i did not bother killing to save myself any possible aggrevation mentioned in above posts. When it was clear i moved to the top of the stairs and pulled the nearest Chosen out of the group of 3 who are facing west. Taking the mob back to the corner where i landed initially for a safe area to kill. Be careful not to aggro the duelling Chosens. Repeat when clear till all Chosens at the top of the stairs are down.\
\
With the first Darkreaver yet to spawn i then flew to 68, 34 for a safe 1 Darkreaver pull.\
\
72, 38 also provides a safe 1 Darkreaver pull.\
\
When they respawn repeat from the corner for any remaining Chosen's.\
\
This worked nice for me, i hope it helps someone :)",
    "10817205728102057282007/12/22 18:57:36fluxdragonI also used Izne's technique and can confirm coordinates are correct. By this level you should definately know your limits so watch your proximity and save yourself the hassle of extra agro'd mobs.",
    "1081736724161359732007/02/16 01:53:15decker12Aye excellent location at 72,41. Can easily pull those 4 closest slayers over and over again while avoiding the Eye and the wandering Elite. Just cram yourself in the corner to heal and drink, and wait on the slayers to repop, rinse and repeat until you have all 8.\
\
Of course you need a flying mount to get to this location without going down the hall and killing every slayer anyway, but for druids it's perfect.",
    "108177592330759232007/05/01 06:23:45blackhornHere is how I did it, quickly, with no deaths (requires flying mount):\
\
1)  Land on the wall at 71,41.  No mob will aggro or pursue you whiel you are standing on this wall, so it is your safe spot.  In front of you will be a row of slayers, which are all single pulls.  \
\
Wait for the elite and the eye of kilrogg to pass heading west (to your left), then get down off the wall pull and kill 1-3 slayers before hopping back up on the wall to wait for the elite pat again.    Note:  You need to fly to get back up on the wall, so give yourself time to mount.  Once you get your 8 slayers move to...\
\
2)  Fly to 72,38 land on the Darkweaver and kill him.  you are safe here from all except a Chosen pat on a long walk (kill him if he comes by), but all of the nearby mobs are bugged so you wil want ot move.  Fly to 71,39 and repeat on this darkweaver.\
\
3)  Fly to 70,35 and land on the wall.  This wall is different from the wall in step 1 in that mobs CAN and WILL path up onto it.  So time your kills to avoid the elite pat, and be in the air when he is coming around.  He's on a fairly long path, maybe 2 minutes.  Stay here and kill Chosen until you are done.  \
\
Note:  To compensite for a slow spawn timer, you can alternate between steps 2 and 3 as the spawns appear.\
\
Note:  Take the time to learn how the elite path to your kill spot.  it will prevent long lonely trips from the gy.",
    "108175059060505902007/03/13 14:25:25NickenyfikenWhen you do this horrible quest you can kill Smith Gurlonk (68, 36) at the same time because he drops the Primed Key Mould which starts the questline to get the key for Shattered Halls instance in Hellfire Peninsula.",
