Not sure if it's comparable, but the NPC at the wicker man fest givies the Horde quest to stink up Southshore.",
    "1658176624101766242007/10/30 00:15:58AnsawaEasily done at level 55. I mounted up, ran all the way up through Silverpine Forest, then just stayed on the road until I could see the statue in the distance. Veered off the road to the right, toward the plateau the ruins are on, passed behind a tree, and moseyed my way on up behind the Wickerman where the guards obviously couldn't see me. Sidled down to stand right behind the effigy, got the quest notification, then took right back off down the road--the guards aggroed on me but never even caught up to hit me once.\
\
Very, very easy way to net 12650 XP, and I daresay anyone over level 40 and mounted could do it that way with no fuss at all. Good luck to everyone doing it at 25; you're braver than I. ;)\
\
Edit: Also, there's no reason for people heading to the Wickerman NOT to go through Silverpine (on the road). The majority of mobs on/near the road up near the top of Hillshore are Alliance-friendly (Dalaran mages), and past that there's nothing over 15-16 near the road. There's ONE Horde NPC, level 13, actually walking on the road itself, but even if you're only level 25, you can easily avoid tangling with him. (Or kill him; he's not even PvP so if you shy from getting yourself flagged, like I do, there's not even that stopping you.)",
    "1658173063201730632007/10/22 09:09:01laughingnomeMy lvl 25 druid did this, but was killed by the elite guard. I saw him come at me, but I had to get a bit closer to complete the quest, so I actually ran a bit towards him knowing I would die. I was just a little over my half way point to lvl 26, so upon turning this in I was pleasantly surprised to see me level! 12650 XP is awesome, and I only did it thinking of the 4G!",
    "1658177814111734982007/11/01 17:56:57AnsawaThe route here would probably be best on a PvP server if you're trying to avoid getting ganked by Hordies in Silverpine.\
\
Otherwise, (see my comment below), there's no reason whatsoever to avoid the road if you're too low-level to travel past Dalaran safely (level 31+ beast mobs). It *may* be a straighter shot, as the crow flies, than going up through Silverpine, but since you're going to be spending a large part of it swimming, I don't know if it will take less time.",
    "1658172343201723432007/10/20 17:52:00Kisaac275 Alliance rep",
    "1658173498301734982007/10/23 05:25:45AisenfaireEasiest route, especially if you're too low for the Plaguelands, is to go north to Alterac Mountains (from Southshore), then west to Dalaran, and further west into the huge lake/ small sea with islands dotting it. \
\
The mobs in Dalaran are level 31 or so, and the mobs in this lake are level 18 or thereabouts, which should give you no trouble.  They're murlocs and treants staying on the islands, mostly; keeping to the water should not bring any mobs to bother you.  \
\
Once in the lake, head north and you will reach Undercity very quickly.  Of course, don't go directly up/ into the city.  Just follow the path towards Undercity, and you will see a gigantic burning scarecrow statue thing (56, 69) with 2 giant elite abominations on either side of it.\
\
Here are maps that I've dotted to show the path to take:\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=267:497522507469510407529374558359562299554250551201551151547097532052]Hillsbrad Foothills[/url]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=36:520728531776531815531862532922492735470763444782415801388821348821371834317805292772275732259667246609238557238502230462216413202347187295177260156211146153]Alterac/ Dalaran[/url]\
[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=85:564959547916537866528821524770536730564691]Tirisfal[/url] --> The last dot on top of Undercity in this map shows the location of the statue.\
\
\
You will not be able to stealth successfully past them if you are 40 or lower.  Your best bet is to zip up to the statue and die on top of it, so that you will at least have completed the quest. \
\
My level 41 druid tried to stealth up to it though, by creeping along the wall, and was nearly at the statue when one of the abominations noticed.  I basically ran right on top of the statue and managed to get the quest completed as I died. \
\
This quest gave my druid (at 41) 12650 exp.",
    "1658202011020202006/10/18 17:42:21PhogHawkIt's just to the west of the Undercity, along the road. There's a giant statue thing made of hay. Run up to the statue, then run away.",
    "1658172835201728352007/10/21 19:57:54TheGmerI tired to do this quest as a level 16 mage on a PVP server, and would not get it.  After some research online, looks like it is it is open to 26 and above.  Has anyone under 26 been able to do this?",
