    "106655665431564032007/03/24 23:39:19DuodecimalPosted a movie of how to do this as a mage, look for Mechanar at the top of the page of www.slashflee.org. The first half deals with this, the second half is just old stuff I needed to put up so I can get the raw videos off my computer.",
    "1066544506190445062007/03/01 10:52:00jmdbcoolSoloed as a level 70 rogue.\
\
When you walk in, take the right hallway. You will need to stealth very close to some high level mobs, so, you can:\
(a) have Master of Deception\
(b) use a Sneaking Potion (this is what I did, I'm combat spec)\
(c) sprint like a madman and then vanish.\
\
Get to the ramp that Gatewatcher Iron-Hand patrols on. He walks up to the top of the ramp, walks down and says hi to Capacitus, and then walks back up. If you stand on the edge of the ramp he will not see you.\
\
Looking over the edge of the ramp you can see your prize-- there should be 4 Overcharged Manacells there. Closest to you there is a group of 2 Sunfury Engineers, and 2 Mechanar Tinkerers. Don't even think about fighting any of them, you'd die-- we have something much more roguish planned.\
\
Wait until Iron-Hand is at the bottom of the ramp, and then throw/shoot at one of the engineers. They will start to path all the way around the pillar and up the ramp towards you. When they are about to get to you, jump off the ramp landing right next to one of the manacells. Vanish, and grab it. You should have enough time to get it with a couple seconds to spare, before they kindly come back and kill you, porting you out of the instance.\
\
This would have been easy to get in a group, since you only have to clear to the first boss, but if you're up for an exciting challenge, you can try this method.\
\
Enjoy the rest of this excessively long quest chain. ^_^",
    "10665101929511012162007/06/10 14:22:48rrcp1usTo answer my own question, the item is still clickable on heroic.",
    "106655640340564032007/03/24 14:29:07DuodecimalMages can also solo this very similarly. Timing is extremely tight, so you'll be better off waiting for Invisibility to cool down.\
\
1. Go invisible and run through the corridor on the right, sticking to the left as you head up through the first hall. There will be a barrier on the left. Head to it and let Invisibility wear off there.\
\
2. Gatewatcher Ironhand's patrol path takes approximately 55 seconds. Once the cooldown has finished for Invisibility, wait for him to come up to the top of the ramp, behind the mo'arg and blood elfs. When he turns to head back down, cast Invisibility, wait for the fade, and then head to the ramp.\
\
3. Once you're on the ramp, climb up onto the left side of it and cast Mana Shield to dispel invisibility. There is a guard at the top of the ramp and a group of mobs at the bottom of the ramp, so you will need to space yourself midway between the two ends of the ramp as you stand on the ledge.\
\
You will see the mana cells down below you, a short drop away.\
\
4. As soon as you can target them, fireblast any of the four mobs (two non-elites, two elites). They will start pathing around the column, aggroing two other groups on the way. Wait until they almost on top of you or about to hit you with ranged attacks, then jump down next to a mana cell.\
\
5. This apparently breaks line of sight. Immediately loot the nearest mana cell and prepare to die. You did disrobe prior to this exercise, correct?",
