  ["Kael'thas and the Verdant Sphere70"] = {
    "1100770itemVerdant Sphere32405npcA'dal18481",
    "11007204921202049212007/12/21 07:23:16KamisutraNewest info on the Sunwell storyline zone and both instances, released yesterday(thanks to wowinsider and worldofraids). \
\
* Sunwell Isle is a new zone, north of Silvermoon City\
\
* The 5-man wing of the instances is called Magister's Terrace featuring normal and heroic difficulty\
\
* The raid wing is called Sunwell Plateau, players can fight 6 raidbosses here and the one of the main stories of Burning Crusade continues here\
\
* Outside the instances there will be lots of quests (daily quests too), wrapping up the story of Tempest Keep\
\
* The questhub of the zone will be interactive, as players complete quests, the activity in the town will increase more and more, eventually growing into a big town, similar to how Silithus prepared for the Qiraji war, on a smaller scale though\
\
* The quests and instances introduce a new faction called \"Shattered Sun Offensive\", the Aldors and Scryers unite under this name to stop Kael'thas from summoning Kil'Jaeden (upd)\
\
* One of the bosses in the Magister's Terrace will be Kael'thas, whose story continues the Verdant Sphere quest. He'll have a large green crystal attached to his chest ^^\
\
* Kil'jaeden will be featured in the 25-man instance, and the EPICness of the fight will be on par with Illidan's. There are 5 more bosses: Brutalicus, a pit lord; Kalecgos, the blue dragon from the Sunwell Trilogy (who is enslaved by Kil'jaeden); a Fel Dragon; female Eredar twins; and a Dark Naaru!\
\
* The raidinstance is designed for players with Tier 6 equipment and it will be slightly more difficulty than Black Temple (upd)\
\
* There won't be a Tier 7 raidset, however there are sets in the loottables (upd)\
\
* The raidinstance doesn't have an attunement requirement, but players of the entire realm must complete a certain amount of daily quests on the Sunwell Isle, to unlock the last 3 bosses (upd)",
    "11007133285111332282007/08/06 14:49:37BearclawMore likely that it refers to Kil'Jaeden.",
    "11007190049501900492007/11/23 17:17:23KamisutraUsually in any major instance there's an endboss drop starting a quest, which confirms the Boss' lore status, such as:  http://www.wowhead.com/?item=21221\
http://www.wowhead.com/?item=22520\
or the Verdant Sphere we're curenly discussing.\
\
So for example the Eye of C'thun confirms C'thun's demise, while The Phylactery of Kel'Thuzad  or the Verdant Sphere confirm Kel and Kael aren't dead. \
\
I'm sure Blizzard will implement a similar item for Kil'jaeden to confirm his lore status.",
    "11007136888201368882007/08/13 04:25:11ildonWhat the text means is that Kael'thas lived, his soul still trapped in the sphere (or something). From within the sphere, Kael calls to a higher power, that higher power being Kil'jaeden. And the location in Azeroth that A'dal refers to is most likely the Sunwell Plateau, the final raid dungeon of TBC, with Kil'jaeden as the final boss.",
    "110071378981811368882007/08/14 15:19:45CheffsActually, Kael is indeed allied with the burning legion. He realized that Illidan was insane, so he turned his back on him. Thats the reason horde players can kill blood elfs and, eventuelly Kael himself. The scryers didn't like that he allied with The burning legion, so they left and are now fighting him instead. The blood elfs still in azeroth doesn't know about that Kael'thas is evil,so they continue to travel to outland. \
\
This it what he yells when you turn in the quest.\
\
Silence descends upon Shattrath \
A'dal's thoughts invade your mind \
Kael'thas Sunstrider has been defeated by (name)and (his/her) allies \
The time to strike at the remaining blood elves of Tempest Keep is now. Take arms and let A'dal's song of battle empower you! \
Kael'thas Sunstrider yells: Your monkeys failed to finish the job, naaru! Beaten but alive... The same mistake was not made when we took command of your vessel. \
Kael'thas Sunstrider yells: All for what? Trinkets? You are too late. The preparations have already begun. Soon the master will make his return. \
Kael'thas Sunstrider yells: And there is nothing you or that fool, Illidan, can do to stop me! You have both served me in your own right - unwittingly. \
Kael'thas Sunstrider yells: Lay down your arms and succumb to the might of Kil'jaeden!",
    "11007123093701230932007/07/19 01:40:52Whitemanehttp://www.wowhead.com/?spell=39953\
\
That's the buff everyone in Shattrath gets when the quest is completed.",
    "11007187747111576142007/11/19 15:16:44KamisutraIn the Games for Windows september issue(I highly encourage anyone interested in the instance to get a copy of it), I mentioned before, Metzen said that one of the reasons for implementing the Sunwell was that he wanted the Burning Crusade expansion pack to have a clear ending and the players to achieve a clear victory over the Burning Legion. \
\
So while Kil'jaeden might indeed not die, I'm fairly sure he'll at least end up without a body like Sargeras did. As the fact that  the Burning Legion constantly tries to conquer Azeroth and constantly fails despite all its power has become rather old, very fast. Blizzard does have more psychologically interesting and more viewer appealing villains anyways, Arthas, Azshara, Deathwing.\
\
On a side note, if Blizzard decided to kill him off anyway, getting killed by 25 super powered mortals, while in a weakened half-summoned state, sounds as a prettier way to go than being blown up by a bunch of whisps. :P",
    "11007197310211959712007/12/07 06:30:19KamisutraIt was already stated in several blue posts on the Blizzard forums that the Sunwell will be implemented before WotLK and is meant as an ending to TBC.\
\
Alliance will be able to get to the instance without having to ride through Ghostlands and Eversong(though Blizzard hasn't yet specified how, I assume a teleport or a boat).\
\
Arthas will have no direct involvement in the reappearence of the Sunwell, the Sunwell will be reignited thanks to the energy transfered from Outland's Netherstorm via Kael'thas(it turns out that's what the Manaforges were build for).\
\
Most of the info I provided is easily findable on sites like worldofraids.com or blizzplanet.com",
    "11007152518411368882007/09/13 13:41:10KamisutraKael's soul isn't trapped in the Sphere as ildon claims, he actually makes an appearence during the event in Shattrath(don't know if it was this way always, or if it got implemented after a hot fix). \
\
And yes, judging by the fact that Metzen mentioned in an interview with Games for Windows Magazine(september issue) that Kil'jaeden will be an encounter at the Sunwell Plataeu, this quest is certainly a teaser/lead-up.",
