  ["Blood Elf + Giant = ???70"] = {
    "1077417068npcWildhammer Gryphon Rider19382npcWildhammer Gryphon Rider1938215800110772210773310774410775510776",
    "10774121520201215202007/07/16 09:27:12GuardixSolo'd as mage with the same method as hunter, but instead of jumping off the hill loosing too much hp, make sure you have some light feathers to float down.\
I kited Corok the Mighty all the way to Wildhammer Stronghold with this route by using ice lance to keep the aggro:\
http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=3520:538687554695569697580691591677602664611642611625603607590592580580569574555568537568520568505574485574462565449539444524427520404520387532374543\
Once you hit town the guards will help you kill Corok, but just leave Chancellor Bloodleaf, instead fly back to her correct position and kite her around the wall at the caravan with fireblast and just counterspell her whenever she manages to use arcane missiles.",
    "107743576040357602007/02/14 08:09:36marmalCan be soloed as a hunter. \
\
You pull them by concussion shooting the blood elf. She will be behind from this point. Then you concentrate your fire on the giant and pull him down the hill on the east side (you lose about 7000 HP from falling down), through the netherwing pass past the air elementals, and up through netherwing fields and then out on the road. \
\
The giant is simple, just normal kiting (except that the terrain makes it difficult), but the blood elf is very hard. If your pet is full arcane resistance spec you should be able to kill her after you kite the giant down. Kiting the BE was difficult because she has a 30 yard range on her arcane missiles, while my gun has a 35 yard range, so you gotta stay out of her range, while still getting off a shot at her now and then. I think it's easiest to let the pet tank her once the giant is down. \
\
Also, when you kill the giant, you can then FD and return to her spawn point and kill only her.\
\
I didn't solo the BE, because my pet had the wrong spec, but I think it should be doable.",
    "10774154441101544412007/09/17 23:30:19PapsYou can kill one and die, then come back for the other.  I soloed it this way on my feral druid.",
    "10774127204201272042007/07/26 14:20:11PaeganWell, I couldn't get the kiting method to work properly, they kept resetting when I jumped off and used my Skyguard slowfall cloak. So, after 5 attempts, I managed to solo it by \"brute force\" as a 70 BM hunter.\
\
Send in pet at the elf, use every cooldown and trinket that you have, keep Mend Pet up, and try to kill him before both pet and you die. It's very close and you need a bit of luck, but it's do-able. You have to tank the giant for at least half the fight because the HoT from Mend Pet will make him come for you after a few ticks. This is good though, the pet won't live long enough against both of them. Pop a healing pot, whatever, just try to get the elf down. If you can do that then you can feign death and have plenty of time to revive pet and recover hp/mp before taking on the giant, who isn't much of a problem by himself.\
\
Would be much, much easier duo though, neither mob is all that hard one-on-one. If both of them weren't immune to freeze traps this would be a piece of cake.",
    "10774193627101936272007/11/29 22:13:38AzuronU can pull the giant away with the flying mount; u have to keep a high enough altitude so u wont aggro the BE and fligh close to the giant (real close) he will atack u but u wont get agrro from anything else, then fly slowly away so as not to lose his focus till ur out of the BE range.\
Note that this means having to take the punding from him for short while, but if ur a holy pala like myself that wont matter too much ^^\
\
Also another thing, for ranged clases: u can stand on the ruined wall block right next to the caravan and pund away at the BE, the Giant wont inteviene as u are on higher \"inaccesible\" grounds, while the BE will engage\
in ranged combat",
    "107743925080392502007/02/20 10:32:25MunksgaardThey are standing together at 53;70.",
    "10774150371101503712007/09/07 14:32:46GeemahSolod as a Feral Druid with Engineering and [URL=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=23825]Nigh Invulnerability Belt[/URL].\
\
Started the fight in Cat Form and used Pounce + Shred on the bloodelf. After Shred i shifted to Bear Form (no damage taken so far). Used Mangle and Swipe to dps her down. Bash works well to avoid the nasty Arcane Damage she makes (Note: they both are cc immun, but not stun immun). \
\
The bloodelf was nearly dead when i had to use the belt to heal myself. Finished her off and went on with the Giant. Imp LotP kept my health up till he died; i still had Bash + Barkskin ready for a heal, but i dont needed it.\
\
Took me some tries to figure out the right equip, ended up with a mix of tank, dmg and arcane resi gear ;)",
    "10774151787101517872007/09/11 18:34:33PaladiniusWith a good tank, and a good healer, this quest may take a while, but it can be easily 2-manned.\
\
Stand on the cliff side of the covered wagon (opposite side of the giant and elf), and pull the blood elf.  Kill the elf first...least health and armor.  Make sure you are not standing too close to the edge of the cliff, at the giant does have a minor knockback.\
\
DPS the elf making sure to keep enough threat on the tank to prevent your squishy priest friend from getting smashed flat.  Utilize anything you can to interrupt the arcance missiles...they hurt.\
\
After the elf is dead (and she can hit hard), it's an easy tank and spank on the giant, provided your healer still has mana.\
\
Went through this as a ret pally with a holy priest with literally no issues.  Priest did get a little low on mana (about 35%) while both were alive, but utilizing the lightwell helped the priest out with healing.  After the elf was dead, the priest actually gained mana back.",
    "107745402021357602007/03/20 01:42:05seleceDefinately doable, although challenging.  The best method I found by following this is to clear a few of the elementals in the pass first, rush back, MD your pet and then begin the kite.  If you shoot the giant and keep him tapped, the BE will leash before you hit the Corrupted Air totems NPC.\
\
Extra challenging on PVP servers where the other faction is tempted to gank you while you're at 1k hp kiting a giant around. :P",
    "10774161407101614072007/10/01 14:28:06brocSolo'd this as a combat sword rogue. I did this by taking out the blood elf first, looting the quest item, and vanishing. Easy kill, just make sure to get in a kick to stop the arcane missles. She is immune to sap.\
\
The blood elf seems to have a long respawn timer, so after Adrenaline Rush and Evasion was back up I killed Corok pretty easily. Just make sure you watch for patrols.",
