    "102807698541755702007/05/03 07:26:15sweltThe follow-on, how to break into arcatraz, has rewards for mainstream specs.  Thus I think it's fine that this quest rewards 'offspecs'.",
    "10280116091811072742007/07/05 16:36:29WildhammerzWhile that may not be the best argument, saying the quest rewards for this aren't good because they are overly class specific isn't either.\
\
For instance, a warrior leveling in outland has to deal with paladin plate from almost every quest reward.  A warrior gets 0 benefit from plate with intellect, spell damage, and mana regen, so shouldn't there also be a reward for him from that same quest with melee crit and AP?\
\
How about a hunter who does a quest and gets a piece of mail from the quest reward with caster stats as well, like spell damage and spell crit?  Where is his quest reward with agi and ranged AP?\
\
Basically, what anyone who argues that the quest rewards for this specific quest are bad are saying that the vast majority of quests in Outlands and the entire game are bad because they don't provide enough variety.  Some quests give rewards that are designed for some classes.  Some aren't.  Not every quest is going to give you an item thats specific for your class and build (which is the same for every other class and build in the game).",
