    "109298259631243242007/05/13 22:07:15jacktwistthis is a fantastic strategy, but i'm surprised that no one has mentioned the absurdly large nets that the guards throw on the bone sifters.  for some odd reason, i find that amusing.",
    "109299912930991292007/06/06 02:32:12chriswtThe best area to do this would be [b]50,76[/b] because an NPC, Vindicator Haylen will help you. He doesn't do a whole lot of DPS but he has a net which helps sometimes and you can just leave undesirable mobs that spawn [i](Sand Gnomes)[/i] to him.",
    "1092920470721221342007/12/20 21:18:11KhamoraI never had a sifter hit me for much as a 64 feral druid.  Their normal hits  were around 230 and maxed out at  around 400, while their poison was around 267 nature damage each hit (on green same level leather armor).  Beating the drums as CLOSE to the camp as you can is a great idea even the sifters may aggro some of the guards to help, BE CAREFUL because if you don't do enough damage, more than 50% of the damage, you can't loot the corpse.  To keep the poison shots to a minimum, move your camera angle behind the sifter (they always sink and reappear behind you) so when they start to go down into the ground you can turn and run towards them as they reappear.  No trouble at all I'm assuming as a 63 or even 62 if you manage to get to the camp safely.",
    "109298100020810002007/05/10 16:27:30badgirlssays group but really is quite soloable. did this as a ret pally lvl 64 with really no trouble. Also if u dont feel like killing the sand gnomes since they grant no xp nor can you loot them. Do this quest near the bone wastes entrance to the allerian stronghold. when a gnome spawns run to the guards. saves time and prolly food andor mana drinks.\
\
good luck",
    "109292213450221342007/01/20 16:04:12elonex48,73 area, drop rate is 100% :) .. Drum either spawns a gnome or the Sifter u need. Sifter's do around 900-1000 poison dmg.",
    "109297233031715572007/04/24 19:54:16Fingolfin269Be careful if you are a Paladin.  You may need to let him port once or twice in order to do enough damage to get credit.",
    "109299589630958962007/06/02 10:06:31uaeknightUse the drum anywhere in The Bone Waste, when you see the minimap written The bone Waste, there you can use it, a big worm will spawn or a sand gnome, the worm drops the quest item every time you kill him wich means 100%m but the gnome doesn't.........btw, you can use the drum up to infinite times in the same place (must be in The Bone Waste), you can use it , finish the quest, get the reward in almost the same place.",
    "1092924324610243242007/01/25 10:12:13smanjoEasily compelted:\
\
