    "9859144582101445822007/08/27 00:47:52webermgSoloed as a 69 holy paladin.  Used 1h and shield, judged wisdom, and kept wisdom sealed all the time.  Kept concentration aura on all the time, since I had to heal every 10 seconds or so.  I popped hammer of justice, divine favor, and divine illumination every time they were up.  I think I bubbled once, but it wasn't really necessary; i'd save the bubble for an 'oh crap' moment.  I didn't use lay on hands.  A couple of super mana potions wouldn't hurt, the main goal in the fight is to keep your mana higher than it's health.  \
\
It hit me for 500, crit for 1k, used an annoying knockback move that interrupted heals, and also gored for a minor bleed effect.  Because of the knockback, start those heals early, don't wait til you're almost dead.  It has 25k hp, fight took literally ten minutes.  For that reason, i suggest using greater blessing of wisdom at the beginning rather than regular blessing of wisdom.",
