    "11122701npcNeill Ramstein23558npcNeill Ramstein23558",
    "111221652011001652012007/10/09 13:40:57JoroesanOn Alliance side I can max out at 51 tickets, 17 trips.\
\
Basically I start out as far away from the quest giver as I can while facing the direction I'm going to go with the Ram Racing Reins bound to a key so I can spam it easily while moving with my mouse for direction. I spam the Ram Racing Reins to keep a gallop all the way to the apple barrel by the bridge (it will reset without you having to stop) and over the small hill and then right as I go over the hill I stop pressing my key binding. When I reach the tiny stone wall on the ground by the road I turn around (he throws the keg even if I don't go all the way to him). When I reach the hill again on my way back I will begin to canter automatically since I haven't been spamming my keybinding. I canter all the way back to the apple barrel by the bridge, usually pressing the key binding for the Ram Racing Reins periodically to slowly swap between gallop and canter, just enough not to get exhausted. When I reach the apple barrel I start spamming my Ram Racing Reins again to gallop all the way back and repeat.\
\
(start) ->\
apple barrel by bridge -> over hill (stop using reins) -> turn around at stone wall -> over hill (begins canter) -> apple barrel by bridge -> turn in turn around and repeat\
\
It took a while to get used to, but this is faster than galloping between all the apple barrels. I used my bank alts to practice with. Before I reached around 30 tickets galloping the entire way, but this way it is possible to get around 50. Another good trick to shave a tad more time off of the trips is that when you are about to turn around; adjust the camera so you can see behind your character with your left mouse button, then turn around suddenly by clicking your right mouse button behind you. This should make you do a complete 180 without missing a step or wasting time moving in a half-circle. Although I cannot prove it, seems to me that the Riding Crop works on the Brewfest mount too.",
    "11122163746201637462007/10/06 12:38:32navheadYou can complete this with your normal mount too, don't know if it's intended or not. Accidentally clicked some beer in my inventory instead of the reins and got dismounted, still could pick up and return the kegs and thus complete the quest without the ram.",
    "11122163656201636562007/10/06 09:06:35sportman1280You don't have to talk to the guys when picking up or delivering, you just ride by them and they give you credit.  Flynn is near the Inn, and has a ^ over his head.  go near him and you'll get your keg.  Then ride back to where you got the quest from.  And repeat.",
    "11122163895301638952007/10/06 17:49:33SentientBest route is:\
Beer Tents -> Apple Barrel at crossroad ->Flynn at Karanos -> Keep riding past him about 20 feet to an apple barrel near a flag. -> Apple Barrel at crossroad -> Beer Tents\
\
Doing this you should be able to stay at a gallop and complete at least 9 runs for 27 tickets.. if you are perfect you might be able to do 10 runs for 30 tickets, but I usually hit some lag (or have to wait for an apple barrel to proc).",
    "11122165277211652012007/10/09 17:19:12BoydboydI've tried Joroesan's method and it works.  I was hitting all the apple buckets and maxing out at 11 trips.  I've only tried this method twice, but I've made 15 trips each time.  I'll get 17 next time since I know what I'm doing now.  Thanks for your insight Joroesan!",
    "11122158613101586132007/09/26 05:29:29Shaanvery nice LotR reference :)\
'There and back again' is the title of the book Bilbo starts and Frodo continues, then gives to Samwise at the end of the story.\
\
fun quest as well.\
\
this quest is the opener for the daily ram racing quests, it being repeatable forever is a bug that has been hotfixed and is now repeatable on a12 hours delay (not daily quest).",
    "11122165558111652012007/10/10 11:51:34HiddoAwesome find.  I have been doing the 'full run' circuit for many days and can get up to 12 runs in one session.  I'll be trying this when I get home tonight!",
  },
