  ["Teleport This!69"] = {
    "108576967npcNether-Stalker Nauthis20471npcNether-Stalker Nauthis2047115400The Consortium350110855210856310857",
    "1085777903151246822007/05/04 20:45:03MordritchOn a map: http://www.wowhead.com/?maps=3523:390200410190420210",
    "108575922971585532007/03/29 14:43:29MarrnYou can avoid the elite by mindcontrolling one on the other side of the boss.  The teleporter destroying spell of your pet is a ranged attack, so you don't actually have to get close enough to aggro the elite.",
    "10857194666101946662007/12/02 00:44:21olwenAs a Warlock, you don't even need to use the rod. You can enslave demon and it has the same effect.",
    "1085737781140377812007/02/17 21:28:28ShootaboySame with hunters, you must dismiss your pet before MC'ing a monster.",
    "1085749781201425862007/03/11 22:01:54DirgeIt's actually not mislabeled.  Mo'arg is the race of \"creature\" that the Cyber-Rage Forgelords are.  It would be the as a quest asking you to do something to the Blood Elves in the vicinity when they'd actually be named \"Sunfury Champion\" or whatever else.",
    "10857197931590197932007/01/08 09:52:22ErindYou must use the Rod to Mind Control one of the Cyber-Rage Forgelords near the portals and use their Detonate ability while standing next to it. If your pet bar doesn't show up, the ability's hot-key should default to Ctrl+5.",
    "108573785291363882007/02/18 00:24:01GilheruBighat figured it out.  If you are having trouble chances are good you are walking the demon out of the range of the control rod.  Move yourself closer to the teleporter and try again.  If you constantly try to MC them from max range and then move the Mor'ag away from you it will break.",
    "1085717134811377812007/10/18 19:58:35unitepunxWarlocks the same. Dismiss before you use it.\
\
Or enslave. Seems to work the same.",
    "1085766876111197932007/04/13 21:49:20zealvurteAs usual, having plenty of problems with no pet interface showing up. constantly. Thank's for the hot key idea.",
    "1085718193331197932007/11/10 11:56:10AmanitaThis quest aggravated the pi$$ out of me. As a hunter, you will have to dismiss your pet to be able to control the Cyber-Rage Forgelord. I highly recommend clearing as much of the area around the teleporters as possible ... the aggro you take while controlling the thing makes you break control ... then you have two aggressors. Watch out for roving pats of Priestesses and minion. I saw a 70 Dranaei warrior having a time also. You MUST be very close to the teleporter AND the Cyber-Rage Forgelord you control or you will lose control of it. Grrrrrrrrr! Glad it's done!",
    "10857177785401777852007/11/01 16:28:55FizzleboyThe Mental Interference Rod can be resisted !",
    "10857142449701424492007/08/22 18:39:45armuriIf you have a flying mount, there is a very easy way to do this quest. Land on one of the obelisk-type things with the green beams coming out of them, which are around the teleporters. Pick one with a Cyber-Rage Forgelord right next to it. It's a little difficult to land perfectly on the tip, but it is possible. When you land you will enter combat. After a few seconds of evading, he will appear right on top of you. Now use the Mental Interference Rod on the Forgelord. If you try to use it on him while he's on the ground, he will evade. With the Forgelord controlled, walk him off the obelisk and into the teleporter and use his move to destroy the teleporter.\
\
Another tip: if the pet bar doesn't appear, try using this macro:\
/Script PetActionBarFrame : Show()",
    "10857205945102059452007/12/23 09:04:08kazenoyoukaiIf you're a warlock, this quest is obscenely easy.  The goals of the quest don't specify that the rod be used, just that the teleporters be destroyed.  Use Enslave Demon, on one close to you.  Send it to attack something on the other side of the teleporter.  As he passes by, use the skill.  The elite is no problem.  For that matter, attack the elite with him!  Just use the skill when he gets down there.",
    "1085736388220363882007/02/15 10:26:21BighatJust remember that the range for the mental interference rod isn't very far. So you just need to stand close to the teleporter, and not move very far with the mo'arg",
    "10857120152131246822007/07/13 18:02:27SleuthIf you're like me and like accuracy, I have the exact coordinates:\
\
Eastern: 42.3, 21.1\
Central: 41.1, 19.4\
Western: 39.2, 20.4",
    "1085724682850246822007/01/25 21:23:52PorterWestern: 39, 20\
Central: 41, 19\
Eastern: 42, 21",
    "10857202904102029042007/12/17 13:57:19MotokiAs a hunter with a flying mount, you can complete this quest without having to kill anything.  Simply use Track Demons to find a spot close to a transporter within range of a mo'arg.  You should be able to destroy the transporter within seconds, giving you ample time to feign death.  Be careful at the central transporter, there are multiple patrolling mobs as well as the elite pit lord, and it is difficult to find a clear spot to land.",
  },
