    "103216189910618992007/04/04 07:36:40PhearfulThe person that you have to kill to shut it down is right there.. she is channeling (sorry if I spelt it wrong... I'm on vacation hehe) a red beam. It's pretty easy but sometimes two go out at once so you have to attack both",
    "1032127167120271672007/01/29 13:22:14NyghtravenLocated at 48,81",
    "103218405210840522007/05/16 12:49:24Badger1217Ok i've killed the overseer 3-4 times and still haven't gotten the crystal.....is anybody else having this problem as well?",
    "103213946340394632007/02/20 16:51:32AlariusDo this along with Attack on Manaforge Coruu (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10246).",
    "10321133299201332992007/08/06 15:23:40GweedoSpeed is the key.  Either watch your back constantly or spin a lot.  Just when you think you can take a breath a couple of them will appear out of nowhere.  If you have a ranged attack, hit them with the ranged attack when they try to channel on the mana forge.  That will break their attempt to abort the shutdown, and agro them.  They're MUCH less to worry about one you have them agro'ed.",
    "103213845540384552007/02/19 01:14:33SierajEnter the manaforge from the west: there's an elite guarding the east door, and the overseer's on the west side anyway. Techs spawned two at a time, but still easy. Elite wanders a bit, but will not path around to the west side.",
    "103218695231384552007/05/21 15:58:43VelscinthWhen I did this quest the elite wasn't on the west side when I entered, he was standing in the doorway of the southern most entrance of the Manaforge. However, he was pathing around a bit to the east and back to the south. I was able to complete the quest without even coming close to the elite.",
