    "10132681017068102006/12/05 22:49:44enasimaGet a group of 2-3 for this.  Colossals will spawn adds as their health depletes(up to 3 total).",
    "101322657640265762007/01/28 18:33:16xxanSolo'd easily by any warlock as these giants can be feared. If you keep your fear up at all times, you don't even have to deal with the small spawns.",
    "10132137560101375602007/08/14 02:41:49ZubastikSoloed by my lvl61 hunter, pretty easy for hunters and warlocks that have tanking pets. Just heal your pet through the fight and kill adds 1 by 1.",
    "1013247390101226122007/03/06 23:07:05satinternOnly good for Alliance as the temple guards are alliance.",
    "101322423860242382007/01/25 07:25:25senstarrrThese can  be soloed as a feral dr00d. Just take care to kill the first two spawns as soon as they are there.\
\
My strat:\
\
Root the mob, cast moonfire, faerie fire. Regrowth/rejuv then bear charge into the mob and maul away.\
\
First add spawns at 70%, kill that straight away; 2k hp and should die fast.\
\
After that add was dead, carry on mauling/mangling away. If hp does run low - bash/root run away heal, hots whatever and go back in. Kill the 2nd add that spawns as fast as possible that should be around 45% hp.\
\
After that kill the mob till he's dead then kill the spawns after. One thing I did notice is when I CCed the last spawn with nature's grasp, and finished the mob off because my health was running low, was that the spawn despawned after maybe 10-15 seconds. It might be worth someone testing this to see if all spawns disappear after 10 seconds or so. :)\
\
It's gonna be slow but they are soloable. Just be very careful where you pull, casting demo roar can pull a nearby mob to you and that is insta death for you. Move the mob to a clear area and you should have no problems at all.",
    "10132197034101970342007/12/06 16:52:49amensentisSoloable by locks, fear and CoE works just fine =) although i had problems with them running back and evading everything =S got rather confused",
    "101322261210226122007/01/21 23:34:20OscaronCan solo easily by kiting these mobs through the pass leading to the Temple steps.\
\
Guards take care of the rest.\
\
Warning: Grabbing more than one may seem like a good idea to speed things up, yet every time I did this the guards seemed to hesitate and I'd die or have to Feign, and lose at least one. Classes unable to dump aggro may find themselves in trouble.",
    "101329296661850432007/05/29 08:51:37CleodoraIt is possible to kill the colossus without getting any adds if you succeed in keeping it chain feared for the entire fight. Summoning the adds is an active skill and not a passiv eeffect, but if your fear lets off for even a single second, that's all he needs to bring the shardlings into play.\
\
It can still be done solo with the shardlings, but it's unnecessarily harder. Chain fearing makes it much easier.",
    "10132192695401926952007/11/28 09:50:49FinrearThe adds are summoned at 75, 50 and 25%.  If the mobs are stunned at that point then no adds will be summoned.  Makes it a lot easier to burn them down and stun just before the relevant percentages.",
    "1013221965140219652007/01/20 07:47:48JavaCoords: (18.40) and surrounding area.\
\
Suggested group: 3 people although it can be done with 2. Perfect group: tank, healer, dps\
\
These mobs summon non-elite adds (up to 3) as their health drops down. Once they are dead, they can be looted again with mining skill.\
\
Take care with agroing more mobs, move your target away from the area, since these elites wander around, and also Fel Reavers",
    "10132151094301510942007/09/10 01:13:46ZellynDuring this quest you will find a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=29476\"]Crimson Crystal Shard[/url] which is then turned in a few times and leads to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10351]Natural Remedies[/url], but isn't technically a quest-chain because quests come from two different NPCs.",
    "101327196390719632007/04/24 03:13:56TaemojitsuAs of 2.1.0, these now evade if you kite them more than a couple hundred meters, so it is no longer possible to kite them to the nearby temple. If you're trying to kill them then, make sure you kite them in a circle instead of just running away, or they'll up and evade on you.\
\
These can be soloed as a frost mage, possibly by any spec mage as long as you're good with snares. If you can't avoid aggroing the shardlings, you can use CoC/FN to root them all giving you time to nuke down the elite. The shardlings will despawn a little bit after the elite dies, so don't waste mana killing them if you can avoid it.\
\
The shardlings hit for about 225 on cloth, which is almost as much as the colossus once it splits a few times, so you can't just let them beat on you. :) A good opportunity to practice aoe kiting skills, or learn some if you don't have any!",
    "10132119794411098782007/07/13 02:31:24HancaySame, lvl 62 boomkin. Starfire, root, starfire and when roots break, moonfire and insect swarm. The first spawned add can be avoided. If you are at maximum range when he spawns the add, the add will just stand there and not aggro you (it'll simply disappear shortly after the fight is over) \
When the second add is spawned I have my trees summoned and treat myself with some mana (innervate or pot).\
If performed well you don't need any pots, and since I'm only a moderate boomkin I'm sure others can perform even better.\
\
Not sure if it matters a lot, but I was wearing quite a few feral pieces. Had only 150(!) spell damage and my starfires were hitting for ~850. \
The 200+ agi and ~5500 HP were certainly nice when I had 3 mobs hitting me. Usually 1 mob was focusing on my trees though. With barkskin/natures grace I could take out the others. \
\
All in all one of the first more challenging mobs you face while visiting the Outland.",
    "101328926650892662007/05/24 07:21:43darukaruThe colossi are leashed pretty tightly now, if you're going to try to fear-kite them don't do it on the side nearest the temple. If they go more than a couple feet in the wrong direction your work will be wasted. Still soloable (62 affliction lock), you just have to be careful.",
