    "9717144613501446132007/08/27 01:57:27snotnoseIt was a pain, but solo'd as a 70 Warlock.  Bring plenty of invisibility or lesser invisibility potions and use eye of kilrogg to scout.  For those that care, this is how I did it:\
\
1. Kill first two mobs (1 at a time).  Next is a linked group of 3, so didn't bother.\
2. Dismissed pet and went invisible, then ran.\
3. Took an immediate left and into the water to dump aggro.\
4. Back out of the water ('cause of the fish).\
5. Waited and took another invisibility potion and hugged the water line.\
6. Waited and took a fourth potion and went up.\
7. Took my last potion and got behind the frond.\
8. Summoned pet to keep mobs busy (just in case) and got frond.\
9. Died as I ran away screaming like a little girl.\
\
During the potion cooldowns, keep using Eye of Kilrogg to plan your next stopping point and to time one or two of the roaming mobs.  40+ minutes later, all done.  Maybe getting a group would have made more sense, but...",
