    "10329160101201601012007/09/28 23:24:37GaloheartAll these shutdown quests are soloabe. I'm a 70 Protection Paladin and i did the shutdown quest the first time i kept killing the NPC's one at a time as they kept running in to stop and restart the sequence and it kept going on and on. I would initiate stop and fight them as they run in and another NPC would sneak in the other side and restart the process.\
\
The easiest way i found to do this IF your a Melee Fighter was. Get full health and start shutdown. As the NPC's keep running in all you have to do is just play defence defending the controol while its in the 2 min shutdown. Don't try to kill and the NPC if you dont have to. JUst aggro tag them on hit and keep moving around to tag all the NPC's as they run in, but keep an eye out to see the NPC's as they run in and tag all of them. They all will be fighting you and thats what you want, them fighting you and not trying to restart the sequence. So just keep them occupied long enough for the 2 min sequence to finish. When its at Zero you will hear it and see it in your text log, then you can kill off the NPC's if most not alreasy dead. Easiest way as a Melee fighter i did all these shutdown quest and all in one rolling fight. Hope it helps some one else.",
