    "10218196573101965732007/12/05 17:10:52LuxrinMy group did this last night (all around lvl 64-65). The best advice I can give is to have a plan before you accept the quest. The first time I attempted the quest, our entire group was caught offguard and we wiped.\
\
With seduction and sheep, we had an easier time handling the mobs that spawned. What we did was.. we feared the mobs, crowd controlled, then killed. The frustrating thing is that the npc you're helping will sometimes break cc.",
    "102184479070447902007/03/01 21:28:09doombringerIf you have/had this quest and 'failed' it (it will not show Failed in your quest log), you can drop it and re-take it from the Cryo-Engineer.\
\
Basically, I had this quest in my log but did not complete it (our group wiped on it). When I returned to the instance I was able to get the Cryo-Engineer to appear by using the teleporter cube before Shaffar's room. However, the Engineer did not have a quest exclamation over his head. When someone in my group started the quest, I did not get a \"So and so has started this quest...\" warning. So, I DROPPED the quest in my log and was able to get it again from the Engineer.\
\
It's a very difficult quest. My group (high 60s, two 70s) cleared Tombs without a problem, but we wiped hard on this escort quest. By that time everyone was tired of Tombs and gave up... not that we could get the quest again without resetting the instance anyway. Blizz needs to tune this quest.",
    "102183261030326102007/02/08 08:10:36pfunkWe did this last night with\
