    "10218133303101333032007/08/06 15:28:47beemeriderLOL - I hadn't read up on the quest so I just fired it up while on a heroic run.  Don't try this at home!  We died quickly.",
    "1021840057170400572007/02/21 16:41:34MalentraI can confirm the following, having completed this quest last night:\
\
- all party members who have completed the pre-req quest will get credit for the escort quest, regardless of whether or not they initiate the encounter\
\
- the event is *not* difficult if the group uses good crowd control, coordination, and focus fire (namely all the group tactics that allow you to finish mana tombs in the first place)\
\
- it consists of 2-3 5 mob spawns in different areas as the NPC moves back to the entrance of the instance, followed by a relatively easy boss encounter (easier than any in the instance)\
\
- the NPC will give you a 30 second break (without moving) before the final boss encounter, giving anyone who died during some of the trash mob spawns to run back if necessary\
\
- ensure the instance is completely clear from the quest initiation point to the entrance of the instance; it will make things go a lot smoother\
\
- as far as I can tell the boss at the end does not drop anything of note (i.e. a trash mob loot table)\
\
- after killing the boss near the entrance of the instance, you will \"complete\" the quest, but you must leave the instance and talk to an NPC outside to turn it in",
    "102182878620287862007/02/01 08:12:33htniklesI didn't see to much of a problem with it being too difficult. I was tanking (druid-17k armor) with a 66 lock 68 mage and 65 druid. We 4 manned it. Our priest had to leave after the last boss",
