    "102184635980463592007/03/05 04:35:03hepathHave done this 3 times:\
1st attempt failed. Essentially the mobs in the second fight spawned close and fast and we wiped. Was a very balanced group but once the priest went down ... fubar!\
\
Quest remained as failed - I just removed it. \
\
2nd attempt worked we were more prepared; as a feral druid tanking I managed to get all aggro on me so healer concentrating on me with MA peeling them off. \
\
3rd attempt Failed.. For some reason the engineer in the middle of the infamous 2nd fight fight walked off! We think its because that we fought a little ways back from him and thus as with ll escort quests you get too far away from him and *poof* quest fails!\
\
This quest has similar analogies withthe ways mob spawn as the escort quest from the \"Shadow Tomb\" http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10887. In other words, unlike *old world quests* having tramled a path through the mobs to get the quest would normally mean it's clear; thus that quest enforces mobs to spawn on the way out and in the open meaning that unless you go slightly ahead you have respawns and quest mobs to deal with.\
\
I would suggest that \
a) Always clear every mob! Personally I prefer to kill the last boss for those with the quest. Saves time, and no reason to enter after an escort wipe.\
\
b) Be prepared - 2nd fight seesm to be the worst. Lay traps and have CC peeple ready. No time for Priest MC - they should be targetting the main tank who shoul dbe trying to keep aggro. Rest of group following the Main Assist. \
\
c) Between fights ensure mana people drink!! If duid is in group get them to innervate after 1st fight as that has least time for drinking; also allowing recylcle before final fight.\
\
Once second fight comlpete get ahead to fight 2 Nexus Terrors ahead leaving clear run through to final fight in the first dungeon room.\
\
I love this quest! It has taken the monotony out of escort quests! You have to be prepared, you have to think and act on your feet. \
\
This is a great dungeon for feral druids to cut their teeth as an MT. I was level 65 with ~12kAC and 1k AP; kit green and blue for TBC quests; nothing special. Resto shammy quite easily to keep me up.",
    "10218210111112058952007/12/30 21:27:19MadinI had the same issue and opened a ticket on the matter.\
3 and a half hours later, the GM said that the issue was that someone turned in the pre-req quest, Safety is Job One (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=10216), before we started the last boss.  It took us two attempts on the boss and apparently this was too long.  Cryo-Engineer Sha'heen, the quest-giver who starts the escort, disappears after X amount of time and we had waited just a hair too long.  >.>",
    "10218209170102091702007/12/29 05:45:40Eljewstertheres a few bugs with this quest, most notably if a member dies and releases even if he is rezed or runs back quickly, he may or may not receive credit on completion.\
 I know several people this has happened to and the GM's have told all of them more or less tough luck",
