    "1107890258500902582007/05/25 12:49:21aasartorHere's some detailed information about the dragon fights for this quest:\
\
There are a total of four dragons that you can summon for this quest - Rivendark, Obsidia, Furywing, and Insidion.  Any one of these four dragons will drop the Dragon Teeth quest item needed to finish the quest.  I felt that Rivendark was the easiest of the four, so I would recommend killing him first.  However, all four dragons are fairly easy - all of them can be killed in a reasonable time frame by a group of three people or more (tank, dps, healer)\
\
Rivendark can be summoned at (27, 64).  \
Obsidia can be summoned at (34, 54).\
Furywing can be summoned at (66, 14).\
Insidion can be summoned at (62, 7).\
\
All four dragons are nearly identical.  They are basically Onyxia clones tailored for groups of size 3-5 people.  They all possess the following abilities:\
\
Melee Attack - hit the tank for about 450-600 damage\
Cleave - standard cleave attack\
Flame Breath - frontal cone attack for about 600 fire damage\
Tail Swipe - knockback effect from the tail of the dragon (similar to Onyxia's).  Our fury warrior kept getting knocked backwards right off the ledge.\
Bellowing Roar - AoE fear, similar to Onyxia's\
\
Along with the afore mentioned abilities, each dragon possess exactly one unique ability:\
\
Rivendark - casts Corruption on random party members; identical to a warlock's Corruption\
Obsidia - casts Hellfire; identical to a warlock's Hellfire.  The Hellfire was hitting for about 500 fire damage a tick.\
Furywing - casts Wing Buffet on the tank;  similar to Firemaw's Wing Buffet.  This ability reduces the threat on primary target by a significant amount and knocks that target back.  It's not a big deal if the tank loses aggro, since Furywing is not immune to taunt.\
Insidion - casts a stacking Flame Buffet on the entire party;  similar to Firemaw's Flame Buffet.  This ability increases fire damage taken by the party and stacks a large number of times.  Since Insidion's only fire attack is Flame Breath, the only person really getting hit with fire damage should be the tank.  Thus, Flame Buffet stacking on the rest of the group shouldn't really matter.\
\
For loot, each dragon drops a green or blue item, as well as a scale unique to that dragon (lootable by everybody in the party).  If you obtain a scale from each of the four dragons, you can create this item  http://www.wowhead.com/?item=31942#M0z.",
    "11078131819101318192007/08/03 16:59:32FiresinAppears you need to do Bombing Run ( http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=11010 ) and Wrangle some Aether Rays ( http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=11065 ) before you will see this quest.",
