    "9853176011111276322007/10/28 13:41:49MairinAre you sure you don't mean 2.3? I just enslaved one and solo'd Gurok about 10 minutes ago as a 68 affliction lock with only around 600 ish +shadow damage. He zapped me once with nature damage for like 1400 (earth shock maybe?) which after a few drain/siphon life ticks was healed and he died with the felguard at 66% and me at full health. Threw a curse of doom on him with amplify curse up but Gurok was dead a little before it went off.",
    "9853165680511276322007/10/10 18:03:10angelspireTrue! Easily soloable as a lvl 67 lock. \
\
Just don't forget to gather all skulls BEFORE actually enslaving felguard. Otherwise you'll waste your enslave time on farming for those. \
\
So, \
\
1. Gather skulls (clearing all the way to the summoning place while farming will help alot), \
2. Go back, enslave felguard at the Forge Camp, \
3. Mount up, ride all the way to the summoning circle (ignore angry mobs, they'll forget about you when you'll reach the place), \
4. Get your skulls heated, summon, put felguard on Gurok and \
5. Nuke him badly. \
\
(!) Don't forget to start SUMMONING staying your back to the wall, so felguard will tank the bastard in the same position. Otherwise he'll throw your felguard away. \
\
(!!) Keep your back covered too. Since in my case, he aggroed me at like 5% or so. \
\
Only used healthstone at the end of fight. Ended with 40 - 50% health on me and more than 50% (don't recall the exact amount) on felguard. 1 min fight. \
\
Easy as hell if done properly.\
\
Used: \
* 2 shards - to enslave felguard and to re-summon blue bubble after the fight\
* lvl 67 Healthstone\
* +23 spell damage buff food\
\
Possible expenses:\
* 1 more shard for soulshatter if you don't use KTM and will rip aggro from felguard too early\
\
That's it.",
