    "9729147413301474132007/09/01 02:45:28grawssAccording to the Armory, this quest's minimum level is 63.",
    "9729127168101271682007/07/26 13:12:18RealUnimportantNot even soloable at 70... Feral Druid, running along and killing everything as fast as Fhwoor would move and either he times out and despawns (happened twice) or you make it to the final encounter with the elite and his 2 guards only to get wtfpwned - ok, so I'm not decked out in full epics, but even so at 70 and with an NPC assistant I'd expect to be able to take out a 66/67 elite!",
    "9729129993301299932007/07/31 18:20:47dangerfoxI recieved 979 rep for completing this quest, as I already had 20/1000 rep in Exalted.  Looks like this quest just finishes out your exalted bar, similar to the quest for Netherwing.\
\
As a lvl 70 enhancement shaman, I WAS able to solo this quest, although I was very slim on mana the entire time and had to mana pot twice.  Fhwoor doesn't slow down while he is in the camp so you have to move ahead of him and clear the way before he pulls too many.\
\
When Ssslith comes out, I simply put down my Earth Elemental totem to tank the adds and popped heroism, didn't have a problem with them at all.  I would still suggest any other level 70 to bring a friend, but if you're a shaman, you're in luck for this one.  :)",
    "972955225190552252007/03/22 06:11:26BruciatoConfirmed that you can get the quest only when you reach exalted with Sporeggar.\
\
This quest is not soloable. (maybe at level 70)\
\
First part:\
You just need to escort Fhwoor in the same place where you do the quest to kill 12 and 12 nagas. You can make it with some bandages and a couple of potions. I soloed this part as a warrior level 63. Fhwoor is quite strong and can solo a couple of mobs. So sometimes you can let him fight and in the while you can rest to full hp/mana. Like any other NPC, Fhwoor will regen to full health within seconds.\
\
Second part:\
When Fhwoor gets his item and you're going away, just outside the naga camp will spawn Ssslith, an elite level 65 with 3 adds (2 wars and 1 enchantress). Ssslith as i saw is immune to fear and piercing howl and hits for around 1k on plate (clearly dps geared). He even does a frostnova for around 800 dmg and it's quite annoying. I suggest you to bring a couple of friends to do this.",
    "97293726440372642007/02/16 21:53:02emidanIt's a real shame that Blizzard changed this quest to be accessed only at Exalted.  Back in the Beta you could pick it up at Honored (or maybe it was Revered?)  It definitely wasn't Exalted.  By the time I hit Exalted with these guys, I was already level 70.  The rewards didn't do much for me then.",
    "972956345120563452007/03/24 11:42:44JyL1These items are are excellent if you're below, say, 64.\
64-67, they're decent.\
68+ they're D/E or vendor food.\
\
Blizzard either needs to lower the rep requirement to honored or at the very least, revered, or buff the items significantly.\
\
It's unfair to force players to farm Sporeggar rep pre-70, putting their leveling to a grinding halt, or give them sub-par items at 70.",
    "972932493370324932007/02/08 00:29:57sinizuhNeed to be exalted to have access to this quest, but by the time you're there, this quest doesn't give you anything useful other than more time spent helping out those loveable Sporeggar.",
