    "1023116764npcEzekiel19715npc\"Dirty\" Larry1972011650The Sha'tar250110227210228310231410251510252610253",
    "10231202493102024932007/12/16 18:56:27Zurrif it takes you too long to beat him then you will not get a complete.",
    "102314134720413472007/02/23 22:41:59denstarkSolo'ed as a 67 Druid. It was a pain at first, but once I got the strategy down it was pretty easy. I talked to Dirty Larry and got to max distance while he was getting ready. Once he aggro'ed, I rooted him and went bear, to take out the adds. He arrived as I was killing the second add, and I killed the second add while using Frenzied Rejuv. I then bashed him (Or tried to, it actually missed) and then got out of bear form and rooted him. I backed off, and healed myself. I waited for about a minute, letting the roots tick and my mana rejuv, all the while my bash cooling down. I then went back in, and repeated the bash --> root combo again. Hope this helps!",
    "1023111977350119772006/12/09 03:24:38enasimaDirty Larry is the NPC you'll need to find and talk to for this quest. He can be found in the northwesternmost point of lower Shattrath with two of his buddies. Upon asking for the book he'll say a few lines and give you a countdown till he attacks you. During this countdown you are allowed to get the first shot. Dirty Larry himself is a 66 elite and his friends are 66 non elites. They are NOT immune to snaring/rooting, so kiting is a definite option if you're looking to solo this. If you kite him too far(past the nearby bank) he will reset.\
\
I was able to solo this guy at 64 as a frost mage, here's how I did it:\
1. Start the event.\
2. Sheep one of his friends instantly after talking to Larry.\
3. After one is sheeped, kill the other.\
4. Larry should be on you now kite him around. I used my water elemental to put up a little DPS and to help with frost nova'ing him. Keep up the kiting/dpsing till he dies -- remember to keep the other mob sheeped. I had to use cold snap and 3 frost shields.\
\
This may be extremely tough to solo for certain classes.",
    "102317719611340342007/05/03 15:21:49ViocheI soloed this as a level 67 shadow priest, started to fully dot up dirty then feared and kill the adds, used 2 netherweave nets + some running to make it. not to hard if you got decent gear",
    "10231147987201479872007/09/02 06:06:11TonyJackI just stood at the side as some other guy was doing it (was not in the same party as him), and as he beat down dirty larry, I got the objective completed too. I was just there for no reason at all, didnt even know I had the quest. kinda fancy",
    "102318363440836342007/05/15 18:39:10mrb4b00There is a glitch with this quest that makes it very easy(relatively).I found it accidentally by doing failed tries with my druid.\
\
1 Start the event, the mobs will turn yellow and become attackable after a while.\
\
2 They'll start running to you, don't engage them, simply run(on my druid i fought one of them but i decided to run instead).\
\
3. They'll reset after you run past the bank, now quick follow them back, there is a brief time period after they run back to their initial positions, that they are still attackable and yellow before they become talkable again.\
\
4. You can go close or range pull the elite off the group without worrying about his adds.  He has about 20K-30K HP and hits for 700-800 without armor, and has no special abilities.",
    "1023160138141237682007/03/31 13:05:22zealvurteI can confirm that you can complete the quest just by being nearby when someone does this quest.",
    "1023122493350224932007/01/21 17:37:45KylaraHe and his friends are at 43,29",
    "102318712911836342007/05/21 23:52:04deathbystereoThis same glitch happened to me on my Priest..  I would start the event, then go up on top of the nearby platform with my flying mount.  They would evade and eventually reset.  Then I went back to the ground and did a Holy Fire on the elite from maximum range and he single pulled without his adds.  Was a nice surprise since it makes it much easier to solo with a Holy priest without his friends.  I wasn't able to test whether or not this works every time...I could have just gotten lucky.",
    "102314196041237682007/02/25 07:14:26The013I rode up on my horde mage when some alliance guy was doing the quest, helped him subdue Larry and got quest credit. Go figure.",
    "1023123768150237682007/01/24 14:25:10JumpeeIt is possible to complete the quest if a different group defeats Dirty Harry.  I happened to ride up as an alliance group (im horde) just finished him up, and I got the \"Complete\" thing to pop up, and was able to talk to Harry and have him give me the next quest.",
