    "1088432067240320672007/02/07 06:16:11filtrHeroic mode is pretty tough and there is a 55 minute time limit to save the npcs that are being executed (Must save them to complete the quest). It's done easily after learning the pulls so probably not your first time through on heroic put should be able to do it the 2nd or 3rd try.",
    "10884112461311071512007/06/28 16:47:10PotjehDon't foget that after doing this quest chain you still get an epic resistance ring which could come in handy. Everyone aiming for The Eye or SSC should also aim for better playing skill/teamwork, and difficult heroics are perfect for that role.",
    "1088441817300418172007/02/24 22:59:51emidanIt should be stated that the 55-minute countdown does not start until you go through the second door in the Grand Warlock's room.  That is to say, once you kill the Grand Warlock (1st boss), and leave his room to continue onward, you receive a debuff - similar to 45 Baron runs - that shows you how much time you have remaining.",
    "108849092461666892007/05/26 09:47:29KapoueReply to Vulpes : If a group member DCs and you replaece him it's gonna be ok.  The problem arise when the DC'd person logs back in and his char is still in the instance.  At that point you have 6 members in the instance and every quest item despawns.  Same thing if a dead member is kicked out of the group and replaced before he gets his corpse back.",
